#. [unit_type], id=Aetheryon_Emperor, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Emperor_Taryen, race=human, gender=male
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Aetheryon_Emperor.cfg:4
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Emperor_Taryen.cfg:5
msgid "Emperor of Wesnoth"
msgstr "Emperador de Wesnoth"

#. [unit_type], id=Aetheryon_Emperor, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Aetheryon_Mage, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Aetheryon_Master, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Aetheryon_Emperor.cfg:18
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Aetheryon_Mage.cfg:18
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Aetheryon_Master.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Together with his twin sister Aethra, Aetheryon is the youngest offspring of "
"Emperor Taryen of Wesnoth, sired from his second wife, Ylleanne of "
"Elensefar, who died soon after her twin children were born. He and his "
"sister spent most of their childhood on their own at the northern city of "
"Dorest, raised by servants; the only relative who seemed to care about them "
"was their older half-brother, Aeldhoryan. When Aetheryon reached the age of "
"twelve, however, his father ordered him to start training as a soldier at "
"Weldyn's Royal Military Academy, but he chose to join Alduin instead. There "
"he was taught not only fire magic, but also Necromancy, thanks to a White "
"Necromancer – as the dark mages working for the Crown are known – sent by "
"his father. After graduating, he became Aeldhoryan's squire, following his "
"wherever he went, until finally settling at Kodakuni, where he was made "
"Province Governor by his brother. But Aetheryon has found much more to do "
"there than just ruling the Sogen: in the ancient ruins which gave the region "
"its name, he found traces of a long-lost knowledge... and an undreamed power "
"who could be harnessed by those who found it.\n"
"\n"
"People close to him often remark on how generous and kind he is; but "
"Aetheryon is also cunning and calculating, and as he tries to prove himself "
"a worthy heir of the Iron Dynasty, those two traits might serve him better "
"than kindness or generosity ever could."
msgstr ""
"Junto con su hermana gemela Aethra, Aetheryon es el hijo menor del Emperador "
"Taryen de Wesnoth, engendrado con su segunda esposa, Ylleanne de Elensefar, "
"quien murió poco después del nacimiento de sus hijos gemelos. Él y su "
"hermana pasaron la mayor parte de su infancia solos en la ciudad norteña de "
"Dorest, criados por sirvientes; el único familiar que parecía preocuparse "
"por ellos era su medio hermano mayor, Aeldhoryan. Sin embargo, cuando "
"Aetheryon cumplió doce años, su padre le ordenó comenzar su entrenamiento "
"como soldado en la Academia Militar Real de Weldyn, pero él eligió unirse a "
"Alduin en su lugar. Allí le enseñaron no solo magia de fuego, sino también "
"nigromancia, gracias a un Nigromante Blanco —como se conoce a los magos "
"oscuros que trabajan para la Corona— enviado por su padre. Tras graduarse, "
"se convirtió en escudero de Aeldhoryan, siguiéndolo a donde fuera, hasta que "
"finalmente se estableció en Kodakuni, donde su hermano lo nombró Gobernador "
"Provincial. Pero Aetheryon encontró mucho más que hacer allí que solo "
"gobernar a los Sogen: en las antiguas ruinas que dieron nombre a la región, "
"encontró rastros de un conocimiento perdido hace mucho… y un poder "
"inimaginable que podía ser aprovechado por quienes lo encontraran.\n"
"\n"
"Las personas cercanas a él suelen comentar lo generoso y amable que es; pero "
"Aetheryon también es astuto y calculador, y mientras intenta probarse como "
"un digno heredero de la Dinastía de Hierro, esas dos cualidades podrían "
"servirle mejor que la bondad o la generosidad."

