#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Olokun.cfg:433
msgid ""
"Olokun Maahes was born on the Arajunnan city of Ifeh from a Maat'Karian "
"father and a Chomi mother. According to them, his birth was a very "
"complicated one, and could have ended with both his and his mother's deaths, "
"were it not for the intervention of a 'sea queen' who healed the mother and "
"delivered the child in safety. The boy Olokun was always very curious about "
"that sea queen, and would often spend hours staring at the ocean as if "
"expecting her to appear once again, but all he found was a profound love for "
"the sea. As a youth, he moved to his father's city to study at New "
"Maat'Kare's Magic Academy; and there, amidst the burning sea of sand, he "
"felt very unhappy, to the point that he sought to return to Ifeh as soon as "
"his basic studies were completed. Instead, he received a mission from the "
"Academy's headmaster, Ankhmare Merwenut: to locate the legendary Myra of "
"Hiera'Shirsha reborn. And Olokun accepted it without thinking twice, as much "
"for the mission's importance as for the fact that it would allow him to "
"search for the sea queen who helped bring him into Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Olokun Maahes nació en la ciudad arajunnana de Ifeh de un padre maat'kariano "
"y una madre chomi. Según ellos, su nacimiento fue muy complicado y podría "
"haber terminado con la muerte de ambos, de no haber sido por la intervención "
"de una «reina del mar» que sanó a la madre y entregó al niño a salvo. El "
"niño Olokun siempre fue muy curioso acerca de esa reina del mar, y a menudo "
"pasaba horas mirando el océano como esperando que volviera a aparecer, pero "
"todo lo que encontró fue un amor profundo por el mar. De joven, se mudó a la "
"ciudad de su padre para estudiar en la Academia de Magia de Nueva Maat'Kare; "
"y allí, en medio del mar ardiente de arena, se sintió muy infeliz, al punto "
"de querer regresar a Ifeh tan pronto como terminara sus estudios básicos. En "
"cambio, recibió una misión del director de la Academia, Ankhmare Merwenut: "
"localizar a la legendaria Myra de Hiera'Shirsha renacida. Y Olokun la aceptó "
"sin pensarlo dos veces, tanto por la importancia de la misión como por el "
"hecho de que le permitiría buscar a la reina del mar que ayudó a traerlo a "
"Irdya."

