#. [unit_type], id=Runemaster_Algil, race=dwarf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Runemaster_Algil.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Runemaster"
msgstr "Maestro rúnico enano"

#. [unit_type], id=Runemaster_Algil, race=dwarf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Runemaster_Algil.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Except for those with almost supernatural skill, the highest rank a "
"runecrafter can rise to is that of the Dwarvish Runemaster. Striking blows "
"nearly as powerful as those of the best warriors, they would be fearsome "
"without their craft, but with it they are also nigh on invincible, since "
"their runes cause the physical blows of their enemies to deal less damage "
"than would be expected."
msgstr ""
"Aparte de aquellos con habilidades casi sobrenaturales, el mayor rango al "
"que puede llegar un herrero rúnico enano es el de maestro rúnico enano. "
"Golpean casi tan fuerte como los mejores guerreros, por lo que serían "
"temibles aun desprovistos de su arte, pero contar con él los hace casi "
"invencibles, ya que sus runas hacen que los enemigos hagan menos daño de lo "
"esperado."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Runemaster_Algil.cfg:40
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Udhark.cfg:33
msgid "hammer"
msgstr "martillo"

#. [unit_type], id=Sky Dragon Dummy, race=monster
#. [unit_type], id=Sky Dragon, race=monster
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon.cfg:7
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:5
msgid "High Dragon of the Sky"
msgstr "Alto Dragón del Cielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Sky Dragon Dummy, race=monster
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The Sky Dragon Svarballi is the mightiest of the three ancient High Dragons. "
"After being defeated by the other two, he was placed in a deep slumber that "
"lasted millennia. Now that he has been awakened again, every single being of "
"Irdya is at great danger.\n"
"\n"
"Having been created by the hands of the so-called Ancient Ones themselves, "
"Svarballi, by his power and nigh-invincibility, is the closest thing to a "
"god any dweller of Irdya has ever seen."
msgstr ""
"El Dragón del Cielo Svarballi es el más poderoso de los tres antiguos "
"Grandes Dragones. Tras ser derrotado por los otros dos, fue sumido en un "
"sueño profundo que duró milenios. Ahora que ha despertado de nuevo, todos "
"los seres de Irdya están en grave peligro.\n"
"\n"
"Habiendo sido creado por las manos de los llamados Ancianos, Svarballi, por "
"su poder y casi invencibilidad, es lo más cercano a un dios que cualquier "
"habitante de Irdya haya visto jamás."

#. [unit_type], id=Sky Dragon, race=monster
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The Sky Dragon Svarballi is the mightiest of the three ancient High Dragons. "
"He was defeated thrice in the past - first by Agniballi and Nitiballi, "
"second by Maat, and third by Myra of Hiera'Shirsha -, but none of them "
"managed to truly destroy Svarballi. Now that he has been awakened again, "
"every single being of Irdya is at great danger.\n"
"\n"
"Having been created by the hands of Ananke, the mightiest of the Avatars, "
"Svarballi, by his power and nigh-invincibility, is the closest thing to a "
"god any dweller of Irdya has seen in millennia."
msgstr ""
"El Dragón del Cielo Svarballi es el más poderoso de los tres antiguos "
"Grandes Dragones. Fue derrotado tres veces en el pasado —primero por "
"Agniballi y Nitiballi, segundo por Maat, y tercero por Myra de Hiera'Shirsha"
"—, pero ninguno de ellos logró destruir verdaderamente a Svarballi. Ahora "
"que ha sido despertado nuevamente, todo ser de Irdya está en gran peligro.\n"
"\n"
"Habiendo sido creado por las manos de Ananke, la más poderosa de los "
"Avatares, Svarballi, por su poder y casi invencibilidad, es lo más cercano a "
"un dios que cualquier habitante de Irdya ha visto en milenios."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:150
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Valerya.cfg:79
msgid "dragon fang"
msgstr "colmillo de dragón"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:163
msgid "Falling Heavens"
msgstr "Cielos en Caída"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:177
msgid "Rain of Fire"
msgstr "Lluvia de Fuego"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Sky_Dragon_Svarballi.cfg:191
msgid "Heaven's Spears"
msgstr "Lanzas del Cielo"

#. [unit_type], id=Star Master, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Star_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Star Master"
msgstr "Maestro Estelar"

#. [unit_type], id=Star Master, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/Star_Master.cfg:23
msgid ""
"One of the many contributions of Maat'Karians in the fields of science "
"concerns the observation of the stars; they were the ones who first noticed "
"that the sun itself was one of them, and that it shone so much brighter "
"because it was closer to Irdya. But it was Merwe of Medewi, the renowned "
"master of three lights who fought in the War of the Jewel alongside Akhen "
"Wadjet, who first noticed that Lucent mages could draw energy from the stars "
"of the night sky just like they drew it from the sun. Known as Uranometria, "
"this technique solves the greatest weakness of Lucent mages: their "
"vulnerability in nocturnal battles.\n"
"\n"
"And Uranometria was not Merwe's only contribution to Maat'Karian magic lore; "
"in fact, she established a brand new school of magic known as Sideral Arts, "
"centered around the study of astronomy and the influences of the stars on "
"Irdya. Though closely related to the Lucent Arts, this school sets itself "
"apart for its techniques, which employ the energy emitted by the stars in "
"spells that are often based on astronomical phenomena - such as the 'Star "
"Quake', which sends one massive pulse of bright arcane energy.\n"
"\n"
"The Sideral Arts were quick to earn the respect of Maat'Karians and to be "
"placed on the same prestigious level of the other Four Arts. Those who "
"master its extensive lore are known as Star Masters. Though usually focused "
"on studies and teaching, the destruction they can wreak on a battlefield is "
"both impressive and fearsome."
msgstr ""
"Una de las muchas contribuciones de los maat'karianos en los campos de la "
"ciencia se refiere a la observación de las estrellas; fueron ellos quienes "
"primero notaron que el sol mismo era una de ellas, y que brillaba mucho más "
"intensamente porque estaba más cerca de Irdya. Pero fue Merwe de Medewi, la "
"renombrada maestra de las tres luces que luchó en la Guerra de la Joya junto "
"a Akhen Wadjet, quien primero notó que los magos Lucentes podían extraer "
"energía de las estrellas del cielo nocturno de la misma forma que la "
"extraían del sol. Conocida como Uranometría, esta técnica resuelve la mayor "
"debilidad de los magos Lucentes: su vulnerabilidad en batallas nocturnas.\n"
"\n"
"Y la Uranometría no fue la única contribución de Merwe al conocimiento "
"mágico maat'kariano; de hecho, estableció una escuela de magia completamente "
"nueva conocida como Artes Siderales, centrada en el estudio de la astronomía "
"y las influencias de las estrellas en Irdya. Aunque estrechamente "
"relacionada con las Artes Lucentes, esta escuela se distingue por sus "
"técnicas, que emplean la energía emitida por las estrellas en hechizos que a "
"menudo se basan en fenómenos astronómicos —como el «Terremoto Estelar», que "
"envía un pulso masivo de brillante energía arcana.\n"
"\n"
"Las Artes Siderales rápidamente ganaron el respeto de los maat'karianos y se "
"colocaron al mismo nivel prestigioso que las otras Cuatro Artes. Aquellos "
"que dominan su extenso conocimiento son conocidos como Maestros Estelares. "
"Aunque normalmente se centran en estudios y enseñanza, la destrucción que "
"pueden causar en un campo de batalla es tanto impresionante como temible."

