#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:7
msgid "race^Maat'Karian"
msgstr "Maat'kariano"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:8
msgid "race+female^Maat'Karian"
msgstr "Maat'kariana"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:9
msgid "race^Maat'Karians"
msgstr "Maat'karianos"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:13
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians descend of Aragwaithi and Hannuks who journeyed from the "
"Great Continent to Netjer-Ta led by Myra of Hiera'Shirsha. They get their "
"name from the first city they built on their new land, Maat'Kare.\n"
"        \n"
"Maat'Kare's History is full of challenges and conflicts. The first of them "
"concerned the Maat'Karians' consolidation as an unified culture: their "
"ancestors, the Hannuks and the Aragwaithi, were historical enemies, and none "
"of them was willing to abandon their own respective cultures to embrace the "
"other's. This schism's most critical moment happened when a large group of "
"Aragwaithi decided to abandon Maat'Kare and settle in Argea, a continent to "
"the south of Netjer-Ta. It was Kun'lun, a Sage of the city's third "
"generation, who found the way to unite both cultures: with the aid of her "
"scholars, she revived the ancient language of the Windsong and made its "
"learning obligatory in the the schools, later turning it into the city's "
"official language. This common tongue broke many of the cultural barriers "
"between both peoples; and it was so popular that, in the following "
"generations, more and more aspects of the ancient Windsong culture were "
"adopted by the Maat'Karians - including names and their main symbol, the "
"Winged Protectress.\n"
"\n"
"Maat'Karian society sets itself apart from most of the world's civilizations "
"for two things. The first is that the power to rule the nation is not "
"concentrated on the hands of a single person; rather, it's shared by two "
"governing bodies, the Chamber of Sages, formed the nation's oldest and "
"wisest individuals; and the Chamber of Lords, formed by the generals and the "
"rulers of the towns and even villages. Since these Lords can be stripped of "
"their title if the citizens are unsatisfied with them, one can say that "
"Maat'Kare is a near-democratic nation. The second thing is the Maat'Karians' "
"high level of education: even at the tiniest village, every child is sent to "
"schools maintained by the Academy, and thought subjects such as History, "
"Geography, Grammar and Math. Thus, they become very well-educated citizens, "
"and are more participative in the country's politics. Furthermore, if the "
"child shows signs of magical talents, he/she is granted a place at the "
"Academy of Maat'Kare, which is arguably the best magic academy in the world "
"for forming masters in nearly all areas of magic, including the Elemental "
"and the Dark Arts.\n"
"\n"
"The population of Maat'Kare has never been high. In order not to be forced "
"to expand and take lands from their allies, the Maat'Karians are only "
"allowed to have two children for couple - though this birth control was only "
"established much time after Maat'Kare's founding. There's little internal "
"migration amongst Maat'Karians, who generally live their entire lives in the "
"cities they're born at.\n"
"\n"
"The Maat'Karian nation's formed by many near-independent cities and towns "
"all over the Land's End peninsula, in Netjer-Ta's utmost east, and in "
"Tarkyn's Meadows, which separates the peninsula from the rest of the "
"continent. There are also many Migdols - or armed outposts - in farther "
"locations which are under Maat'Karian control, such as the Gnoll Swamps and "
"the Windswept Cliffs.\n"
"\n"
"Maat'Karians do not differ from other human peoples, even though they live "
"in a different environment - that is, except for their resistance against "
"high temperatures, a natural adaptation to the Land's End peninsula's heat "
"and sunniness. On the other hand, they're more vulnerable to cold than most "
"humans."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos descienden de aragwaithi y hannuks que viajaron desde el "
"Gran Continente hasta Netjer-Ta liderados por Myra de Hiera'Shirsha. Reciben "
"su nombre de la primera ciudad que construyeron en su nueva tierra, "
"Maat'Kare.\n"
"\n"
"La historia de Maat'Kare está llena de desafíos y conflictos. El primero de "
"ellos concernió la consolidación de los maat'karianos como una cultura "
"unificada: sus ancestros, los hannuks y los aragwaithi, eran enemigos "
"históricos, y ninguno estaba dispuesto a abandonar su propia cultura para "
"abrazar la del otro. El momento más crítico de esta división ocurrió cuando "
"un gran grupo de aragwaithi decidió abandonar Maat'Kare y establecerse en "
"Argea, un continente al sur de Netjer-Ta. Fue Kun'lun, una Sabia de la "
"tercera generación de la ciudad, quien encontró la forma de unir ambas "
"culturas: con la ayuda de sus eruditos, revivió la antigua lengua de las "
"Hijas del Viento y hizo su aprendizaje obligatorio en las escuelas, "
"convirtiéndola luego en la lengua oficial de la ciudad. Esta lengua común "
"rompió muchas de las barreras culturales entre ambos pueblos; y fue tan "
"popular que, en las generaciones siguientes, cada vez más aspectos de la "
"antigua cultura de las Hijas del Viento fueron adoptados por los "
"maat'karianos —incluyendo nombres y su principal símbolo, la Protectora "
"Alada.\n"
"\n"
"La sociedad maat'kariana se distingue de la mayoría de las civilizaciones "
"del mundo por dos cosas. La primera es que el poder para gobernar la nación "
"no se concentra en las manos de una sola persona; más bien, se comparte "
"entre dos órganos de gobierno: la Cámara de Sabios, formada por los "
"individuos más viejos y sabios de la nación; y la Cámara de Señores, formada "
"por los generales y los gobernantes de las ciudades e incluso aldeas. Dado "
"que estos Señores pueden ser despojados de su título si los ciudadanos no "
"están satisfechos con ellos, se puede decir que Maat'Kare es una nación casi "
"democrática. La segunda cosa es el alto nivel de educación de los "
"maat'karianos: incluso en la aldea más pequeña, todos los niños son enviados "
"a escuelas mantenidas por la Academia, y se les enseña materias como "
"Historia, Geografía, Gramática y Matemáticas. Así, se convierten en "
"ciudadanos muy bien educados y más participativos en la política del país. "
"Además, si el niño muestra signos de talento mágico, se le concede un lugar "
"en la Academia de Maat'Kare, que es posiblemente la mejor academia de magia "
"del mundo para formar maestros en casi todas las áreas de la magia, "
"incluidas las Artes Elementales y las Artes Oscuras.\n"
"\n"
"La población de Maat'Kare nunca ha sido alta. Para no verse obligados a "
"expandirse y tomar tierras de sus aliados, a los maat'karianos solo se les "
"permite tener dos hijos por pareja —aunque este control de natalidad se "
"estableció mucho tiempo después de la fundación de Maat'Kare. Hay poca "
"migración interna entre los maat'karianos, quienes generalmente viven toda "
"su vida en las ciudades donde nacen.\n"
"\n"
"La nación maat'kariana está formada por muchas ciudades y pueblos casi "
"independientes en toda la península de Fin de la Tierra, en el extremo este "
"de Netjer-Ta, y en los Prados de Tarkyn, que separa la península del resto "
"del continente. También hay muchos Migdols —o puestos armados— en lugares "
"más lejanos que están bajo control maat'kariano, como los Pantanos de Gnolls "
"y los Acantilados Barridos por el Viento.\n"
"\n"
"Los maat'karianos no difieren de otros pueblos humanos, aunque viven en un "
"entorno diferente —es decir, excepto por su resistencia a las altas "
"temperaturas, una adaptación natural al calor y la soleada península de Fin "
"de la Tierra. Por otro lado, son más vulnerables al frío que la mayoría de "
"los humanos."

#. [race], id=chomi
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:162
msgid "race^Chom"
msgstr "Chom"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:163
msgid "race+female^Chom"
msgstr "Chom"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:164
msgid "race^Chomi"
msgstr "Chomi"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:168
msgid ""
"The Chomi are a people, or a confederation of culturally similar tribes, who "
"lived on the northern shores of the continent of Arajunna. They were "
"numerous, had relatively large cities and were good at sailing and trading, "
"but weren't very strong in terms of military, and their settlements weren't "
"fortified; thus, they were constantly being harassed by the neighbouring "
"Washraha and, in rarer occasions, by the giants known as Deshra.\n"
"\n"
"They stand out amongst the dwellers of Arajunna for their knowledge of "
"seafaring skills. Indeed, the sea plays a large role in the Chomi culture, "
"being the main source of the food they eat, the main defence against both "
"Washraha and Deshra (who are both afraid of the sea) and the stage of many "
"of their legends. Their vessels, albeit frail, can endure long journeys in "
"the stormy seas to the north of Arajunna.\n"
"\n"
"Each of the Chomi tribes is ruled by its own king; other than through "
"commerce, those tribes didn't have any strong relationship with each other. "
"Even though they do not excel at war, even the Washraha fear the day the "
"Chomi cities-state will unite, for such a day might mark the beginning of a "
"new era in the whole continent, such is the strength of the Chomi culture."
msgstr ""
"Los Chomi son un pueblo, o una confederación de tribus culturalmente "
"similares, que vivía en las costas norteñas del continente de Arajunna. Eran "
"numerosos, tenían ciudades relativamente grandes y eran buenos navegando y "
"comerciando, pero no eran muy fuertes en términos militares, y sus "
"asentamientos no estaban fortificados; por eso eran constantemente acosados "
"por los vecinos Washraha y, en ocasiones más raras, por los gigantes "
"conocidos como Deshra.\n"
"\n"
"Se destacan entre los habitantes de Arajunna por su conocimiento de las "
"habilidades marítimas. En efecto, el mar juega un papel importante en la "
"cultura chomi, siendo la principal fuente de alimento que comen, la "
"principal defensa contra tanto los Washraha como los Deshra (quienes temen "
"al mar) y el escenario de muchas de sus leyendas. Sus embarcaciones, aunque "
"frágiles, pueden soportar largos viajes en los mares tormentosos al norte de "
"Arajunna.\n"
"\n"
"Cada una de las tribus chomi es gobernada por su propio rey; aparte del "
"comercio, esas tribus no tenían ninguna relación fuerte entre sí. Aunque no "
"destacan en la guerra, incluso los Washraha temen el día en que las ciudades-"
"estado chomi se unan, pues tal día podría marcar el comienzo de una nueva "
"era en todo el continente, tal es la fuerza de la cultura chomi."

#. [race], id=washraha
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:325
msgid "race^Washraha"
msgstr "Washraha"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:326
msgid "race+female^Washrahani"
msgstr "Washrahani"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:327
msgid "race^Washrahan"
msgstr "Washrahan"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:332
msgid ""
"The nation of Washraha on Arajunna was formed when the Tarva dynasty came to "
"power and united several squabbling tribes and city-states to drive out the "
"giants known as Deshra. The ruler of the city-state of Shray Tahl, a warlord "
"known as Tarva Pah, was responsible for uniting these cities-state. His army "
"became known as the Washrajan, or knee-cutters, and they lent their name to "
"the resulting empire.\n"
"\n"
"When he became their first emperor, Tarva Pah became a fearful and paranoid "
"man. He instituted a paradigm of isolationism and xenophobia, building a "
"wall along their land borders as mighty Washrahan scouting groups watched "
"over the savannah and the mountains surrounding his lands, swiftly putting a "
"violent end to anyone who came exploring or seeking trade or refuge. These "
"policies were carried out by his successors for generations; the Washrahan "
"themselves often visited neighbouring lands and people, but with ill-"
"intention: for in the belligerent Washrahan culture, the warriors must be "
"constantly proving their mettle in combat, and so they are often raiding "
"smaller foreign tribes, though seldom destroying any of them completely.\n"
"\n"
"In the reign of Empress Sa-Tarva, however, the Washraha decided to expand, "
"razing countless towns and villages and conquering vast extensions of land, "
"becoming the absolute power in Arajunna. Their power became unrivalled "
"indeed, and it could have expanded to realms far beyond their continent, "
"were it not for the Washraha's almost superstitious fear of the sea."
msgstr ""
"La nación de Washraha en Arajunna se formó cuando la dinastía Tarva llegó al "
"poder y unió varias tribus y ciudades-estado en disputa para expulsar a los "
"gigantes conocidos como Deshra. El gobernante de la ciudad-estado de Shray "
"Tahl, un señor de la guerra conocido como Tarva Pah, fue el responsable de "
"unir estas ciudades-estado. Su ejército se conoció como los washrajan, o "
"cortadores de rodillas, y prestaron su nombre al imperio resultante.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando se convirtió en su primer emperador, Tarva Pah se volvió un hombre "
"temeroso y paranoico. Instituyó un paradigma de aislacionismo y xenofobia, "
"construyendo un muro a lo largo de sus fronteras terrestres mientras "
"poderosos grupos de exploración washrahan vigilaban la sabana y las montañas "
"que rodeaban sus tierras, poniendo fin violento rápidamente a cualquiera que "
"viniera explorando o buscando comercio o refugio. Estas políticas fueron "
"llevadas a cabo por sus sucesores durante generaciones; los propios "
"washrahan a menudo visitaban tierras y pueblos vecinos, pero con malas "
"intenciones: pues en la cultura beligerante washrahan, los guerreros deben "
"probar constantemente su valía en combate, y por eso a menudo saquean tribus "
"extranjeras más pequeñas, aunque rara vez destruyen alguna por completo.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, en el reinado de la Emperatriz Sa-Tarva, los Washraha "
"decidieron expandirse, arrasando incontables pueblos y aldeas y conquistando "
"vastas extensiones de tierra, convirtiéndose en el poder absoluto en "
"Arajunna. Su poder se volvió realmente sin rival, y podría haber expandido a "
"reinos mucho más allá de su continente, de no ser por el miedo casi "
"supersticioso de los Washraha al mar."

#. [race], id=deshra
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:393
msgid "race^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:394
msgid "race+female^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:395
msgid "race^Deshrai"
msgstr "Deshrai"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:401
msgid "The Deshra (literally "
msgstr "Los Deshra (literalmente "

#. [race], id=trueelemental
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:458
msgid "race^True Elemental"
msgstr "Elemental Verdadero"

#. [race], id=trueelemental
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:459
msgid "race^True Elementals"
msgstr "Elementales Verdaderos"

#. [race], id=trueelemental
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:463
msgid ""
"There are a few mage academies over the world which teach a form of magic "
"that calls upon the powers of nature, enabling the mage to summon creatures "
"known as Elementals. What they don't know is that these creatures are but an "
"imitation of the true elementals, created from nature's energy and that of "
"the mage. True elementals are nothing less than the spirits of nature "
"themselves, materialized into the mortal plane with the aid of a true nature "
"mage.\n"
"Elementalists must not be blamed for not knowing that, though, for the one "
"with the power to materialize true elementals is still to be born."
msgstr ""
"Hay algunas academias de magos en el mundo que enseñan una forma de magia "
"que invoca los poderes de la naturaleza, permitiendo al mago convocar "
"criaturas conocidas como Elementales. Lo que no saben es que estas criaturas "
"son solo una imitación de los elementales verdaderos, creados a partir de la "
"energía de la naturaleza y la del mago. Los elementales verdaderos no son "
"menos que los espíritus de la naturaleza mismos, materializados en el plano "
"mortal con la ayuda de un mago de la naturaleza verdadero.\n"
"A los elementalistas no se les puede culpar por no saberlo, pues quien tiene "
"el poder de materializar elementales verdaderos aún está por nacer."

#. [race], id=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:651
msgid "race^Sogen"
msgstr "Sogen"

#. [race], id=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:652
msgid "race+female^Sogen"
msgstr "Sogen"

#. [race], id=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:653
msgid "race^Sogen-Ningen"
msgstr "Sogen-Ningen"

#. [race], id=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:657
msgid ""
"The Sogen tribes are the descendants of people who lived on the steppes of "
"the Great Continent' Far East for many ages. Adept of horse-riding and "
"dexterous at archery, they were the absolute lords of the steppes for more "
"than four thousand years.\n"
"\n"
"However, everything changed when the steppes became overcrowded. The "
"abundance of crops sucked slender rivers crossing the steppes dry, and the "
"soil became infertile. With plants dying out, the steppes became "
"increasingly barren; when the Second Sun rose, the increased heat started a "
"process of desertification in those once green lands. The steppe peoples, "
"frightened by the changes and angered by famine, fought each other in a "
"series of devastating conflicts, and most of them disappeared from the face "
"of earth.\n"
"\n"
"The only ones who survived that chaos were those who wisely chose to leave "
"their ancestral land for the forested and wetter west. They settled in a "
"land full of ruins of an once mighty empire which featured in their oldest "
"legends, and called it Kodakuni, which, in their tongue, literally means "
"'Ancient Land'. Living in a land full of forests, hills and valleys opened "
"new ways of life to the Sogen-Ningen, the People of the Steppes: some "
"dedicated to farming and were called Yasai-Ningen, or Farming Folk; others "
"dedicated to foot warfare and became known as Ken-Ningen, or Sword Folk; and "
"those who insisted on preserving their ancestors' traditions and ways of "
"life were known as Uma-Ningen, or Horse Folk."
msgstr ""
"Las tribus sogen son descendientes de personas que vivieron en las estepas "
"del Lejano Oriente del Gran Continente durante muchas edades. Expertos en "
"montar a caballo y diestros en el arco, fueron los señores absolutos de las "
"estepas durante más de cuatro mil años.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, todo cambió cuando las estepas se volvieron superpobladas. La "
"abundancia de cultivos agotó los delgados ríos que cruzaban las estepas, y "
"el suelo se volvió infértil. Con las plantas muriendo, las estepas se "
"volvieron cada vez más áridas; cuando se levantó el Segundo Sol, el calor "
"aumentado inició un proceso de desertificación en aquellas tierras que "
"alguna vez fueron verdes. Los pueblos de las estepas, asustados por los "
"cambios y enfurecidos por el hambre, se enfrentaron entre sí en una serie de "
"conflictos devastadores, y la mayoría desapareció de la faz de la tierra.\n"
"\n"
"Los únicos que sobrevivieron al caos fueron aquellos que sabiamente "
"eligieron abandonar su tierra ancestral por el oeste boscoso y más húmedo. "
"Se establecieron en una tierra llena de ruinas de un antiguo imperio "
"poderoso que aparecía en sus leyendas más antiguas, y la llamaron Kodakuni, "
"que en su lengua significa literalmente 'Tierra Antigua'. Vivir en una "
"tierra llena de bosques, colinas y valles abrió nuevas formas de vida a los "
"Sogen-Ningen, el Pueblo de las Estepas: algunos se dedicaron a la "
"agricultura y fueron llamados Yasai-Ningen, o Pueblo Agricultor; otros se "
"dedicaron a la guerra a pie y se conocieron como Ken-Ningen, o Pueblo de la "
"Espada; y aquellos que insistieron en preservar las tradiciones y formas de "
"vida de sus ancestros fueron conocidos como Uma-Ningen, o Pueblo del Caballo."

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:764
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:765
msgid "Woodlander"
msgstr "Habitante del Bosque"

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:766
msgid "Woodlanders"
msgstr "Habitantes del Bosque"

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:769
msgid ""
"The Woodlanders are a quite variegated population. Indeed, this faction "
"isn't composed by only one race but by some different ones with some common "
"traits. In addition to their shy and lone nature (that makes them very "
"skilled in hiding and ambushes), these warriors have in common the choice of "
"the forest as their habitat; some forced to it, others for their own will. "
"The members of this group are mainly legendary creatures, whose existence is "
"still ignored by some. Indeed those who had met this army rarely had such a "
"long life to be able to tell it! Many legends are told about some of them, "
"wherein sometimes they are evil wizards who draw their prey where they can "
"be lethal (into the wood), other times they are told as good creatures "
"living a nature-friendly and cheerful life. However, wise travelers usually "
"avoid those places where the shadow of the trees eats the light and "
"thousands glittering eyes are seen in the dark."
msgstr ""
"Los Habitantes del Bosque son una población bastante variada. En efecto, "
"esta facción no está compuesta por una sola raza sino por varias diferentes "
"con algunos rasgos comunes. Además de su naturaleza tímida y solitaria (que "
"los hace muy hábiles en esconderse y tender emboscadas), estos guerreros "
"tienen en común la elección del bosque como su hábitat; algunos obligados a "
"ello, otros por voluntad propia. Los miembros de este grupo son "
"principalmente criaturas legendarias, cuya existencia aún es ignorada por "
"algunos. ¡En efecto, quienes han encontrado a este ejército rara vez han "
"vivido lo suficiente para contarlo! Muchas leyendas se cuentan sobre algunos "
"de ellos, en las que a veces son magos malvados que atraen a sus presas "
"donde pueden ser letales (dentro del bosque), otras veces se les describe "
"como criaturas buenas que viven una vida amistosa con la naturaleza y "
"alegre. Sin embargo, los viajeros sabios suelen evitar esos lugares donde la "
"sombra de los árboles devora la luz y miles de ojos brillantes se ven en la "
"oscuridad."

#. [race], id=baryag
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1024
msgid "race^Baryag"
msgstr "Baryag"

#. [race], id=baryag
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1025
msgid "race+female^Baryag"
msgstr "Baryag"

#. [race], id=baryag
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1026
msgid "race^Baryags"
msgstr "Baryags"

#. [race], id=baryag
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1030
msgid ""
"The Baryags are one of the many human civilizations on the Great Continent, "
"rulers of the vast Emerald Plains. Their ancestors were both a human nation "
"who lived on those plains since before Wesnoth's founding and an eastern "
"people whom some believe to have been an offset of the Aragwaithi. They're "
"known for their belligerence: in their culture, fighting skills are regarded "
"as one of highest values, and so even a common peasant knows how to fight. "
"This belligerence has led them to war countless times, first against the "
"elves, then against the drakes and the orcs; and, when both of these enemies "
"were too strong, they squabbled amongst themselves.\n"
"\n"
"In spite of their aggressiveness, they can be extremely loyal allies and "
"dedicated friends to those who earn their respect. When a great orcish "
"sovereign rose in the north in 997 YW, the Baryags accepted allying with the "
"Northern Alliance in order to fight him; in the centuries to come, Mhreghost "
"- the unofficial Baryag capital, built by the plains' original inhabitants - "
"welcomed many heralds from the Alliance.\n"
"\n"
"The contact with the Northern Alliance led the Baryags to learn more about "
"the world outside the plains, as did the expansion of the Wesnothian Empire "
"towards their frontiers. Unlike the men of the Northern Alliance, the "
"Wesnothians arrived at the Emerald Plains with arrogant demeanour and "
"covetous eyes, and the result was that they were brutally repelled by the "
"Baryags. For many decades, Baryags and Wesnothians fought each other in a "
"series of conflicts known as the Emerald Wars. As of 1400 YW, the Emerald "
"Plains remain under Baryag control, but Wesnoth still hasn't given up on "
"conquering the region.\n"
"\n"
"And one of the main responsibles for the continued Baryag presence in the "
"region was Dragana Vasilya. Being the heiress of the House of Ivarik - the "
"first High King of Baryags, son of an easterner man and a native noblewoman "
"- she was to be the supreme ruler of her people, but, as Baryags usually "
"only acknowledge the power of arms, she had to forge her authority with "
"steel and blood. And such was her prowess as a fight and a commander and her "
"charisma that she even managed to stop the Baryag lords from fighting each "
"other. Her victory over the orcish sovereign Red-Eye Bork - the one moment "
"in her people's History when the Baryags truly feared being destroyed - was "
"decisive to establish her as the supreme authority in the Emerald Plains, "
"faithfully followed and obeyed by all Baryags."
msgstr ""
"Los Baryags son una de las muchas civilizaciones humanas del Gran "
"Continente, gobernantes de las vastas Llanuras Esmeralda. Sus ancestros "
"fueron tanto una nación humana que vivía en esas llanuras desde antes de la "
"fundación de Wesnoth como un pueblo oriental que algunos creen que fue un "
"derivado de los aragwaithi. Son conocidos por su beligerancia: en su "
"cultura, las habilidades de combate se consideran uno de los valores más "
"altos, y por eso incluso un campesino común sabe luchar. Esta beligerancia "
"los ha llevado a la guerra innumerables veces, primero contra los elfos, "
"luego contra los dracos y los orcos; y, cuando ambos enemigos eran demasiado "
"fuertes, se peleaban entre sí.\n"
"\n"
"A pesar de su agresividad, pueden ser aliados extremadamente leales y amigos "
"dedicados para quienes ganan su respeto. Cuando un gran soberano orco se "
"alzó en el norte en 997 YW, los Baryags aceptaron aliarse con la Alianza del "
"Norte para combatirlo; en los siglos venideros, Mhreghost —la capital no "
"oficial baryag, construida por los habitantes originales de las llanuras— "
"recibió a muchos heraldos de la Alianza.\n"
"\n"
"El contacto con la Alianza del Norte llevó a los Baryags a aprender más "
"sobre el mundo fuera de las llanuras, al igual que la expansión del Imperio "
"Wesnothiano hacia sus fronteras. A diferencia de los hombres de la Alianza "
"del Norte, los wesnothianos llegaron a las Llanuras Esmeralda con actitud "
"arrogante y ojos codiciosos, y el resultado fue que fueron brutalmente "
"repelidos por los Baryags. Durante muchas décadas, baryags y wesnothianos se "
"enfrentaron en una serie de conflictos conocidos como las Guerras Esmeralda. "
"A partir de 1400 YW, las Llanuras Esmeralda permanecen bajo control baryag, "
"pero Wesnoth aún no ha renunciado a conquistar la región.\n"
"\n"
"Y una de las principales responsables de la presencia continua baryag en la "
"región fue Dragana Vasilya. Siendo la heredera de la Casa de Ivarik —el "
"primer Gran Rey de los Baryags, hijo de un hombre oriental y una noble nativa"
"— debía ser la gobernante suprema de su pueblo, pero, como los baryags "
"suelen reconocer solo el poder de las armas, tuvo que forjar su autoridad "
"con acero y sangre. Y tal fue su destreza como luchadora y comandante y su "
"carisma que incluso logró detener a los señores baryag de pelear entre sí. "
"Su victoria sobre el soberano orco Ojo Rojo Bork —el único momento en la "
"historia de su pueblo en que los Baryags temieron verdaderamente ser "
"destruidos— fue decisiva para establecerla como la autoridad suprema en las "
"Llanuras Esmeralda, fielmente seguida y obedecida por todos los Baryags."

#. [race], id=dryad
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1093
msgid "race^Dryad"
msgstr "Dríada"

#. [race], id=dryad
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1094
msgid "race^Dryads"
msgstr "Dríadas"

#. [race], id=warg
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1106
msgid "race^Warg"
msgstr "Huargo"

#. [race], id=warg
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1107
msgid "race+female^Warg"
msgstr "Huargo"

#. [race], id=warg
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1108
msgid "race^Wargs"
msgstr "Huargos"

#. [race], id=warg
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1112
msgid ""
"Warg are also known as wolfmen. They live in the wilds and woods in almost "
"any climate, some favor the lush jungle, others the arctic woods, others "
"alpine mountains. The warg tend to live in packs or clans, and establish "
"their hunting grounds where they tend not to like intruders. Although "
"hunters, they are for the most part peaceful, however they have a primal "
"blood-lust, that can be inspired by various things, especially if vampires "
"are involved."
msgstr ""
"Los huargos también son conocidos como hombres-lobo. Viven en zonas salvajes "
"y bosques en casi cualquier clima: algunos prefieren la selva exuberante, "
"otros los bosques árticos, otros las montañas alpinas. Los huargos suelen "
"vivir en manadas o clanes y establecen sus terrenos de caza donde no suelen "
"tolerar intrusos. Aunque son cazadores, en su mayoría son pacíficos; sin "
"embargo, tienen una sed de sangre primal que puede desencadenarse por varias "
"causas, especialmente si hay vampiros de por medio."

#. [race], id=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1265
msgid "race^Black Elf"
msgstr "Elfo Negro"

#. [race], id=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1266
msgid "race+female^Black Elf"
msgstr "Elfa Negra"

#. [race], id=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1267
msgid "race^Black Elves"
msgstr "Elfos Negros"

#. [race], id=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1269
msgid ""
"Since times immemorial, elves have lived in the largest forests of the "
"continent; in fact, they've lived there for so long that many people believe "
"that they depend on their forests to survive, that they might die if they "
"stay away from their trees for too long. This is, of course, an erroneous "
"belief, though a forgivable one; because of their preference for woody "
"environments, few people know of the elves' high adapting skills, which may "
"be greater even than the humans'. Furthermore, few know of how the elves "
"were once given to exploring and colonizing: long before Wesnoth was "
"founded, the elves wandered about the Great Continent, settling not only on "
"uninhabited forests, but also uninhabited mountains and, surprisingly, even "
"caves. Those elves who chose to live in the dark and harsh underground "
"adapted to it, becoming as adept to the caves as the dwarves themselves; one "
"of their adaptations was changing the elves' traditional green clothing for "
"black garments, which earned them the name given by their forest kin."
msgstr ""
"Desde tiempos inmemoriales, los elfos han vivido en los bosques más grandes "
"del continente; de hecho, han vivido allí durante tanto tiempo que muchas "
"personas creen que dependen de sus bosques para sobrevivir, que podrían "
"morir si se alejan de sus árboles demasiado tiempo. Esto es, por supuesto, "
"una creencia errónea, aunque comprensible; debido a su preferencia por "
"entornos boscosos, pocas personas conocen las altas habilidades de "
"adaptación de los elfos, que pueden ser incluso mayores que las de los "
"humanos. Además, pocos saben cómo los elfos alguna vez se dedicaron a "
"explorar y colonizar: mucho antes de que se fundara Wesnoth, los elfos "
"vagaron por el Gran Continente, estableciéndose no solo en bosques "
"deshabitados, sino también en montañas deshabitadas y, sorprendentemente, "
"incluso en cuevas. Esos elfos que eligieron vivir en el oscuro y duro "
"subsuelo se adaptaron a él, volviéndose tan hábiles en las cuevas como los "
"propios enanos; una de sus adaptaciones fue cambiar la vestimenta verde "
"tradicional de los elfos por prendas negras, lo que les ganó el nombre dado "
"por sus parientes del bosque."

#. [race], id=avatar
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1329
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1331
msgid "race^Avatars"
msgstr "Avatares"

#. [race], id=avatar
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1330
msgid "race+female^Avatar"
msgstr "Avatar"

#. [race], id=avatar
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1334
msgid ""
"The Avatars are the first sentient beings to appear in the universe. It is "
"not known, even to themselves, how they came into existence; what is known "
"is that they appeared as thinking manifestations of the forces which existed "
"in unbound shape in the first aeon.\n"
"\n"
"Some of the Avatars whose names have been heard by human ears were: Ananke, "
"Demere, Vanadya, Nannan, Quezatla and Moriann. This is all the information "
"on them that has survived to this day:\n"
"\n"
"Ananke was the Avatar of Will, the Mind which bends everything that it at "
"pleasure; it is believed that she was the first to appear, and the one who "
"gave origin to all other Avatars; she also gave the ability of sentience to "
"the most developed living beings.\n"
"\n"
"Demere was the Avatar of Life, the Mother from whom the energy which gives "
"matter the ability to move and evolve on its own has originated. Albeit "
"loving of her children and fond of innocent creatures, she was somewhat "
"fierce-tempered and wilful; she did not live on planets with harsh weather, "
"and so only a few worlds sheltered living beings - her favourite being "
"Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Vanadya was the Avatar of Magic, the living incarnation of the one energy in "
"the universe that is truly eternal. She is arguably the most powerful of the "
"Avatars - with the (debatable) exception of Ananke - and the last one to "
"share her essence with others. It is told that she was extremely arrogant, "
"and refused to share her true essence with others for many aeons, until she "
"met a human man called An-Usrukhar, with whom she fell in love. After "
"meeting him, she decided to give other living beings the ability of "
"harnessing magic - though not everyone received such gift.\n"
"\n"
"Nannan was the Avatar of Time, also known as Avatar of Wisdom, Balance and "
"Death. Hers was the power over the flow of time, which she wisely did not "
"share with anyone - though she did allow a few ways through which those with "
"the keenest senses may see both the future and the past. She was also the "
"one responsible for setting a finite lifespan on every living and sentient "
"being in the universe, Avatars included, arguing that new generations are "
"the key of evolution, and that they would not survive if the older ones "
"persisted.\n"
"\n"
"Quezatla was the Avatar of Light, the Mother of Stars and master of the "
"Arcane, one of the most mysterious forms of energy in the universe. She was "
"also known as the Avatar of Peace due to her calm, pacifist and helpful "
"nature.\n"
"\n"
"Moriann was the Avatar of Souls, twin sister of Quezatla, with whom she "
"originally shared the mastery of the Arcane. Moriann was the first Avatar to "
"die, as she sacrificed her own existence so that her Soul Essence might "
"become souls for the countless living beings in the universe - for the soul "
"was the link which connected Mind and body, and so it was needed for life. "
"Her corpse still lay in the Land of the Dead."
msgstr ""
"Los Avatares son los primeros seres sensibles que aparecieron en el "
"universo. No se sabe, ni siquiera para ellos mismos, cómo llegaron a "
"existir; lo que se sabe es que aparecieron como manifestaciones pensantes de "
"las fuerzas que existían en forma ilimitada en el primer eón.\n"
"\n"
"Algunos de los Avatares cuyos nombres han sido escuchados por oídos humanos "
"fueron: Ananke, Demere, Vanadya, Nannan, Quezatla y Moriann. Esta es toda la "
"información sobre ellos que ha sobrevivido hasta hoy:\n"
"\n"
"Ananke fue el Avatar de la Voluntad, la Mente que dobla todo lo que desea a "
"su placer; se cree que fue la primera en aparecer, y la que dio origen a "
"todos los demás Avatares; también otorgó la capacidad de sensibilidad a los "
"seres vivos más desarrollados.\n"
"\n"
"Demere fue el Avatar de la Vida, la Madre de la cual se originó la energía "
"que da a la materia la capacidad de moverse y evolucionar por sí misma. "
"Aunque amorosa con sus hijos y aficionada a las criaturas inocentes, tenía "
"un temperamento algo feroz y voluntarioso; no vivía en planetas con climas "
"duros, y por eso solo unos pocos mundos albergaban seres vivos —su favorito "
"siendo Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Vanadya fue el Avatar de la Magia, la encarnación viva de la única energía "
"en el universo que es verdaderamente eterna. Es posiblemente la más poderosa "
"de los Avatares —con la (debatible) excepción de Ananke— y la última en "
"compartir su esencia con otros. Se cuenta que era extremadamente arrogante, "
"y se negó a compartir su verdadera esencia con otros durante muchos eones, "
"hasta que conoció a un hombre humano llamado An-Usrukhar, de quien se "
"enamoró. Tras conocerlo, decidió otorgar a otros seres vivos la capacidad de "
"aprovechar la magia —aunque no todos recibieron tal don.\n"
"\n"
"Nannan fue el Avatar del Tiempo, también conocido como Avatar de la "
"Sabiduría, el Equilibrio y la Muerte. Suya era el poder sobre el flujo del "
"tiempo, que sabiamente no compartió con nadie —aunque sí permitió algunas "
"formas mediante las cuales aquellos con los sentidos más agudos podían ver "
"tanto el futuro como el pasado. También fue la responsable de establecer una "
"duración finita de vida en todo ser vivo y sensible del universo, incluidos "
"los Avatares, argumentando que las nuevas generaciones son la clave de la "
"evolución, y que no sobrevivirían si los mayores persistieran.\n"
"\n"
"Quezatla fue el Avatar de la Luz, la Madre de las Estrellas y maestra del "
"Arcano, una de las formas de energía más misteriosas del universo. También "
"era conocida como el Avatar de la Paz debido a su naturaleza calmada, "
"pacifista y servicial.\n"
"\n"
"Moriann fue el Avatar de las Almas, hermana gemela de Quezatla, con quien "
"originalmente compartía el dominio del Arcano. Moriann fue el primer Avatar "
"en morir, ya que sacrificó su propia existencia para que su Esencia de Alma "
"se convirtiera en almas para los innumerables seres vivos del universo —pues "
"el alma era el vínculo que conectaba la Mente y el cuerpo, y por lo tanto "
"era necesaria para la vida. Su cadáver aún yace en la Tierra de los Muertos."

#. [race], id=celestial
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1353
msgid "race^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1354
msgid "race+female^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1355
msgid "race^Celestials"
msgstr "Celestiales"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/factions.cfg:1359
msgid ""
"The Celestials have vestigial wings that for most of them do not mature. "
"Celestials believe that light and darkness each have power, and they choose "
"as a culture to fight for the light, and to spread it through-out the world. "
"They are a militaristic society with great law and order that gives them "
"strength and unity which caries over into their style of fighting. The order "
"and unified purpose of celestial society tends to make them form larger "
"nations than the other factions giving the Celestials great military "
"strength."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales tienen alas vestigiales que en la mayoría no llegan a "
"desarrollarse. Los celestiales creen que la luz y la oscuridad tienen poder "
"propio, y eligen como cultura luchar por la luz y difundirla por todo el "
"mundo. Son una sociedad militarista con gran ley y orden que les otorga "
"fuerza y unidad, lo que se refleja en su estilo de combate. El orden y "
"propósito unificado de la sociedad celestial tiende a hacer que formen "
"naciones más grandes que otras facciones, otorgando a los celestiales una "
"gran fuerza militar."

