#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Marksman, race=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Marksman.cfg:5
msgid "Marksman"
msgstr "Tirador"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Marksman, race=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Marksman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Adapting to the crossbow was not easy for the elves - less because of their "
"skill in using it, and more for their refusal to take such an unelegant "
"weapon for themselves. Those who had no qualm about that, however, managed "
"to join their innate elven skill to the crossbow's own power, thus becoming "
"a deadly force on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"Adaptarse a la ballesta no fue fácil para los elfos —menos por su habilidad "
"para usarla, y más por su negativa a tomar un arma tan poco elegante para sí "
"mismos. Aquellos que no tuvieron reparos al respecto, sin embargo, lograron "
"unir su habilidad élfica innata al poder propio de la ballesta, "
"convirtiéndose así en una fuerza mortal en el campo de batalla."

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Marshal, race=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Marshal.cfg:5
msgid "Marshal"
msgstr "Mariscal"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Slayer, race=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Slayer.cfg:5
msgid "Slayer"
msgstr "Asesino"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Slayer, race=blackelf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Slayer.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Despite the prejudice that crossbowman elves used to suffer, the danger they "
"posed to any underground foe quickly earned them the respect of their peers "
"- and that led to the popularization of their weapon of choice, with "
"crafters developing harder, stronger and more accurate crossbows. As "
"crossbowmen were given hunting and assassination missions, they became "
"masters of moving stealthily in dark environments.\n"
"\n"
"That newly-acquired ability, together with their precision and the power of "
"their special crossbows, earned them an even greater respect from their "
"fellow elves, and the dread of anyone who opposes them - both in the "
"underground and on the surface."
msgstr ""
"A pesar del prejuicio que solían sufrir los arqueros de ballesta elfos, el "
"peligro que representaban para cualquier enemigo subterráneo rápidamente les "
"ganó el respeto de sus compañeros —y eso llevó a la popularización de su "
"arma preferida, con artesanos desarrollando ballestas más duras, fuertes y "
"precisas. Al recibir misiones de caza y asesinato, se convirtieron en "
"maestros del movimiento sigiloso en entornos oscuros.\n"
"\n"
"Esa habilidad recién adquirida, junto con su precisión y el poder de sus "
"ballestas especiales, les ganó un respeto aún mayor de sus compañeros elfos, "
"y el temor de cualquiera que se les oponga —tanto en el subsuelo como en la "
"superficie."

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Witch, race=blackelf, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Witch.cfg:5
msgid "Dark Elf^Witch"
msgstr "Bruja Elfo Oscuro"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Elf Witch, race=blackelf, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/black-elves/Witch.cfg:21
msgid ""
"One of the most fundamental differences between the healers of both forest "
"and cave elves is their demeanour: while the former are more peaceful, the "
"latter have far less qualms about bringing pain upon other livings beings. "
"They do repudiate the idea of shedding blood, though; instead of piercing, "
"slashing or crushing their foes, Black Elf shamans prefer to blow them with "
"gusts of cold underground air. While being blown once or twice by their "
"winds may not cause much harm, even the toughest dwarf warrior will soon "
"find his own body numb from the cold; a prolonged exposure will cause "
"frostbite, which in turn will continue to worsen until the frozen limbs will "
"crack and fall off.\n"
"\n"
"This slow, painful way of killing their foes has earned those with a higher "
"kill count the dubbing of witches. Though their healing powers are "
"invaluable to Black-Elvish society, most black-elves are wary of getting too "
"involved with any of them."
msgstr ""
"Una de las diferencias más fundamentales entre los sanadores de los elfos "
"del bosque y los de cueva es su comportamiento: mientras los primeros son "
"más pacíficos, los segundos tienen muchos menos escrúpulos para infligir "
"dolor a otros seres vivos. Sin embargo, repudian la idea de derramar sangre; "
"en lugar de perforar, cortar o aplastar a sus enemigos, los chamanes elfos "
"negros prefieren derribarlos con ráfagas de aire frío subterráneo. Aunque "
"ser golpeado una o dos veces por sus vientos puede no causar mucho daño, "
"incluso el guerrero enano más resistente pronto encontrará su cuerpo "
"entumecido por el frío; una exposición prolongada causará congelación, que a "
"su vez seguirá empeorando hasta que las extremidades congeladas se agrieten "
"y caigan.\n"
"\n"
"Esta forma lenta y dolorosa de matar a sus enemigos ha hecho que aquellos "
"con un mayor conteo de muertes sean apodados brujas. Aunque sus poderes de "
"sanación son invaluables para la sociedad elfo negra, la mayoría de los "
"elfos negros son cautelosos de involucrarse demasiado con cualquiera de "
"ellos."

