#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_Under_the_Moon.cfg:75
msgid "Flame of Barbaria"
msgstr "Llama de Barbaria"

#. [unit_type], id=King Under the Sun, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_Under_the_Sun.cfg:4
msgid "King-Under-the-Sun"
msgstr "Rey-Bajo-el-Sol"

#. [unit_type], id=King Under the Sun, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_Under_the_Sun.cfg:26
msgid ""
"In our days, humankind is the most widely spread race in the world, having "
"large settlements in every known continent; and it is also the most diverse "
"of all. However, in the ancient days, humans did not know any of the lands "
"beyond the shores of their native Arajunna; and in those days, there was one "
"man who earned the respected of the many human tribes of that continent. "
"Blessed by the Goddess of Magic herself, he was the first of all mages, and "
"the first human to set out of his land to explore the realms beyond the "
"seas, thus igniting amongst his fellow humans the desire to explore the vast "
"green world.\n"
"\n"
"Though he held no official position in any country, his wisdom was "
"appreciated and admired by other humans like no other, and his advices were "
"always welcome and often followed. He was a true leader of humankind, one "
"who dedicated his entire life to helping his people establish themselves in "
"the world. Such man was the first King-Under-the-Sun; whoever wishes to "
"inherit his title must be one committed not to a country or a culture, but "
"to humankind itself."
msgstr ""
"En nuestros días, la humanidad es la raza más extendida en el mundo, con "
"grandes asentamientos en todos los continentes conocidos; y también es la "
"más diversa de todas. Sin embargo, en los días antiguos, los humanos no "
"conocían ninguna de las tierras más allá de las costas de su nativa "
"Arajunna; y en aquellos días, hubo un hombre que ganó el respeto de las "
"muchas tribus humanas de ese continente. Bendecido por la propia Diosa de la "
"Magia, fue el primero de todos los magos, y el primer humano en partir de su "
"tierra para explorar los reinos más allá de los mares, encendiendo así entre "
"sus semejantes el deseo de explorar el vasto mundo verde.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque no ocupó ningún cargo oficial en ningún país, su sabiduría fue "
"apreciada y admirada por otros humanos como ninguna otra, y sus consejos "
"siempre fueron bienvenidos y a menudo seguidos. Fue un verdadero líder de la "
"humanidad, uno que dedicó toda su vida a ayudar a su pueblo a establecerse "
"en el mundo. Tal hombre fue el primer Rey-Bajo-el-Sol; quien desee heredar "
"su título debe ser alguien comprometido no con un país o una cultura, sino "
"con la humanidad misma."

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_Under_the_Sun.cfg:41
msgid "Staff of An-Usrukhar"
msgstr "Bastón de An-Usrukhar"

#. [unit_type], id=King in the Abyss, race=troll
#. [option]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:4
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:400
msgid "King-in-the-Abyss"
msgstr "Rey-en-el-Abismo"

#. [unit_type], id=King in the Abyss, race=troll
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Trolls do not write on their own history, but they do remember it through "
"legends passed down the generations; and through these legends they still "
"remember a time when their people dwelled in the deepest halls of the world, "
"where the blood of volcanoes runs like rivers and oceans. It is not known "
"how the trolls came into existence in such inhospitable environment, though "
"the shamans claim that their kind is the offspring of Ymer, the Earthen "
"Father of their culture.\n"
"\n"
"The trolls did not live in the bowels of earth forever, though; under the "
"guidance of their leader Griknagh, they emerged into the surface world even "
"before the dwarves did. Nevertheless, they did not adapt to living beneath "
"the bright sun, and withdrew into underground tunnels closer to the surface. "
"And it was then that they met the Dvergar tribe of dwarves, then under the "
"rule of Moradin.\n"
"\n"
"As both trolls and dwarves were unaccustomed to dealing with different "
"cultures, their first meetings were very hostile, and resulted in "
"increasingly violent battles; until their respective leaders met and made "
"peace. More than that: Griknagh and Moradin became true friends, and dwarves "
"and trolls, after the initial distrust, started working together in the "
"building of their own underground world.\n"
"\n"
"However, it all changed when those two leaders obtained the Twin Hammers. No "
"legend tells of how they were created, but it is known that, while one "
"became Moradin's possession and was dubbed the Hammer of Buri; the other was "
"claimed by Griknagh and named the Hammer of Ymer. Each of those artefacts "
"held great power, and each was supposed to belong to one of the underground "
"rulers. Tragically, however, Moradin became too infatuated with the power of "
"Buri's Hammer, and began to covet Ymer's Hammer as well. During a time of "
"great turmoil, Moradin betrayed Griknagh, murdering him and seizing his "
"hammer.\n"
"\n"
"This betrayal sparked an anger amongst trolls which survive to this day - "
"even though most of them do not even remember the betrayal of their great "
"leader. The Hammer of Ymer remained in dwarvish hands for the following "
"ages; and, though it allowed itself to be used by worthy dwarves, it craves "
"the moment it will return to the hands of a troll worthy enough to be known, "
"like Griknagh in the past, the King-in-the-Abyss."
msgstr ""
"Los trolls no escriben su propia historia, pero la recuerdan a través de "
"leyendas transmitidas de generación en generación; y a través de estas "
"leyendas aún recuerdan un tiempo en que su pueblo habitaba en las salas más "
"profundas del mundo, donde la sangre de los volcanes corría como ríos y "
"océanos. No se sabe cómo los trolls llegaron a existir en un entorno tan "
"inhóspito, aunque los chamanes afirman que su especie es descendiente de "
"Ymer, el Padre Terrestre de su cultura.\n"
"\n"
"Los trolls no vivieron en las entrañas de la tierra para siempre, sin "
"embargo; bajo la guía de su líder Griknagh, emergieron al mundo de la "
"superficie incluso antes que los enanos. No obstante, no se adaptaron a "
"vivir bajo el brillante sol, y se retiraron a túneles subterráneos más "
"cercanos a la superficie. Y fue entonces cuando conocieron a la tribu "
"Dvergar de enanos, entonces bajo el dominio de Moradin.\n"
"\n"
"Como tanto trolls como enanos no estaban acostumbrados a tratar con culturas "
"diferentes, sus primeros encuentros fueron muy hostiles, y resultaron en "
"batallas cada vez más violentas; hasta que sus respectivos líderes se "
"encontraron e hicieron la paz. Más que eso: Griknagh y Moradin se "
"convirtieron en verdaderos amigos, y enanos y trolls, tras la desconfianza "
"inicial, comenzaron a trabajar juntos en la construcción de su propio mundo "
"subterráneo.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, todo cambió cuando esos dos líderes obtuvieron los Martillos "
"Gemelos. Ninguna leyenda cuenta cómo fueron creados, pero se sabe que, "
"mientras uno se convirtió en posesión de Moradin y fue apodado el Martillo "
"de Buri; el otro fue reclamado por Griknagh y nombrado el Martillo de Ymer. "
"Cada uno de esos artefactos tenía gran poder, y cada uno debía pertenecer a "
"uno de los gobernantes subterráneos. Trágicamente, sin embargo, Moradin se "
"encaprichó demasiado con el poder del Martillo de Buri, y comenzó a codiciar "
"también el Martillo de Ymer. Durante un tiempo de gran agitación, Moradin "
"traicionó a Griknagh, asesinándolo y apoderándose de su martillo.\n"
"\n"
"Esta traición encendió una ira entre los trolls que sobrevive hasta hoy —"
"aunque la mayoría de ellos ni siquiera recuerda la traición de su gran "
"líder. El Martillo de Ymer permaneció en manos enanas durante las edades "
"siguientes; y, aunque se permitió ser usado por enanos dignos, anhela el "
"momento en que regresará a las manos de un troll lo suficientemente digno de "
"ser conocido, como Griknagh en el pasado, el Rey-en-el-Abismo."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:43
msgid "Hammer of Ymer"
msgstr "Martillo de Ymer"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:56
msgid "flame mastery"
msgstr "maestría en llamas"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:68
msgid "Ginnungagap"
msgstr "Ginnungagap"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Abyss.cfg:82
msgid "Ymer's Thunderstrike"
msgstr "Golpe de Trueno de Ymer"

#. [unit_type], id=King in the Earth, race=dwarf
#. [option]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:5
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:387
msgid "King-in-the-Earth"
msgstr "Rey-en-la-Tierra"

#. [unit_type], id=King in the Earth, race=dwarf
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:26
msgid ""
"The oldest legends of dwarven-kind tell of a time when the dwarves did not "
"know the outside world; when the only sunlight they saw was that which "
"ocasionally shone into the underground through rifts in the mountain rock. "
"In those days, the dwarves were united into a single clan, the Dvergar, who "
"claimed to be the descendants of Buri, the Earthen Father.\n"
"\n"
"The Dvergar lived in the underground tunnels for many ages; the outside "
"world was seen as a mystical realm, and the creatures which sometimes came "
"from there were held as sacred. But the world of the Dvergar was "
"revolutionized in the days of Moradin. He was the one dwarf who defied "
"tradition and emerged into the outside world; followed by his sons "
"Motsoghnir and Durin, he wandered the new world, expanding the knowledge of "
"his people like none of his predecessors had done.\n"
"\n"
"But the contact with the people of the surface world was not a good "
"experience for the Dvergar, at first. Unused as they were to dealing with "
"different cultures and ways of thinking, they had dire disagreements with "
"other nations - the first and most serious of them with the elves. However, "
"Moradin managed to tame his people's belligerence and make peaceful ties "
"with elves, drakes and saurians.\n"
"\n"
"According to legend, it was around that time, after the end of the first war "
"with the elves, that Moradin emerged wielding the Hammer of Buri for the "
"first time. There is no consensus about how he forged it, only that the "
"oldest runes ever found are those that can still be seen carved on the "
"hammer's surface.\n"
"\n"
"For his power and for his people's mastery of the underground realm, Moradin "
"became known as the King-in-the-Earth, who ruled from beneath the mountains "
"from the bowels of Irdya."
msgstr ""
"Las leyendas más antiguas del pueblo enano hablan de un tiempo en que los "
"enanos no conocían el mundo exterior; cuando la única luz solar que veían "
"era la que ocasionalmente brillaba en el subsuelo a través de grietas en la "
"roca de la montaña. En aquellos días, los enanos estaban unidos en un solo "
"clan, los Dvergar, que afirmaban ser descendientes de Buri, el Padre "
"Terrestre.\n"
"\n"
"Los Dvergar vivieron en los túneles subterráneos durante muchas edades; el "
"mundo exterior era visto como un reino místico, y las criaturas que a veces "
"venían de allí eran consideradas sagradas. Pero el mundo de los Dvergar fue "
"revolucionado en los días de Moradin. Él fue el único enano que desafió la "
"tradición y emergió al mundo exterior; seguido por sus hijos Motsoghnir y "
"Durin, vagó por el nuevo mundo, expandiendo el conocimiento de su pueblo "
"como ninguno de sus predecesores había hecho.\n"
"\n"
"Pero el contacto con los pueblos del mundo de la superficie no fue una buena "
"experiencia para los Dvergar, al principio. No acostumbrados a tratar con "
"culturas y formas de pensar diferentes, tuvieron graves desacuerdos con "
"otras naciones —el primero y más serio de ellos con los elfos. Sin embargo, "
"Moradin logró domar la beligerancia de su pueblo y establecer lazos "
"pacíficos con elfos, dracos y saurios.\n"
"\n"
"Según la leyenda, fue alrededor de ese tiempo, después del fin de la primera "
"guerra con los elfos, que Moradin emergió empuñando el Martillo de Buri por "
"primera vez. No hay consenso sobre cómo lo forjó, solo que las runas más "
"antiguas jamás encontradas son las que aún pueden verse talladas en la "
"superficie del martillo.\n"
"\n"
"Por su poder y por la maestría de su pueblo en el reino subterráneo, Moradin "
"se conoció como el Rey-en-la-Tierra, quien gobernó desde debajo de las "
"montañas, desde las entrañas de Irdya."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:44
msgid "Hammer of Buri"
msgstr "Martillo de Buri"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:57
msgid "Runa Isaz"
msgstr "Runa Isaz"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:70
msgid "Runa Sowilo"
msgstr "Runa Sowilo"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:82
msgid "Runa Ansuz"
msgstr "Runa Ansuz"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/King_in_the_Earth.cfg:96
msgid "Buri's Thunderstrike"
msgstr "Golpe de Trueno de Buri"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Air, race=drake, gender=female
#. [option]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Air.cfg:4
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:374
msgid "Queen-in-the-Air"
msgstr "Reina-en-el-Aire"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Air, race=drake, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Air.cfg:20
msgid ""
"There have been many disagreements between dragons, drakes and saurians; but "
"one thing they do have in common is their admiration for their greatest "
"leader, the High Dragon of Fire Agniballi. In a society where might is "
"right, Agniballi was not only a feared ruler, but a hero who garnered the "
"respect even from the lizards who disliked him. As a testament of his power, "
"he singlehandedly built the monumental lava city of Aghayu, where he managed "
"to gather dozens of belligerent dragons and drakes in relative harmony.\n"
"\n"
"If the magnificence of Aghayu was not enough to convince a dragon of "
"Agniballi's power, meeting the High Dragon himself would change his mind. "
"For the crown which adorned the Dragons' King's head was a flame which shone "
"and burned like the sun itself, and to which even some dragons could not "
"stand for long.\n"
"\n"
"That flame, as drake legends tell, was a mystical fire, created by Agniballi "
"from his own body and soul; it had the power to protect the lizards even "
"after the High Dragon passed away, for that fire would not die out before "
"the Unmaking of the world. Such was the Brilliant Flame, the greatest power "
"of the nation which once ruled the skies of Irdya unchallenged. Whatever "
"dragon, drake or lizard that is deemed worthy enough to wield it shall be "
"known by his people as the King-in-the-Air."
msgstr ""
"Ha habido muchos desacuerdos entre dragones, dracos y saurios; pero una cosa "
"que tienen en común es su admiración por su mayor líder, el Alto Dragón de "
"Fuego Agniballi. En una sociedad donde la fuerza es el derecho, Agniballi no "
"fue solo un gobernante temido, sino un héroe que ganó el respeto incluso de "
"los lagartos que lo detestaban. Como testimonio de su poder, construyó él "
"solo la monumental ciudad de lava de Aghayu, donde logró reunir a docenas de "
"dragones y dracos beligerantes en una armonía relativa.\n"
"\n"
"Si la magnificencia de Aghayu no era suficiente para convencer a un dragón "
"del poder de Agniballi, encontrarse con el propio Alto Dragón cambiaría su "
"opinión. Pues la corona que adornaba la cabeza del Rey de los Dragones era "
"una llama que brillaba y ardía como el sol mismo, y a la que incluso algunos "
"dragones no podían resistir por mucho tiempo.\n"
"\n"
"Esa llama, como cuentan las leyendas draco, era un fuego místico, creado por "
"Agniballi de su propio cuerpo y alma; tenía el poder de proteger a los "
"lagartos incluso después de que el Alto Dragón falleciera, pues ese fuego no "
"se apagaría antes de la Deshacedora del mundo. Tal era la Llama Brillante, "
"el mayor poder de la nación que una vez gobernó los cielos de Irdya sin "
"desafío. Cualquier dragón, draco o lagarto que sea considerado lo "
"suficientemente digno de empuñarla será conocido por su pueblo como el Rey-"
"en-el-Aire."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Air.cfg:47
msgid "Great Claw"
msgstr "Gran Garra"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Air.cfg:56
msgid "Fire Storm"
msgstr "Tormenta de Fuego"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Air.cfg:68
msgid "Volcanic Explosion"
msgstr "Explosión Volcánica"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Ocean, race=merman, gender=female
#. [option]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Ocean.cfg:4
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:413
msgid "Queen-in-the-Ocean"
msgstr "Reina-en-el-Océano"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Ocean, race=merman, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Ocean.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Wielding both the Trident of the Seas and the mysterious powers of the ocean "
"nymphs, the legendary Queen-in-the-Ocean is the absolute master of Irdya's "
"aquatic environment. Her control over all water found in nature allows her "
"not only to control the weather and invoke lightning storms but, also, she "
"can reshape entire landscapes and alter coastlines, push the ocean waves "
"deep into a land mass and claim it for the sea kingdom. If you ever earn the "
"wrath of the Queen-in-the-Ocean, know that even the highest mountain top may "
"not protect you."
msgstr ""
"Empuñando tanto el Tridente de los Mares como los misteriosos poderes de las "
"ninfas oceánicas, la legendaria Reina-en-el-Océano es la maestra absoluta "
"del entorno acuático de Irdya. Su control sobre toda el agua presente en la "
"naturaleza le permite no solo dominar el clima e invocar tormentas de "
"relámpagos, sino también remodelar paisajes enteros y alterar líneas "
"costeras, empujar las olas del océano hacia el interior de una masa "
"terrestre y reclamarla para el reino marino. Si alguna vez provocas la ira "
"de la Reina-en-el-Océano, ten en cuenta que ni siquiera la cima de la "
"montaña más alta podrá protegerte."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Ocean.cfg:40
msgid "Trident of the Seas"
msgstr "Tridente de los Mares"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Ocean.cfg:64
msgid "Diluvian Rain"
msgstr "Lluvia Diluviana"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Ocean.cfg:91
msgid "Lightning Chain"
msgstr "Cadena de Relámpagos"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Woods, race=elf, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Woods.cfg:4
msgid "Queen-in-the-Woods"
msgstr "Reina-en-el-Bosque"

#. [unit_type], id=Queen in the Woods, race=elf, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Woods.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some elves have a special connection to their faerie side, which allows them "
"to harness powers which are inaccessible to any other race; and, in every "
"generation, there is an elf which an even greater mastery of the faerie "
"plane - the King-in-the-Wood. However, even these have not reached the full "
"potential of a descendant of Tithanya, the First of the Faeries. Such elves "
"only appear once in an entire era, and they have such a strong affinity with "
"the faerie plane that they become almost like reincarnations of Tithanya "
"herself. It is not known exactly what gives an elf such connection to their "
"faerie nature, though in all of the many scrolls of the elves, only females "
"were recorded as having it. The Queen-in-the-Woods is the ultimate master of "
"the Forest World, the link which unites all races known as the Children of "
"the Forest, and the greatest guardian of the world's flora; as long as she "
"lives, the balance of nature will never be truly broken."
msgstr ""
"Algunos elfos tienen una conexión especial con su lado feérico, lo que les "
"permite aprovechar poderes inaccesibles para cualquier otra raza; y en cada "
"generación hay un elfo con un dominio aún mayor del plano feérico: el Rey-en-"
"el-Bosque. Sin embargo, incluso estos no han alcanzado el pleno potencial de "
"un descendiente de Tithanya, la Primera de las Hadas. Tales elfos solo "
"aparecen una vez en toda una era, y tienen una afinidad tan fuerte con el "
"plano feérico que se vuelven casi como reencarnaciones de la propia "
"Tithanya. No se sabe exactamente qué otorga a un elfo tal conexión con su "
"naturaleza feérica, aunque en todos los numerosos pergaminos de los elfos "
"solo se registraron mujeres con ella. La Reina-en-el-Bosque es la maestra "
"suprema del Mundo del Bosque, el vínculo que une a todas las razas conocidas "
"como los Hijos del Bosque, y la mayor guardiana de la flora del mundo; "
"mientras ella viva, el equilibrio de la naturaleza nunca será verdaderamente "
"roto."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Woods.cfg:36
msgid "Yngvi Sword"
msgstr "Espada Yngvi"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Woods.cfg:48
msgid "Vanadís' Embrace"
msgstr "Abrazo de Vanadís"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/irdya-kings/Queen_in_the_Woods.cfg:61
msgid "Brising Fire"
msgstr "Fuego Brising"

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Apprentice, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Apprentice.cfg:4
msgid "Crimson Apprentice"
msgstr "Aprendiz Carmesí"

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Apprentice, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Apprentice.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians owe much of their magical lore to the Windsong: not because "
"of the magic itself - which origins are mainly in the teachings of Myra, "
"Aldrik, the Celestials and the Book of the Dead - but because the "
"Maat'Karian education, as well as its methods of research and storage of "
"knowledge were all developed by the Windsong who left their order to live "
"alongside the other humans in the then newly-built city. In fact, those "
"Windsong, who dedicated themselves to producing, accumulating and teaching "
"new knowledge rather than to learning new spells, inspired the creation of a "
"whole school of magic; one which members are more scholars than mages, even "
"though they do learn the mastery of the fire cipher, the only Windsong spell "
"they were allowed to learn. The apprentices of the Crimson Arts not only are "
"the main responsibles for the maintenance and development of their "
"civilization's wisdom, but they're also amongst their nation's finest "
"defenders, thanks to the incinerating fire balls that they can shower on "
"whoever is foolish enough to attack the People of the Sun."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos deben gran parte de su conocimiento mágico a las Hijas del "
"Viento: no por la magia en sí —cuyos orígenes están principalmente en las "
"enseñanzas de Myra, Aldrik, los Celestiales y el Libro de los Muertos—, sino "
"porque la educación maat'kariana, así como sus métodos de investigación y "
"almacenamiento del conocimiento, fueron desarrollados por las Hijas del "
"Viento que abandonaron su orden para vivir junto a los demás humanos en la "
"entonces recién construida ciudad. De hecho, aquellas Hijas del Viento, que "
"se dedicaron a producir, acumular y enseñar nuevo conocimiento en lugar de "
"aprender nuevos hechizos, inspiraron la creación de toda una escuela de "
"magia; una cuyos miembros son más eruditos que magos, aunque sí aprenden el "
"dominio del cifrado de fuego, el único hechizo de las Hijas del Viento que "
"se les permitió aprender. Los aprendices de las Artes Carmesíes no solo son "
"los principales responsables del mantenimiento y desarrollo de la sabiduría "
"de su civilización, sino que también están entre los mejores defensores de "
"su nación, gracias a las bolas de fuego incineradoras que pueden lanzar "
"sobre cualquiera lo suficientemente necio como para atacar al Pueblo del Sol."

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Apprentice.cfg:102
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Mage.cfg:91
msgid "female^Crimson Mage"
msgstr "Maga Carmesí"

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Mage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Crimson Mage"
msgstr "Mago Carmesí"

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Mage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Mage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Many people mistakenly believe that for one to graduate as a mage on any "
"path, one must simply increase one's own magical power. In the Lucent Arts, "
"for example, one must prove oneself a pious and virtuous individual before "
"receiving the robes of a Cleric. Crimson Mages, by their turn, are men and "
"women who, in addition to having refined their own fire bursts into a lethal "
"rain of fire, have proved themselves knowledgeable in History, Geography, "
"Biology, Politics, Alchemy, Medicine and Astronomy. In a world and age where "
"not every nation devotes a lot of effort to learning the workings of their "
"planet, the Crimson Mages can easily be counted amongst the most "
"knowledgeable beings in all of Irdya; and many of Maat'Kare's revered Sages "
"have walked the Crimson Path before entering political life.\n"
"        \n"
"Albeit dedicated to studying, every Crimson Mage is always willing to march "
"into battle to defend their homeland. And their worth on the battlefield is "
"undeniable, as they employ their ample knowledge not only to blast the enemy "
"away with fire bursts, but also to heal their allies from any illness they "
"might feel while campaigning."
msgstr ""
"Muchas personas creen erróneamente que para graduarse como mago en cualquier "
"camino basta con aumentar el propio poder mágico. En las Artes Lucentes, por "
"ejemplo, uno debe probar ser un individuo piadoso y virtuoso antes de "
"recibir las túnicas de Clérigo. Los Magos Carmesíes, por su parte, son "
"hombres y mujeres que, además de haber refinado sus propias ráfagas de fuego "
"en una lluvia letal de fuego, han demostrado ser conocedores en Historia, "
"Geografía, Biología, Política, Alquimia, Medicina y Astronomía. En un mundo "
"y una era en que no todas las naciones dedican mucho esfuerzo a aprender el "
"funcionamiento de su planeta, los Magos Carmesíes pueden contarse fácilmente "
"entre los seres más sabios de toda Irdya; y muchos de los venerados Sabios "
"de Maat'Kare han recorrido el Camino Carmesí antes de entrar en la vida "
"política.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque dedicados al estudio, todo Mago Carmesí siempre está dispuesto a "
"marchar al combate para defender su patria. Y su valía en el campo de "
"batalla es innegable, ya que emplean su amplio conocimiento no solo para "
"alejar al enemigo con ráfagas de fuego, sino también para curar a sus "
"aliados de cualquier enfermedad que puedan sentir durante la campaña."

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Master, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Crimson Master"
msgstr "Maestro Carmesí"

#. [unit_type], id=Crimson Master, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Master.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Narmer Mewates, who was Maat'Kare's Great Seer during the War of Blood in "
"506 YF, famously said that what made the Maat'Karian civilization so "
"outstanding wasn't its roots, or its power, or even its wealth; but the vast "
"knowledge that it had gathered and, even more importantly, its awareness of "
"how important cherishing all that knowledge was. In such a learned society, "
"it comes as no surprise that Crimson Masters, the wise amongst the wise, are "
"highly respected even by the Sages. Furthermore, they are the absolute "
"masters of the fire cipher, against which no foe has ever stood for long. "
"Even darkness, which halts even the strongest Wersefet, is utterly powerless "
"before the Crimson Masters, whose fires both guide and warm the soldiers in "
"the dark nights of Netjer-Ta."
msgstr ""
"Narmer Mewates, quien fue el Gran Vidente de Maat'Kare durante la Guerra de "
"Sangre en 506 YF, famosamente dijo que lo que hacía tan destacada a la "
"civilización maat'kariana no eran sus raíces, ni su poder, ni siquiera su "
"riqueza; sino el vasto conocimiento que había acumulado y, aún más "
"importante, su conciencia de cuán importante era atesorar todo ese "
"conocimiento. En una sociedad tan erudita, no sorprende que los Maestros "
"Carmesíes, los sabios entre los sabios, sean altamente respetados incluso "
"por los Sabios. Además, son los maestros absolutos del cifrado de fuego, "
"contra el cual ningún enemigo ha resistido por mucho tiempo. Incluso la "
"oscuridad, que detiene incluso al más fuerte Wersefet, es completamente "
"impotente ante los Maestros Carmesíes, cuyos fuegos tanto guían como "
"calientan a los soldados en las oscuras noches de Netjer-Ta."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Master.cfg:39
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/true-elementals/Agni.cfg:109
msgid "eruption"
msgstr "erupción"

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Crimson_Master.cfg:164
msgid "female^Crimson Master"
msgstr "Maestra Carmesí"

#. [unit_type], id=Desert Bane, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Bane.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Bane"
msgstr "Azote del Desierto"

#. [unit_type], id=Desert Bane, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Desert Ghost, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Desert Shadow, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Bane.cfg:22
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Ghost.cfg:19
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Shadow.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Nothing is known about this unit: its garments, its weapons and its fighting "
"style are unrecognizable to the Maat'Karians. Still, two things are certain "
"about it: it's human, and it's a very dangerous foe."
msgstr ""
"No se sabe nada sobre esta unidad: sus vestimentas, sus armas y su estilo de "
"combate son irreconocibles para los maat'karianos. Aun así, dos cosas son "
"ciertas sobre ella: es humana y es un enemigo muy peligroso."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Bane.cfg:36
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Ghost.cfg:34
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Shadow.cfg:35
msgid "bolas"
msgstr "boleadoras"

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Bane.cfg:133
msgid "female^Desert Bane"
msgstr "Azote del Desierto"

#. [unit_type], id=Desert Ghost, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Ghost.cfg:5
msgid "Desert Ghost"
msgstr "Fantasma del Desierto"

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Ghost.cfg:142
msgid "female^Desert Ghost"
msgstr "Fantasma del Desierto"

#. [unit_type], id=Desert Shadow, race=human
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Shadow"
msgstr "Sombra del Desierto"

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Desert_Shadow.cfg:114
msgid "female^Desert Shadow"
msgstr "Sombra del Desierto"

#. [unit_type], id=Aaneb, race=maatkarian, gender=male
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Aaneb.cfg:5
msgid "A'aneb"
msgstr "A'aneb"

#. [unit_type], id=Aaneb, race=maatkarian, gender=male
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Aaneb.cfg:30
msgid ""
"A'anebs - or 'great lord' - are extremely seasoned commanders, and have led "
"their men to victory on many occasions; they know the best way to fight on "
"each kind of terrain and the best tactical formations, both offensie and "
"defensive; and they know how to grasp victory even when the situation seems "
"hopeless. In addition to their brilliant mind for strategies, they're "
"formidable warriors themselves; their mere presence can boost their "
"soldiers' morale. So formidable and respected they are, that they're often "
"given the title of Lords and entrusted with the government of entire towns."
msgstr ""
"Los A'aneb —o «gran señor»— son comandantes extremadamente experimentados y "
"han llevado a sus hombres a la victoria en muchas ocasiones; conocen la "
"mejor forma de luchar en cada tipo de terreno y las mejores formaciones "
"tácticas, tanto ofensivas como defensivas; y saben cómo arrebatar la "
"victoria incluso cuando la situación parece desesperada. Además de su "
"brillante mente para las estrategias, ellos mismos son guerreros "
"formidables; su mera presencia puede elevar la moral de sus soldados. Tan "
"formidables y respetados son que a menudo reciben el título de Señores y se "
"les confía el gobierno de ciudades enteras."

#. [unit_type], id=Chariot Archer, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Chariot Archer"
msgstr "Arquera de Carro"

#. [unit_type], id=Chariot Archer, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The Hannuks, one of the two peoples from whom the Maat'Karians descend, were "
"famed for being excellent archers and outstanding horsemen. Indeed, both "
"archery and horsemanship were such important skills in their culture that "
"those who managed to excel at both were considered heroes. It is thus ironic "
"that their heirs have so little regard for both archery and horsemanship, "
"prefering to use the horses for transportation and the bows for hunting - "
"archers were taken out of the army for being too vulnerable to enemy attacks "
"with their light armour. Nevertheless, still early in Maat'Kare's History a "
"new military unit was created by women who, not wanting to simply sit "
"comfortably at home but unable to don the standard Maat'Karian armour, "
"ressurrected the old Hannuk War Chariot, but adapting it to their needs: in "
"the end, they had developed a lighter and less resistant, but also swifter "
"and more agile vehicle, and one which didn't lose speed on sandy terrain. "
"Those women also learned archery, becoming quite proficient at it; thus they "
"would, like the War Charioteers of yore, shoot deadly arrows from inside the "
"chariot, which was to be driven by trained charioteers. This unit quickly "
"became quite popular for their accurate ranged attacks, high defense against "
"most physical damage, great speed and capacity of moving through enemy lines "
"thanks to its sheer weight; their only downsides, in fact, are their "
"uselessness on nearly any terrain other than plains and sands, and the high "
"costs of building and maintaining them."
msgstr ""
"Los Hannuks, uno de los dos pueblos de los que descienden los maat'karianos, "
"eran famosos por ser excelentes arqueros y destacados jinetes. En efecto, "
"tanto la arquería como la equitación eran habilidades tan importantes en su "
"cultura que quienes lograban destacar en ambas eran considerados héroes. Por "
"eso es irónico que sus herederos tengan tan poco aprecio por ambas, "
"prefiriendo usar los caballos para transporte y los arcos para cazar —los "
"arqueros fueron retirados del ejército por ser demasiado vulnerables a "
"ataques enemigos con su armadura ligera. Sin embargo, aún temprano en la "
"historia de Maat'Kare, un nuevo grupo militar fue creado por mujeres que, no "
"queriendo simplemente quedarse cómodas en casa pero incapaces de usar la "
"armadura maat'kariana estándar, resucitaron el antiguo Carro de Guerra "
"Hannuk, pero adaptándolo a sus necesidades: al final, desarrollaron un "
"vehículo más ligero y menos resistente, pero también más rápido y ágil, y "
"que no perdía velocidad en terreno arenoso. Esas mujeres también aprendieron "
"arquería, volviéndose bastante competentes en ella; así, al igual que los "
"antiguos Carros de Guerra, disparaban flechas letales desde dentro del "
"carro, que era conducido por cocheros entrenados. Esta unidad se volvió "
"rápidamente muy popular por sus precisos ataques a distancia, alta defensa "
"contra la mayoría del daño físico, gran velocidad y capacidad de atravesar "
"líneas enemigas gracias a su puro peso; sus únicos inconvenientes, de hecho, "
"son su inutilidad en casi cualquier terreno que no sean llanuras y arenas, y "
"los altos costos de construirlos y mantenerlos."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:57
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:69
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:57
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Batal.cfg:31
msgid "composite bow"
msgstr "arco compuesto"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:66
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:81
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:66
msgid "fire arrows"
msgstr "flechas de fuego"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Elder Sage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Elder_Sage.cfg:7
msgid "Elder Sage"
msgstr "Sabio Anciano"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Elder Sage, race=maatkarian
#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Elder_Sage.cfg:21
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sage.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The Sages of Maat'Kare are the eldest and wisest amongst the Maat'Karian "
"citizens. As the representatives of the commoners, they don't have magic or "
"military skills, but their vast life experience and great skill in politics "
"make them competent administrators of the Maat'Karian civilization, and for "
"this they are highly respected."
msgstr ""
"Los Sabios de Maat'Kare son los más ancianos y sabios entre los ciudadanos "
"maat'karianos. Como representantes de la gente común, no tienen habilidades "
"mágicas ni militares, pero su vasta experiencia de vida y gran habilidad en "
"política los convierten en competentes administradores de la civilización "
"maat'kariana, y por eso son altamente respetados."

#. [unit_type], id=Electrum Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Electrum_Slinger.cfg:5
msgid "Maat'Karian Electrum Slinger"
msgstr "Hondero de Electrum Maat'kariano"

#. [unit_type], id=Electrum Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Electrum_Slinger.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Though Slingers are not an official military unit, some commanders do "
"recruit them, to compensate the Sefet's lack of ranged attacks, and because "
"they're far less expensive than Chariot Archers. These Slingers thus have a "
"chance to further hone their skills and improve their physical prowess with "
"military training; and the best ones are given better equipment and electrum "
"balls, which are much harder than stone, as ammunition. Albeit still "
"vulnerable due to their lack of armour, their speed and the deadliness and "
"accuracy of their slingshots are undoubtedly valuable assets for the "
"Maat'Karian Army."
msgstr ""
"Aunque los honderos no son una unidad militar oficial, algunos comandantes "
"los reclutan para compensar la falta de ataques a distancia de los Sefet y "
"porque son mucho menos costosos que las Arqueras de Carro. Estos honderos "
"tienen así la oportunidad de perfeccionar aún más sus habilidades y mejorar "
"su destreza física con entrenamiento militar; y a los mejores se les da "
"mejor equipo y bolas de electrum, mucho más duras que la piedra, como "
"munición. Aunque siguen siendo vulnerables por la falta de armadura, su "
"velocidad y la letalidad y precisión de sus hondas son sin duda activos "
"valiosos para el Ejército Maat'kariano."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Electrum_Slinger.cfg:41
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Slinger.cfg:40
msgid "sling"
msgstr "honda"

#. [unit_type], id=Imeyer, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Imeyer.cfg:4
msgid "Imey'er"
msgstr "Imey'er"

#. [unit_type], id=Imeyer, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Imeyer.cfg:25
msgid ""
"After leading his soldiers for many battles, a Shakafa will have learned the "
"skills that the military academy couldn't teach: to take quick decisions as "
"his life and that of his men are on the verge of death, to gain the trust of "
"his soldiers, to decide the best moves according to terrain, weather and "
"time conditions... Because not all Shakafa live long enough to learn these "
"lessons, those who do are highly valued, and are know as Imey'er, or "
"captains - for only now has he truly earned the right to be known as such."
msgstr ""
"Tras liderar a sus soldados en muchas batallas, un Shakafa habrá aprendido "
"las habilidades que la academia militar no podía enseñar: tomar decisiones "
"rápidas cuando su vida y la de sus hombres están al borde de la muerte, "
"ganarse la confianza de sus soldados, decidir los mejores movimientos según "
"el terreno, el clima y las condiciones del momento… Como no todos los "
"Shakafa viven lo suficiente para aprender estas lecciones, aquellos que lo "
"hacen son altamente valorados y se les conoce como Imey'er, o capitanes —"
"pues solo ahora ha ganado verdaderamente el derecho a ser llamado así."

#. [unit_type], id=Khopesh, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:4
msgid "Khopesh"
msgstr "Khopesh"

#. [unit_type], id=Khopesh, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Sefet who stand out of his colleagues will be given an even stronger "
"armour, and a slightly longer sword - a khopesh - which increases their "
"attacking power. Although the weight of their new armour decreases their "
"speed, it also enables them to withstand considerably more rounds of "
"fighting than most infantry soldiers from other armies. They're still "
"vulnerable to ranged attacks, but they've also learned to make better use of "
"their equipment."
msgstr ""
"Al Sefet que destaca entre sus compañeros se le da una armadura aún más "
"fuerte y una espada ligeramente más larga —un khopesh— que aumenta su poder "
"de ataque. Aunque el peso de su nueva armadura disminuye su velocidad, "
"también les permite resistir considerablemente más rondas de combate que la "
"mayoría de los soldados de infantería de otros ejércitos. Siguen siendo "
"vulnerables a ataques a distancia, pero también han aprendido a hacer mejor "
"uso de su equipo."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:36
msgid "khopesh"
msgstr "khopesh"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:48
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:43
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:51
msgid "stab"
msgstr "apuñalada"

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Adept, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Mages.cfg:147
msgid "Umbra Adept"
msgstr "Adepto Umbra"

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Sorcerer, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Mages.cfg:162
msgid "Umbra Sorcerer"
msgstr "Hechicero Umbra"

#. [unit_type], id=Necromancer, race=maatkarian
#. [unit_type], id=Umbra Master, race=undead
#. [unit_type], id=Umbra Master Lich, race=undead
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Mages.cfg:177
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:5
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/undead/Umbra_Master_Lich.cfg:5
msgid "Umbra Master"
msgstr "Maestro Umbra"

#. [unit_type], id=Maryannu, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:5
msgid "Maryannu"
msgstr "Maryannu"

#. [unit_type], id=Maryannu, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:21
msgid ""
"It has often been pointed out by commanders and even common citizens that "
"the Ten'Thors, with all their might, seldom survive more than seven battles. "
"This is probably due to their defencelessness on all kinds of terrain, which "
"makes them an easy target; and specially to the overconfidence that has "
"become a signature trait of both archer and charioteer. Nevertheless, those "
"Tenthors who do manage to survive many battles and hone their skills even "
"further are amongst Maat'Kare's enemies' most dreaded banes. They thundr "
"across the plains and the desert like a juggernaut, striking down any foe "
"that manages to avoid being cruelly trampled by the vehicle and the horses, "
"and leading infantrymen and Chariot Archers alike as if they were the actual "
"commanders of their respective armies. Imposing and powerful, these superb "
"charioteers and archers have earned the well-deserved name of Maryannu, or "
"'valiant warriors'."
msgstr ""
"A menudo se ha señalado por comandantes e incluso ciudadanos comunes que los "
"Ten'Thor, con toda su fuerza, rara vez sobreviven más de siete batallas. "
"Esto probablemente se debe a su indefensión en todo tipo de terreno, lo que "
"los convierte en un blanco fácil; y especialmente a la exceso de confianza "
"que se ha convertido en un rasgo distintivo tanto del arquero como del "
"auriga. Sin embargo, aquellos Ten'Thor que logran sobrevivir muchas batallas "
"y perfeccionar aún más sus habilidades están entre los azotes más temidos "
"por los enemigos de Maat'Kare. Recorren las llanuras y el desierto como un "
"ariete, derribando a cualquier enemigo que logre evitar ser cruelmente "
"aplastado por el vehículo y los caballos, y liderando a infantes y Arqueras "
"de Carro por igual como si fueran los verdaderos comandantes de sus "
"respectivos ejércitos. Imponentes y poderosos, estos superiores aurigas y "
"arqueros han ganado con justicia el nombre de Maryannu, o «guerreros "
"valientes»."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:58
msgid "fearless charge"
msgstr "carga sin miedo"

#. [unit_type], id=Medjay, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:5
msgid "Medjay"
msgstr "Medjay"

#. [unit_type], id=Medjay, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Many Sentinels die every year in frontier clashes against vampires, "
"minotaurs and orcs; nevertheless, it's exactly this environment of danger "
"and of constant fighting that shapes those who are renowned all over Netjer-"
"Ta as the most fearsome defenders any army can hope to meet. Clad in shining "
"electrum armour and wielding towering shields adorned with the Winged "
"Protectress of Maat'Kare, these warriors are called the Medjay - which means "
"'dead end' in the Maat'Karian language. Indeed, if an enemy comes across a "
"Medjay, his best option is to go another way."
msgstr ""
"Muchos Centinelas mueren cada año en choques fronterizos contra vampiros, "
"minotauros y orcos; sin embargo, es precisamente este entorno de peligro y "
"combate constante el que moldea a aquellos que son renombrados en todo "
"Netjer-Ta como los defensores más temibles que cualquier ejército puede "
"esperar encontrar. Vestidos con brillante armadura de electrum y empuñando "
"escudos imponentes adornados con la Protectora Alada de Maat'Kare, estos "
"guerreros son llamados Medjay —que significa «callejón sin salida» en la "
"lengua maat'kariana. En efecto, si un enemigo se topa con un Medjay, su "
"mejor opción es tomar otro camino."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:38
msgid "Spear"
msgstr "Lanza"

#. [unit_type], id=Migdol Guard, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Migdol_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Migdol Guard"
msgstr "Guardia Migdol"

#. [unit_type], id=Migdol Guard, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Migdol_Guard.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Those amongst the Sentinels who show greater prowess with the spear are "
"given better armour and sent to the Migdols, small fortresses that protect "
"the most vulnerable points of the Maat'Karian frontier."
msgstr ""
"A aquellos Centinelas que destacan más con la lanza se les da mejor armadura "
"y se les envía a los Migdols, pequeñas fortalezas que protegen los puntos "
"más vulnerables de la frontera maat'kariana."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sage.cfg:7
msgid "Sage"
msgstr "Sabio"

#. [unit_type], id=Sefet, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:5
msgid "Sefet"
msgstr "Sefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Sefet, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Since its very founding, Maat'Kare has always been forced to deal with a "
"dilemma: at the same it had to control its population's size, it was "
"constantly involved in wars against vampires, orcs, minotaurs and gnolls. "
"Ravyan Aracyne, one of the city's Founders, was the first to worry about the "
"number of losses that the Maat'Karians could have in each battle; to "
"diminish their chances of dying or being severely maimed, the Maat'Karian "
"soldiers are given a very resistant armour made of electrum (an alloy of "
"gold and silver), which crafting the humans learned from the Aigathol "
"dwarves. This armour protects them well from all kinds of phsical damage, "
"but are very heavy, and so the soldiers are trained to be extremely "
"muscular. The Maat'Karian soldiers' great physical strength, allied with the "
"weight and sharpness of their sefet - or swords -, also renders their blows "
"extremely devastating, especially for such a basic military unit; and their "
"stamina enables them to move well on most terrain types. The downside, "
"however, is that the cost of forging such equipment and training such a "
"soldier is high. Another downside of the Sefet is that they're vulnerable to "
"ranged attacks."
msgstr ""
"Desde su misma fundación, Maat'Kare siempre se ha visto obligada a lidiar "
"con un dilema: al mismo tiempo que debía controlar el tamaño de su "
"población, estaba constantemente involucrada en guerras contra vampiros, "
"orcos, minotauros y gnolls. Ravyan Aracyne, uno de los Fundadores de la "
"ciudad, fue el primero en preocuparse por la cantidad de pérdidas que los "
"maat'karianos podían sufrir en cada batalla; para disminuir sus "
"posibilidades de morir o quedar gravemente mutilados, a los soldados "
"maat'karianos se les da una armadura muy resistente hecha de electrum (una "
"aleación de oro y plata), cuya forja los humanos aprendieron de los enanos "
"Aigathol. Esta armadura los protege bien de todo tipo de daño físico, pero "
"es muy pesada, y por eso los soldados son entrenados para ser extremadamente "
"musculosos. La gran fuerza física de los soldados maat'karianos, aliada al "
"peso y filo de su sefet —o espadas—, también hace que sus golpes sean "
"extremadamente devastadores, especialmente para una unidad militar tan "
"básica; y su resistencia les permite moverse bien en la mayoría de los tipos "
"de terreno. El inconveniente, sin embargo, es que el costo de forjar tal "
"equipo y entrenar a tal soldado es alto. Otro inconveniente de los Sefet es "
"que son vulnerables a ataques a distancia."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:31
msgid "sefet"
msgstr "sefet"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sentinel, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Sentinel"
msgstr "Centinela"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sentinel, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sentinel.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Maat'Karian soldiers are famed for their defensive power: wearing heavy "
"armour that covers nearly the entirety of their bodies, they are highly "
"resistant to most kinds of attack. Nevertheless, this poses two problems for "
"their military: firstly, they can't afford producing electrum armour for "
"many soldiers; and second, even if they could, not all would have the "
"necessary height, strength and stamina to efficiently fight while donning "
"them. It was Erakyn, a famous general of Maat'Kare's third generation, who "
"solved both problems by creating a new unit which donnned a new type of "
"armour, one that didn't protect the soldier as the one donned by the Sefet "
"did; but which was lighter and less expensive, and made of electrum as well. "
"This new unit was given long spears, which was a cheaper and more accessible "
"weapon to people. These units were seldom sent to fight on pitched battles, "
"but they became an important part of Maat'Kare's defence, for they are "
"always employed as guards and patrollers in towns, villages and frontier "
"outposts."
msgstr ""
"Los soldados maat'karianos son famosos por su poder defensivo: vistiendo "
"pesada armadura que cubre casi todo su cuerpo, son altamente resistentes a "
"la mayoría de los tipos de ataque. Sin embargo, esto plantea dos problemas "
"para su ejército: primero, no pueden permitirse producir armadura de "
"electrum para muchos soldados; y segundo, incluso si pudieran, no todos "
"tendrían la altura, fuerza y resistencia necesarias para luchar "
"eficientemente mientras la llevan. Fue Erakyn, un famoso general de la "
"tercera generación de Maat'Kare, quien resolvió ambos problemas creando una "
"nueva unidad que vestía un nuevo tipo de armadura, una que no protegía al "
"soldado como la de los Sefet; pero que era más ligera y menos costosa, y "
"también hecha de electrum. A esta nueva unidad se le dieron lanzas largas, "
"un arma más barata y accesible para la gente. Estas unidades rara vez eran "
"enviadas a luchar en batallas campales, pero se convirtieron en una parte "
"importante de la defensa de Maat'Kare, pues siempre se emplean como guardias "
"y patrulleros en ciudades, aldeas y puestos fronterizos."

#. [unit_type], id=Shakafa, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Shakafa.cfg:4
msgid "Shakafa"
msgstr "Shakafa"

#. [unit_type], id=Shakafa, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Shakafa.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians aren't an expansionistic people by tradition, but it "
"doesn't mean that they simply sit behind their walls waiting for their foes "
"to attack. After the securing of the Land's End peninsula, they set out to "
"conquer nearby lands that were controlled by minotaurs and vampires, and "
"times later, they started attacking faraway vampire and orcish fortresses. "
"These conquest campaigns required soldiers with good leadership skills, and "
"so a new battle school was formed with the goal of training commanders. Not "
"everyone can join it, though, due to the high cost of their equipment: an "
"iron mace and a massive electrum armour, far more resistant than that of a "
"Sefet - after all, a commander must be well protected. This also means that "
"the commander-in-training must develop even stronger muscles than a normal "
"soldier; besides, he's expected to be the first to do whatever he asks of "
"his men, and so he must be courageous.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, if the commander-in-training leaves the military academy "
"successfully, he receives the title of Shakafa, which means 'he who leads "
"the conquests'. However, the most important knowledge he must have to be a "
"true commander can only be found in battle."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos no son un pueblo expansionista por tradición, pero eso no "
"significa que simplemente se queden detrás de sus murallas esperando a que "
"sus enemigos ataquen. Tras asegurar la península de Fin de la Tierra, "
"partieron a conquistar tierras cercanas controladas por minotauros y "
"vampiros, y tiempo después comenzaron a atacar fortalezas lejanas de "
"vampiros y orcos. Estas campañas de conquista requerían soldados con buenas "
"habilidades de liderazgo, y así se formó una nueva escuela de batalla con el "
"objetivo de entrenar comandantes. No todos pueden unirse a ella, sin "
"embargo, debido al alto costo de su equipo: una maza de hierro y una "
"armadura masiva de electrum, mucho más resistente que la de un Sefet —"
"después de todo, un comandante debe estar bien protegido. Esto también "
"significa que el comandante en entrenamiento debe desarrollar músculos aún "
"más fuertes que un soldado normal; además, se espera que sea el primero en "
"hacer lo que pide a sus hombres, y por lo tanto debe ser valiente.\n"
"\n"
"Finalmente, si el comandante en entrenamiento abandona con éxito la academia "
"militar, recibe el título de Shakafa, que significa «el que lidera las "
"conquistas». Sin embargo, el conocimiento más importante que debe tener para "
"ser un verdadero comandante solo se encuentra en la batalla."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Slinger.cfg:4
msgid "Maat'Karian Slinger"
msgstr "Hondero Maat'kariano"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Slinger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Joining the military is the dream of many Maat'Karian youths; unfortunately, "
"however, not all of them have the build to become a Sefet or a Sentinel, or "
"the skill to train as an archer. Those amongst these youths who live in the "
"rural areas were thus forced to remain as farmers; and, while hunting or "
"scaring off wild animals, they developed a great skill with the sling. The "
"usefulness of such ability was first noticed when, during a frontier "
"skirmish against a rogue Warg pack, a group of slingers came to the aid of "
"the soldiers, unbalancing the fight in their favour due to the Wargs' "
"vulnerability to ranged attacks. Since that fight, slingers have risen in "
"prominence, and now there are even some commanders who use them as regular "
"soldiers. Nevertheless, because they are quite vulnerable to physical "
"attacks - after all, they don't wear any armour - they haven't been made an "
"official military unit yet."
msgstr ""
"Unirse al ejército es el sueño de muchos jóvenes maat'karianos; "
"desafortunadamente, sin embargo, no todos tienen la constitución para "
"convertirse en Sefet o Centinela, ni la habilidad para entrenar como "
"arquero. Aquellos entre estos jóvenes que viven en áreas rurales se vieron "
"obligados a permanecer como agricultores; y, mientras cazaban o ahuyentaban "
"animales salvajes, desarrollaron una gran habilidad con la honda. La "
"utilidad de tal habilidad se notó por primera vez cuando, durante una "
"escaramuza fronteriza contra una manada de huargos renegados, un grupo de "
"honderos acudió en ayuda de los soldados, desequilibrando la pelea a su "
"favor debido a la vulnerabilidad de los huargos a ataques a distancia. Desde "
"esa pelea, los honderos han ganado prominencia, y ahora incluso hay algunos "
"comandantes que los usan como soldados regulares. Sin embargo, porque son "
"bastante vulnerables a ataques físicos —después de todo, no llevan armadura— "
"aún no han sido convertidos en una unidad militar oficial."

#. [unit_type], id=Tenthor, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:5
msgid "Ten'Thor"
msgstr "Ten'Thor"

#. [unit_type], id=Tenthor, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Not every commander likes employing Chariot Archers in their batallions, due "
"to their expensiveness and low terrain versatility. Those who do, however, "
"use their own gold to buy electrum and iron plates with which to reinforce "
"the vehicles of the best Chariot Archers, and also horseshoes to make the "
"horses' kicks deadlier. Curiously, though few are the commanders who recruit "
"that unit, those who do often relies heavily on them, forming entire "
"batallions composed exclusively of seasoned Chariot Archers. Because of "
"that, they've been called Ten'Thor, which literally means 'chariot force', "
"and they're widely known for turning the tide of countless battles all by "
"themselves."
msgstr ""
"No todos los comandantes gustan de emplear Arqueras de Carro en sus "
"batallones, debido a su alto costo y baja versatilidad en terrenos. Aquellos "
"que sí lo hacen, sin embargo, usan su propio oro para comprar placas de "
"electrum y hierro con las que reforzar los vehículos de las mejores Arqueras "
"de Carro, y también herraduras para hacer más letales las patadas de los "
"caballos. Curiosamente, aunque pocos son los comandantes que reclutan esa "
"unidad, aquellos que lo hacen a menudo dependen mucho de ellas, formando "
"batallones enteros compuestos exclusivamente de Arqueras de Carro "
"experimentadas. Por eso se les ha llamado Ten'Thor, que literalmente "
"significa «fuerza de carro», y son ampliamente conocidos por cambiar el "
"rumbo de innumerables batallas por sí solos."

#. [unit_type], id=Wersefet, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:4
msgid "Wersefet"
msgstr "Wersefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Wersefet, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Not many soldiers advance past the rank of a Khopesh, and for a simple "
"reason: few are the men who have the strength and the stamina to don the "
"armour and wield the sword reserved for the elite of the Maat'Karian "
"infantry. This sword, known as wersefet - literally 'great blade' is almost "
"as massive as an Orcish chiefain's sword, but far sharper and far more "
"resistant. A single line of Wersefet soldiers, with their golden armour, "
"towering shields and lethal blades gleaming in the sunlight, would be enough "
"to repel even a massive attack by seasoned warriors, but their mere sight is "
"often enough to make most foes flee in terror."
msgstr ""
"No muchos soldados avanzan más allá del rango de Khopesh, y por una razón "
"simple: pocos son los hombres que tienen la fuerza y la resistencia para "
"vestir la armadura y empuñar la espada reservada para la élite de la "
"infantería maat'kariana. Esta espada, conocida como wersefet —literalmente "
"«gran hoja»— es casi tan masiva como la espada de un jefe orco, pero mucho "
"más afilada y mucho más resistente. Una sola línea de soldados Wersefet, con "
"su armadura dorada, escudos imponentes y hojas letales brillando bajo el "
"sol, sería suficiente para repeler incluso un ataque masivo de guerreros "
"experimentados, pero su mera visión a menudo basta para hacer que la mayoría "
"de los enemigos huya aterrorizada."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:39
msgid "wersefet"
msgstr "wersefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Novice Mage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Novice Mage"
msgstr "Mago Novato"

#. [unit_type], id=Novice Mage, race=maatkarian
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Novice Mages are youths who have just been admitted into the Academy of "
"Maat'Kare. Though currently little more than children who can channel their "
"power into mildly burning missiles, they have the potential to become great "
"mages in the future."
msgstr ""
"Los Magos Novatos son jóvenes que acaban de ser admitidos en la Academia de "
"Maat'Kare. Aunque actualmente no son más que niños capaces de canalizar su "
"poder en misiles que queman levemente, tienen el potencial de convertirse en "
"grandes magos en el futuro."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:46
msgid "missile"
msgstr "proyectil"

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:94
msgid "female^Novice Mage"
msgstr "Maga Novata"

#. [unit_type], id=Umbra Master, race=undead
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:24
msgid ""
"In the History of the Maat'Karians, many were the mages renowned for walking "
"a single path of magic: Kun'lun the White, Gebet of the Shadow Forest, the "
"Fire Empress Sadjet... But no mage dared delve too deeply into the Umbra "
"Arts. For a long time, such fact was used by professors as a evidence of how "
"dangerous that path could be, for no master to dare walk too far into it. "
"However, during the Years of the Double Suns some Umbra enthusiasts "
"denounced this fear as pure prejudice, based on an ancient bias against the "
"Lich-Lords of Skiron. Arguing that the Umbra Arts had never been properly "
"understood due to this 'fear', those Umbra mages dedicated themselves to "
"this specific path.\n"
"\n"
"Paramount among these mages is arguably Wesir Amarnat. Despite his well-"
"known penchant for ostentation, for many years he refused to show off his "
"Umbra powers. However, during a war in which New Maat'Kare found itself "
"besieged by an orcish army which outnumbered the city's entire population by "
"3 to 1; he presented his countrymen the fruits of his decades-long studies "
"in a display of power which caused friend and foe alike to stand in awe. A "
"chronicler who witnessed the event wrote that 'it was as if the balance of "
"the dimensions had been broken, bringing the Land of the Dead itself upon "
"the Living World'. After that battle, Wesir became known as the 'God of "
"Death'.\n"
"\n"
"As an Umbra Master and a distinguished member of New Maat'Kare's Chamber of "
"Sages, he is an example of how one could retain sanity and lawfulness while "
"immerging oneself in dark magic."
msgstr ""
"En la historia de los maat'karianos, muchos fueron los magos renombrados por "
"recorrer un solo camino de magia: Kun'lun la Blanca, Gebet del Bosque de las "
"Sombras, la Emperatriz de Fuego Sadjet… Pero ningún mago se atrevió a "
"adentrarse demasiado en las Artes Umbra. Durante mucho tiempo, ese hecho fue "
"usado por los profesores como evidencia de cuán peligroso podía ser ese "
"camino, pues ningún maestro se atrevía a caminar demasiado lejos en él. Sin "
"embargo, durante los Años de los Dos Soles algunos entusiastas del Umbra "
"denunciaron ese miedo como puro prejuicio, basado en un antiguo sesgo contra "
"los Señores Liche de Skiron. Argumentando que las Artes Umbra nunca habían "
"sido comprendidas adecuadamente debido a ese «miedo», esos magos Umbra se "
"dedicaron a ese camino específico.\n"
"\n"
"Entre estos magos destaca probablemente Wesir Amarnat. A pesar de su "
"conocida afición por la ostentación, durante muchos años se negó a mostrar "
"sus poderes Umbra. Sin embargo, durante una guerra en la que Nueva Maat'Kare "
"se encontró sitiada por un ejército orco que superaba en número a toda la "
"población de la ciudad por 3 a 1; presentó a sus compatriotas los frutos de "
"sus décadas de estudio en una demostración de poder que dejó a amigos y "
"enemigos por igual en asombro. Un cronista que fue testigo del evento "
"escribió que «fue como si el equilibrio de las dimensiones se hubiera roto, "
"trayendo la Tierra de los Muertos misma sobre el Mundo de los Vivos». Tras "
"esa batalla, Wesir se conoció como el «Dios de la Muerte».\n"
"\n"
"Como Maestro Umbra y distinguido miembro de la Cámara de Sabios de Nueva "
"Maat'Kare, es un ejemplo de cómo uno podía conservar la cordura y la "
"legalidad mientras se sumergía en la magia oscura."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:34
msgid "staff of rebirth"
msgstr "bastón del renacimiento"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:46
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/undead/Umbra_Master_Lich.cfg:58
msgid "deathly tempest"
msgstr "tempestad mortal"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:59
msgid "umbra wave"
msgstr "ola umbra"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/maatkarians/Umbra_Master.cfg:71
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/undead/Umbra_Master_Lich.cfg:83
msgid "Nefthys Hepet"
msgstr "Nefthys Hepet"

#. [unit_type], id=Agniraksha, race=trueelemental
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Agniraksha.cfg:4
msgid "Agniraksha"
msgstr "Agniraksha"

#. [unit_type], id=Agniraksha, race=trueelemental
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Agniraksha.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Drake legends tell of monsters that dwell in the bowels of volcanoes and in "
"the deepest chambers of the world, and who once guarded the legendary "
"Aghayu, the Citadel of Dragons. These monsters were behemoths of undying "
"fire and lava who could wound even dragons with their massive strength, "
"while not even the hottest flame or the sharpest claw could inflict any "
"considerable damage on them. Such were the Agnirakshai, or Burning Demons; "
"though there is no drake yet living who has seen them, stories of the "
"devastation they were said to wreak instil fear in many drakes - and the "
"fact that even the mighty fire lizards are afraid of them is probably the "
"best testament of the terror they once inspired."
msgstr ""
"Las leyendas draco hablan de monstruos que habitan en las entrañas de los "
"volcanes y en las cámaras más profundas del mundo, y que alguna vez "
"custodiaron el legendario Aghayu, la Ciudadela de los Dragones. Estos "
"monstruos eran behemoths de fuego y lava inmortales que podían herir incluso "
"a dragones con su fuerza masiva, mientras que ni la llama más caliente ni la "
"garra más afilada podían infligirles daño considerable. Tales eran los "
"Agnirakshai, o Demonios Ardientes; aunque no hay draco vivo que los haya "
"visto, las historias de la devastación que supuestamente causaban infunden "
"miedo en muchos dracos… y el hecho de que incluso los poderosos lagartos de "
"fuego les teman es probablemente el mejor testimonio del terror que alguna "
"vez inspiraron."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Agniraksha.cfg:131
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Agniraksha.cfg:140
msgid "magma fist"
msgstr "puño de magma"

#. [unit_type], id=Armageddon Drake Female, race=drake, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Armageddon_Female.cfg:4
msgid "Armageddon Drake"
msgstr "Draco armagedón"

#. [unit_type], id=Armageddon Drake Female, race=drake, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Armageddon_Female.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Were it not for the armor they wear, certain drakes might be "
"indistinguishable from true dragons, at least to the lesser races for whom "
"dragons are but legend. The creatures known as ‘Armageddon Drakes’ are "
"towering things, both immune to and possessed of a tremendous fire."
msgstr ""
"Si no fuera por la armadura que portan, ciertos dracos serían "
"indistinguibles de los verdaderos dragones, al menos para aquellas razas "
"inferiores para las que los dragones no son más que una leyenda. Las "
"criaturas conocidas como «draco armagedón» son seres gigantescos poseedores "
"de un fuego abrasador e inmunes a él."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Armageddon_Female.cfg:50
msgid "battle claws"
msgstr "garras de batalla"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Armageddon_Female.cfg:59
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/true-elementals/Agni.cfg:118
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/true-elementals/Fire_Embodiment.cfg:108
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/true-elementals/Fire_Spirit.cfg:91
msgid "fire breath"
msgstr "aliento ardiente"

#. [unit_type], id=Automaton, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Automaton.cfg:6
msgid "Automaton"
msgstr "Autómata"

#. [unit_type], id=Automaton, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Automaton.cfg:36
msgid ""
"These small metallic beasts seem not to need food or suchlike to live, very "
"similar to undead. However, they cannot be such, since their resistance to "
"fire, cold and arcane attacks is surprisingly high. Heavily armored, "
"wielding a perilous steel mace and a rectangular shield, these ‘automatons’ "
"are the new grunt attack and defense force of the evil forces that have "
"taken over the known world. They somehow move rather quickly for their "
"weight, a mystery that no one has been able yet to decipher. Their only "
"drawback is their apparent lack of practice at moving in rough terrains such "
"as hills and mountains."
msgstr ""
"Estas pequeñas bestias metálicas parecen no necesitar comida ni nada "
"parecido para vivir, muy similares a los no-muertos. Sin embargo, no pueden "
"serlo, ya que su resistencia al fuego, al frío y a los ataques arcanos es "
"sorprendentemente alta. Fuertemente blindados, empuñando una peligrosa maza "
"de acero y un escudo rectangular, estos «autómatas» son la nueva fuerza de "
"ataque y defensa de infantería de las fuerzas malignas que han tomado el "
"control del mundo conocido. De alguna manera se mueven bastante rápido para "
"su peso, un misterio que nadie ha logrado descifrar aún. Su único "
"inconveniente es su aparente falta de práctica para moverse en terrenos "
"accidentados como colinas y montañas."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Automaton.cfg:44
msgid "morning star"
msgstr "lucero del alba"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Automaton.cfg:53
msgid "rectangular shield"
msgstr "escudo rectangular"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Wayfarer AotDS, race=dunefolk
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Batal.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Wayfarer"
msgstr "Viajero barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Wayfarer AotDS, race=dunefolk
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Batal.cfg:18
msgid "There is currently no description available for this unit."
msgstr "Actualmente no hay descripción disponible para esta unidad."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Chariot, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Caravan.cfg:6
msgid "Chariot"
msgstr "Carro"

#. [unit_type], id=High Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Celestial_Seraphin.cfg:5
msgid "High Seraph"
msgstr "Serafín Alto"

#. [unit_type], id=High Seraph, race=celestial, gender=male
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Celestial_Seraphin.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some Seraphs manage to awaken their full inner power, stemmed from the "
"heavenly blood that runs in their veins, and thus become creatures of "
"amazing might. Although no one has ever seen the beings from which the "
"Celestials descend, gazing upon an Ascended Seraph offers the observer a "
"glimpse of their power and glory."
msgstr ""
"Algunos Serafines logran despertar todo su poder interior, proveniente de la "
"sangre celestial que corre por sus venas, y así se convierten en criaturas "
"de fuerza asombrosa. Aunque nadie ha visto jamás a los seres de los que "
"descienden los Celestiales, contemplar a un Serafín Ascendido ofrece al "
"observador un atisbo de su poder y gloria."

#. [unit_type], id=Chomi Vessel, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Chomi_Vessel.cfg:5
msgid "Chomi Vessel"
msgstr "Embarcación Chomi"

#. [unit_type], id=Chomi Vessel, race=mechanical
#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Vessel, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Chomi_Vessel.cfg:19
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/MaatKarian_Vessel.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Chomi vessels are long and slender; albeit frail-looking, it can transport "
"dozens of people through long journeys over even the stormiest seas."
msgstr ""
"Los barcos chomi son largos y esbeltos; aunque parecen frágiles, pueden "
"transportar docenas de personas en largos viajes incluso por los mares más "
"tormentosos."

#. [unit_type], id=Earth Core, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Earth_Core.cfg:4
msgid "Earthenheart"
msgstr "Corazón Terrestre"

#. [unit_type], id=Earth Core, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Earth_Core.cfg:35
msgid ""
"The Earthenheart is an ancient rock imbued with great and mysterious powers. "
"According to troll myth, it was created by Griknagh, the greatest of trolls, "
"to control the seismic activity in the region. Be it truth or myth, the fact "
"stands that the Heart Mountains are riddled with dormant volcanoes..."
msgstr ""
"El Corazón Terrestre es una roca antigua imbuida de grandes y misteriosos "
"poderes. Según el mito troll, fue creado por Griknagh, el mayor de los "
"trolls, para controlar la actividad sísmica en la región. Sea verdad o mito, "
"el hecho es que las Montañas del Corazón están plagadas de volcanes dormidos…"

#. [unit_type], id=Windsong Farstrider, race=windsong, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Farstrider.cfg:5
msgid "female^Farstrider"
msgstr "Caminante Lejana"

#. [unit_type], id=Windsong Farstrider, race=windsong, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Farstrider.cfg:21
msgid ""
"One of the oldest tales that have come down from the wars of the ancients "
"tells of a great battle between the Windsong and their old nemeses, the "
"elves. Each side sent their fastest runner to call for reinforcements, and "
"though the elves felt assured of their agile messenger's victory over his "
"frail human opponent, in the end, the elf fell behind, cursing his weary "
"feet. The Farstrider, on the other hand, ran with the speed and endurance of "
"the wind, and when the Windsong reinforcements arrived two days early, the "
"elves were forced to surrender."
msgstr ""
"Una de las historias más antiguas que han llegado de las guerras de los "
"antiguos cuenta de una gran batalla entre las Hijas del Viento y sus "
"antiguos némesis, los elfos. Cada bando envió a su corredor más rápido para "
"pedir refuerzos, y aunque los elfos estaban seguros de la victoria de su "
"ágil mensajero sobre su frágil oponente humano, al final, el elfo quedó "
"atrás, maldiciendo sus pies cansados. La Caminante Lejana, por otro lado, "
"corrió con la velocidad y resistencia del viento, y cuando los refuerzos "
"Windsong llegaron dos días antes, los elfos se vieron obligados a rendirse."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Farstrider.cfg:49
msgid "Lightning"
msgstr "Relámpago"

#. [unit_type], id=Imperial Flagship, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Flagship.cfg:5
msgid "Imperial Flagship"
msgstr "Buque Insignia Imperial"

#. [unit_type], id=Imperial Flagship, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Flagship.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Untrue to its ancestors' seafaring past, Wesnothians have remained a "
"continental people for many centuries after the kingdom's founding. In the "
"later years of the long-lived Hagarthen Dynasty, however, the maritime past "
"of Wesnoth was rediscovered, and the Wesnothians unleashed themselves upon "
"the seas once again, expanding their empire over the ocean, and learning new "
"seafaring skills in the process. The dreaded Imperial Warships are the "
"culmination of Wesnoth's great naval age: swift and resilient, these "
"juggernauts combine the magic lore of Alduin's mages and the sheer firepower "
"of dwarvish 'explosive dust' to become nigh-invincible engines of "
"exploration and destruction.\n"
"\n"
"Flagships, by their turn, are almost identical to warships in structure and "
"weaponry. Designed to lead the Wesnothian fleets from the vanguard, both "
"their armour and their weaponry are augmented in comparison to that of "
"normal warships."
msgstr ""
"Fieles a su pasado marítimo ancestral, los wesnothianos permanecieron como "
"un pueblo continental durante muchos siglos tras la fundación del reino. Sin "
"embargo, en los últimos años de la longeva Dinastía Hagarthen, el pasado "
"marítimo de Wesnoth fue redescubierto, y los wesnothianos se lanzaron "
"nuevamente sobre los mares, expandiendo su imperio sobre el océano y "
"aprendiendo nuevas habilidades marítimas en el proceso. Los temidos Buques "
"de Guerra Imperiales son la culminación de la gran era naval de Wesnoth: "
"rápidos y resistentes, estos colosos combinan el conocimiento mágico de los "
"magos de Alduin y el puro poder de fuego del «polvo explosivo» enano para "
"convertirse en motores casi invencibles de exploración y destrucción.\n"
"\n"
"Los buques insignia, por su parte, son casi idénticos a los buques de guerra "
"en estructura y armamento. Diseñados para liderar las flotas wesnothianas "
"desde la vanguardia, tanto su armadura como su armamento están mejorados en "
"comparación con los de los buques de guerra normales."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Flagship.cfg:39
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Warship.cfg:37
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Watch_Tower.cfg:50
msgid "volley of arrows"
msgstr "andanada de flechas"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Flagship.cfg:52
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Warship.cfg:50
msgid "fire cannon"
msgstr "cañón de fuego"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Flagship.cfg:65
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Warship.cfg:63
msgid "dragon cannon"
msgstr "cañón de dragón"

#. [unit_type], id=Human_Lady, race=human, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Human_Lady.cfg:5
msgid "female^Lady"
msgstr "Dama"

#. [unit_type], id=Human_Lady, race=human, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Human_Lady.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Refined and elegant, the noblewomen of Wesnoth may not have martial or "
"magical skills, but their influence in the kingdom's politics must not be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""
"Refinadas y elegantes, las damas nobles de Wesnoth pueden no tener "
"habilidades marciales ni mágicas, pero su influencia en la política del "
"reino no debe subestimarse."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Vessel, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/MaatKarian_Vessel.cfg:5
msgid "Maat'Karian Transport Ship"
msgstr "Barco de Transporte Maat'kariano"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/MaatKarian_Vessel.cfg:39
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Watch_Tower.cfg:76
msgid "ballista"
msgstr "balista"

#. [unit_type], id=Merman Thunder Fighter, race=merman
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Merman Thunder Fighter"
msgstr "Luchador del trueno sirenido"

#. [unit_type], id=Merman Thunder Fighter, race=merman
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Fighter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Skilled denizens of the sea, Mermen are powerful and quick in any watery "
"environment, but lose most of their mobility on land. Even so, the powerful "
"storm tridents they wield make them fearsome opponents on any ground."
msgstr ""
"Hábil habitante del mar, los sirenidos son poderosos y rápidos en cualquier "
"entorno acuático, pero pierden la mayor parte de su movilidad en tierra. Aun "
"así, los poderosos tridentes de tormenta que empuñan los convierten en "
"oponentes temibles en cualquier terreno."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Fighter.cfg:36
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Warrior.cfg:38
msgid "trident"
msgstr "tridente"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Fighter.cfg:44
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Warrior.cfg:46
msgid "storm trident"
msgstr "tridente de las tormentas"

#. [unit_type], id=Merman Thunder Warrior, race=merman
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Merman Thunder Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrero del trueno sirenido"

#. [unit_type], id=Merman Thunder Warrior, race=merman
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Merman_Thunder_Warrior.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Mermen Warriors form the core of the mermen armies. Wielding powerful "
"tridents, they are a bane to any who dare enter their waters.\n"
"        \n"
"        Having mastered the use of the storm trident, these warriors are one "
"of the main reasons of the merfolk dominance of the seas."
msgstr ""
"Los Guerreros Sirénidos forman el núcleo de los ejércitos sirénidos. "
"Empuñando poderosos tridentes, son el azote de cualquiera que se atreva a "
"entrar en sus aguas.\n"
"\n"
"Al haber dominado el uso del tridente de tormenta, estos guerreros son una "
"de las principales razones de la dominación sirénida de los mares."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Harrier AotDS, race=dunefolk
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Mighwar.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Harrier"
msgstr "Acosador de Dunas"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Harrier AotDS, race=dunefolk
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Mighwar.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The Khalifate uses these Hillmen as their foot force. They are versatile and "
"excel in hilly terrain."
msgstr ""
"El Califato usa a estos Hombres de las Colinas como su fuerza de infantería. "
"Son versátiles y destacan en terreno montañoso."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Mighwar.cfg:26
msgid "long sword"
msgstr "espada larga"

#. [unit_type], id=Irdya_Spear, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Spear_of_Irdya.cfg:4
msgid "Light of Irdya"
msgstr "Luz de Irdya"

#. [unit_type], id=Irdya_Spear, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Spear_of_Irdya.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The Light of Irdya is an engine created by the Windsong. Capable of "
"channelling the energy of the planet itself, and of shooting it in the shape "
"of a beam, it is possibly the most dangerous mass destruction weapon ever "
"created on the face of this planet."
msgstr ""
"La Luz de Irdya es un motor creado por las Hijas del Viento. Capaz de "
"canalizar la energía del planeta mismo y dispararla en forma de rayo, es "
"posiblemente el arma de destrucción masiva más peligrosa jamás creada en la "
"faz de este planeta."

#. [unit_type], id=Imperial Warship, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Warship.cfg:5
msgid "Imperial Warship"
msgstr "Buque de Guerra Imperial"

#. [unit_type], id=Imperial Warship, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Warship.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Untrue to its ancestors' seafaring past, Wesnothians have remained a "
"continental people for many centuries after the kingdom's founding. In the "
"later years of the long-lived Hagarthen Dynasty, however, the maritime past "
"of Wesnoth was rediscovered, and the Wesnothians unleashed themselves upon "
"the seas once again, expanding their empire over the ocean, and learning new "
"seafaring skills in the process. The dreaded Imperial Warships are the "
"culmination of Wesnoth's great naval age: swift and resilient, these "
"juggernauts combine the magic lore of Alduin's mages and the sheer firepower "
"of dwarvish 'explosive dust' to become nigh-invincible engines of "
"exploration and destruction."
msgstr ""
"Fieles a su pasado marítimo ancestral, los wesnothianos permanecieron como "
"un pueblo continental durante muchos siglos tras la fundación del reino. Sin "
"embargo, en los últimos años de la longeva Dinastía Hagarthen, el pasado "
"marítimo de Wesnoth fue redescubierto, y los wesnothianos se lanzaron "
"nuevamente sobre los mares, expandiendo su imperio sobre el océano y "
"aprendiendo nuevas habilidades marítimas en el proceso. Los temidos Buques "
"de Guerra Imperiales son la culminación de la gran era naval de Wesnoth: "
"rápidos y resistentes, estos colosos combinan el conocimiento mágico de los "
"magos de Alduin y el puro poder de fuego del «polvo explosivo» enano para "
"convertirse en motores casi invencibles de exploración y destrucción."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Tower, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Watch_Tower.cfg:4
msgid "Maat'Karian Defence Tower"
msgstr "Torre de Defensa Maat'kariana"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Tower, race=mechanical
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Watch_Tower.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Watch Towers are good places from which to spot enemies and then shoot "
"miscellaneous items at them with ballistas."
msgstr ""
"Las Torres de Vigilancia son buenos lugares desde los que detectar enemigos "
"y luego dispararles diversos objetos con ballestas."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/miscelanea/Watch_Tower.cfg:63
msgid "volley of fire arrows"
msgstr "andanada de flechas de fuego"

#. [unit_type], id=Akuma, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Akuma.cfg:4
msgid "Akuma"
msgstr "Akuma"

#. [unit_type], id=Akuma, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Akuma.cfg:17
msgid ""
"There are many legends told amongst the Ken-Ningen about masters who, by "
"their talent and by their utter dedication to the path of the sword, have "
"transcended the level of normal humans. Wielding their katanas like "
"extensions of both their body and soul, and boasting a speed so high that "
"their opponents are often rendered unable to even defend themselves, they "
"live as hermits, wandering lands beyond Kodakuni after opponents who can at "
"the very least pose a challenge to their blades. Feared and respected by all "
"Sogen, rarely answering to any lord, these monsters have earned the dubbing "
"of Akumas, which means 'devil' in the Sogen language, and in them the terror "
"once inspired by the Hannuks lives on."
msgstr ""
"Hay muchas leyendas contadas entre los Ken-Ningen sobre maestros que, por su "
"talento y su absoluta dedicación al camino de la espada, han trascendido el "
"nivel de los humanos normales. Empuñando sus katanas como extensiones tanto "
"de su cuerpo como de su alma, y presumiendo de una velocidad tan alta que "
"sus oponentes a menudo quedan incapaces incluso de defenderse, viven como "
"ermitaños, vagando por tierras más allá de Kodakuni en busca de oponentes "
"que al menos puedan plantear un desafío a sus hojas. Temidos y respetados "
"por todos los Sogen, raramente responden a ningún señor, estos monstruos han "
"ganado el apodo de Akumas, que significa «diablo» en la lengua sogen, y en "
"ellos perdura el terror que alguna vez inspiraron los Hannuks."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Akuma.cfg:82
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Master.cfg:65
msgid "katana: way of offence"
msgstr "katana: camino del ataque"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Akuma.cfg:94
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Master.cfg:77
msgid "katana: way of defence"
msgstr "katana: camino de la defensa"

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Akuma.cfg:106
msgid "shunpo"
msgstr "shunpo"

#. [unit_type], id=Sogen Arrow Cavalry, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Arrow_Cavalry.cfg:4
msgid "Arrow Cavalry"
msgstr "Caballería de Flechas"

#. [unit_type], id=Hachiman Priestess, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Hachiman_Priestess.cfg:4
msgid "Hachiman Priestess"
msgstr "Sacerdotisa Hachiman"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Hachiman_Priestess.cfg:58
msgid "spirit arrow"
msgstr "flecha espiritual"

#. [unit_type], id=Sogen Huntress, race=sogen
#. [unit_type], id=Washraha Huntress, race=washraha, gender=female
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Huntress.cfg:4
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/washraha/Washraha_Huntress.cfg:4
msgid "Huntress"
msgstr "Cazadora"

#. [unit_type], id=Ken Master, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Ken Master"
msgstr "Maestro Ken"

#. [unit_type], id=Ken Master, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Master.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The path of the Ken Warrior is one that never ends, as he knows that there "
"is always room for self-improvement. After becoming profficient in the use "
"of the katana and in offensive techniques, Ken Warriors will pursue the "
"mastery of dual-sword fighting styles. This requires them to improve their "
"own speed, which in turn result in a flurry of slashing blows against which "
"few enemies can possibly stand.\n"
"\n"
"Some might think that the addition of a second sword to their arsenal would "
"diminish their defensive power, but Ken Masters have more than once proved "
"that there are far more uses to a sword than in attacking techniques."
msgstr ""
"El camino del Guerrero Ken es uno que nunca termina, ya que sabe que siempre "
"hay espacio para la superación personal. Tras volverse competente en el uso "
"de la katana y en técnicas ofensivas, los Guerreros Ken persiguen el dominio "
"de estilos de combate con dos espadas. Esto les requiere mejorar su propia "
"velocidad, lo que a su vez resulta en una ráfaga de golpes cortantes contra "
"los que pocos enemigos pueden resistir.\n"
"\n"
"Algunos podrían pensar que la adición de una segunda espada a su arsenal "
"disminuiría su poder defensivo, pero los Maestros Ken han demostrado más de "
"una vez que hay muchos más usos para una espada que solo en técnicas de "
"ataque."

#. [unit_type], id=Ken Warrior, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Ken Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrero Ken"

#. [unit_type], id=Ken Warrior, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Ken_Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"When Wesnothians first fought against the Sogen, they were surprised and "
"puzzled by the fact that the enemy swordsmen ran into battle wearing very "
"little armour. The Ken-Ningen, by their turn, disdained the Wesnothians for "
"their use of heavy armour, deeming them cowards who were afraid of getting "
"wounded, as well as clumsy fighters who swang their swords as if their were "
"clubs. Their arrogance may be excused, however; those sword walkers who, by "
"their skill and honour, have earned the right to be known as Ken Warriors, "
"wield their weapons with a precision that renders the best defensive stances "
"useless."
msgstr ""
"Cuando los wesnothianos lucharon por primera vez contra los Sogen, se "
"sorprendieron y desconcertaron por el hecho de que los espadachines enemigos "
"corrían al combate con muy poca armadura. Los Ken-Ningen, por su parte, "
"desdeñaban a los wesnothianos por su uso de armadura pesada, considerándolos "
"cobardes que temían resultar heridos, así como luchadores torpes que "
"blandían sus espadas como si fueran garrotes. Su arrogancia puede excusarse, "
"sin embargo; aquellos caminantes de espada que, por su habilidad y honor, "
"han ganado el derecho a ser conocidos como Guerreros Ken, empuñan sus armas "
"con una precisión que vuelve inútiles las mejores posturas defensivas."

#. [unit_type], id=Sogen Priestess, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Priestess.cfg:4
msgid "Priestess"
msgstr "Sacerdotisa"

