#. [unit_type], id=Sogen Steppe Master, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Sogen_Steppe_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Steppe Master"
msgstr "Maestro de las Estepas"

#. [unit_type], id=Sword Walker, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Sword_Walker.cfg:4
msgid "Sword Walker"
msgstr "Caminante de Espada"

#. [unit_type], id=Sword Walker, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Sword_Walker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The ancestors of the Sogen, a steppe nation known as the Hannuks, had been "
"fierce warriors and conquerors, who plundered and destroyed everything that "
"stood on their path. Such behaviour was what made them feared by "
"neighbouring nations, but that was also their downfall: with the "
"desertification of the steppes and the scarcity of resources, the Hannuk "
"clans raided each other, brutally destroying other clans until there was "
"none left.\n"
"\n"
"The aggressiveness of the Hannuks is reminded by the Sogen as a lesson of "
"how an excessively warlike culture can destroy even itself. Those who wish "
"to become warriors need not only to learn how to fight, but they must also "
"follow a strict code of conduct which deems honour, mercy towards the weak "
"and obedience to a lord as the highest principles. Moreover, both their "
"training and their identity as warriors is intrinsically related to the "
"katana, a unique type of sword with great slashing power, but which requires "
"skilful handling. Because it is a melee weapon, and because it demands great "
"concentration and control, the katana is regarded as the most honourable and "
"civilised of weapons. Such is the importance of this weapon to the Sogen's "
"warrior orders that they are collectively known as the Ken-Ningen, or the "
"Sword People.\n"
"\n"
"Those who are initiates in the path of the sword have learned only basic "
"offensive techniques, but even so they are swordsmen to be feared even by "
"their Wesnothian counterparts."
msgstr ""
"Los ancestros de los Sogen, una nación esteparia conocida como los Hannuks, "
"habían sido feroces guerreros y conquistadores que saqueaban y destruían "
"todo lo que se interponía en su camino. Tal comportamiento fue lo que los "
"hizo temidos por las naciones vecinas, pero también fue su perdición: con la "
"desertificación de las estepas y la escasez de recursos, los clanes hannuk "
"se asaltaron entre sí, destruyéndose brutalmente hasta que no quedó "
"ninguno.\n"
"\n"
"La agresividad de los Hannuks es recordada por los Sogen como una lección de "
"cómo una cultura excesivamente bélica puede destruir incluso a sí misma. "
"Aquellos que desean convertirse en guerreros no solo necesitan aprender a "
"luchar, sino que también deben seguir un estricto código de conducta que "
"considera el honor, la misericordia hacia los débiles y la obediencia a un "
"señor como los principios más altos. Además, tanto su entrenamiento como su "
"identidad como guerreros están intrínsecamente relacionados con la katana, "
"un tipo único de espada con gran poder de corte, pero que requiere un manejo "
"hábil. Al ser un arma de cuerpo a cuerpo y exigir gran concentración y "
"control, la katana es considerada el arma más honorable y civilizada. Tal es "
"la importancia de esta arma para las órdenes guerreras sogen que "
"colectivamente se les conoce como los Ken-Ningen, o el Pueblo de la Espada.\n"
"\n"
"Aquellos que son iniciados en el camino de la espada solo han aprendido "
"técnicas ofensivas básicas, pero aun así son espadachines temidos incluso "
"por sus contrapartes wesnothianas."

#. [unit_type], id=Yasai Peasant, race=sogen
#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Yasai.cfg:20
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Yasai.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Those amongst the Sogen who live an agricultural life are known as Yasai-"
"ningen, or 'farmer people'. They're generally despised by the Ken-ningen and "
"the Uma-ningen; they ignore that, without the food cultivated and collected "
"by the Yasai, the Sogen people would never have become so numerous, as the "
"crops cultivated by Ken and Uma are not enough to sustain large populations."
msgstr ""
"Aquellos entre los Sogen que viven una vida agrícola son conocidos como "
"Yasai-ningen, o «gente agricultora». Generalmente son despreciados por los "
"Ken-ningen y los Uma-ningen; ignoran que, sin la comida cultivada y "
"recolectada por los Yasai, el pueblo sogen nunca habría crecido tanto, ya "
"que los cultivos de los Ken y Uma no son suficientes para sostener grandes "
"poblaciones."

#. [female]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Yasai.cfg:25
msgid "female^Yasai Peasant"
msgstr "Campesina Yasai"

#. [unit_type], id=Yasai Warrior, race=sogen
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/units/sogen/Yasai_Warrior.cfg:4
