msgid "warmed"
msgstr "calentado"

#. [lua]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/freezing-utils.cfg:218
msgid ""
"frozen: This unit is freezing. It will lose 2 HP and have its damage reduced "
"by 1 each turn unless prevented by healers or shelter at a village, a keep "
"or a castle.\n"
"\n"
"Units cannot be killed or deal no damage as a result of freezing."
msgstr ""
"congelado: Esta unidad está congelándose. Perderá 2 PV y su daño se reducirá "
"en 1 cada turno a menos que sea prevenido por sanadores o se resguarde en "
"una aldea, torreón o castillo.\n"
"\n"
"Las unidades no pueden morir ni dejar de hacer daño como resultado de la "
"congelación."

#. [message], speaker=Tenma
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:15
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:102
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:217
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:360
msgid "Back to the earth I return... Too soon..."
msgstr "De vuelta a la tierra regreso… Demasiado pronto…"

#. [message], speaker=Olokun
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:29
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:116
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:231
msgid "I have... failed my mission..."
msgstr "He… fallado en mi misión…"

#. [message], speaker=Kenshiro
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:43
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:130
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:245
msgid "I've been defeated... Now only death can spare me this shame..."
msgstr ""
"He sido derrotado… Ahora solo la muerte puede librarme de esta vergüenza…"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:158
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:273
msgid "Damn it!!! I'm not... going... to fall... like this...!"
msgstr "¡Maldición! ¡No… voy… a caer… así…!"

#. [message], speaker=Donar
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:287
msgid "Aaarrrgghhh!!! Damn them...!"
msgstr "¡Aaarrrgghhh! ¡Malditos sean…!"

#. [message], speaker=Aetheryon
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:301
msgid "I can't... die... before... knowing everyhing...!!!"
msgstr "¡No puedo… morir… antes… de saberlo todo…!"

#. [message], speaker=Kenshiro
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:393
msgid "How could I die when my friends... and her... need me most...?"
msgstr "¿Cómo podría morir cuando mis amigos… y ella… más me necesitan…?"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:397
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:565
msgid "KENSHIRO!!! Damn it, how could I let this happen...?!"
msgstr "¡KENSHIRO! Maldición, ¿cómo pude permitir que esto ocurriera…?"

#. [message], speaker=Valerya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:412
msgid "I've fallen... Alas, I wish I could see you grow, young friends..."
msgstr "He caído… Ay, ojalá pudiera verlos crecer, jóvenes amigos…"

#. [message], speaker=Algil
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:464
msgid ""
"Arrgghh!!! I fall before fulfilling my promise to Udhark... alas, we had "
"such a great chance to end... the war between dwarves and trolls..."
msgstr ""
"¡Arrgghh! Caigo antes de cumplir mi promesa a Udhark… ay, teníamos una gran "
"oportunidad de terminar… la guerra entre enanos y trolls…"

#. [message], speaker=Tenma
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:691
msgid "I... have failed...?"
msgstr "¿He… fallado…?"

#. [message], speaker=Gelendras
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:862
msgid ""
"I go to father's side... Please, lead our people to a better future, "
"sister..."
msgstr ""
"Voy al lado de padre… Por favor, guía a nuestra gente hacia un futuro mejor, "
"hermana…"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:866
msgid "No! Brother, you cannot die now!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Hermano, no puedes morir ahora!"

#. [message], speaker=Idunn
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:881
msgid ""
"I go to the First's side... Queen-in-the-Woods, please protect the Children "
"of the Forests..."
msgstr ""
"Voy al lado de los Primeros… Reina-en-el-Bosque, por favor protege a los "
"Hijos de los Bosques…"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:885
msgid "No! Idunn, you cannot die now!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Idunn, no puedes morir ahora!"

#. [message], speaker=Bogor
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:900
msgid "How could I fall to these puny vermin...?!"
msgstr "¿Cómo pude caer ante estas miserables alimañas…?"

#. [message], speaker=Ankhmare
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:915
msgid "I have fallen... Olokun, make sure there is a future for all of us..."
msgstr "He caído… Olokun, asegúrate de que haya un futuro para todos nosotros…"

#. [message], speaker=Olokun
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:919
msgid "Master, you can't die now!"
msgstr "¡Maestro, no puedes morir ahora!"

#. [message], speaker=Aeldhoryan
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:938
msgid ""
"No! Dragana Vasilya could have been a great ally for the Wesnothians in the "
"future!"
msgstr ""
"¡No! ¡Dragana Vasilya podría haber sido una gran aliada para los "
"wesnothianos en el futuro!"

#. [message], speaker=Udhark
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:957
msgid ""
"Rest in peace, my friend; though the Northern Alliance is no more, its "
"ideals shall live on with our descendants!"
msgstr ""
"Descansa en paz, amigo mío; aunque la Alianza del Norte ya no existe, ¡sus "
"ideales vivirán con nuestros descendientes!"

#. [message], speaker=Natsu
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:972
msgid ""
"I wish we could return to Kodakuni and see the cherry trees as free people, "
"but unfortunately, all I can do is promise I'll make sure your name is made "
"immortal by the scrolls of Umashima. Rest in peace, noble Ikki."
msgstr ""
"Ojalá pudiéramos regresar a Kodakuni y ver los cerezos como personas libres, "
"pero lamentablemente, lo único que puedo hacer es prometer que me aseguraré "
"de que tu nombre sea inmortalizado en los pergaminos de Umashima. Descansa "
"en paz, noble Ikki."

#. [message], speaker=Umbrius
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:983
msgid "Queen-in-the-Woods, please forgive me..."
msgstr "Reina-en-el-Bosque, por favor perdóname…"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:987
msgid ""
"It is I who must be forgiven for not being able to protect you. Rest with "
"the Mother, noble Umbrius, for we shall not allow your death to be in vain."
msgstr ""
"Soy yo quien debe ser perdonada por no haber podido protegerte. Descansa con "
"la Madre, noble Umbrius, pues no permitiremos que tu muerte sea en vano."

#. [message], speaker=Midori
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:999
msgid "Alas, I wish I could at least say goodbye to Tenma..."
msgstr "Ay, ojalá al menos pudiera despedirme de Tenma…"

#. [message], speaker=Natsu
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:1003
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:1019
msgid ""
"Don't worry, my dear, I'll make sure your feelings get to her. Now, rest in "
"peace with the Great Kami, for you deserve it."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes, querido, me aseguraré de que tus sentimientos le lleguen. "
"Ahora, descansa en paz con los Grandes Kami, pues lo mereces."

#. [message], speaker=Akane
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:1015
msgid ""
"Ugh! These darn idiots caught me in the end... I only wish I could see Tenma "
"once more..."
msgstr ""
"¡Ugh! Estos malditos idiotas me atraparon al final… Solo deseo poder ver a "
"Tenma una vez más…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Welcome back, traveller. I knew you'd return for another story; in this era "
"of chaos, where the fight for survival is so violent that only the moment "
"matters, few are left who bother to remember the things that once took place "
"in this vast world of ours."
msgstr ""
"Bienvenido de nuevo, viajero. Sabía que regresarías por otra historia; en "
"esta era de caos, donde la lucha por la supervivencia es tan violenta que "
"solo importa el momento, quedan pocos que se molesten en recordar las cosas "
"que alguna vez ocurrieron en este vasto mundo nuestro."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:12
msgid ""
"I've sung about tales of ages long gone: the tale of Myra of Hiera'Shirsha "
"from a time where dragons still lived at large; the odyssey of Akhen Wadjet "
"from the days the oceans ceased being a frontier to humans... So now I shall "
"sing an aria of our age; or better, of how it began. For that was a time of "
"mighty heroes and great deeds, where both new and ancient powers confronted "
"each other in a battle for the world itself."
msgstr ""
"He cantado sobre cuentos de edades ya lejanas: la historia de Myra de "
"Hiera'Shirsha de un tiempo en que los dragones aún vivían libres; la odisea "
"de Akhen Wadjet de los días en que los océanos dejaron de ser una frontera "
"para los humanos… Así que ahora cantaré un aria de nuestra era; o mejor, de "
"cómo comenzó. Porque fue un tiempo de héroes poderosos y grandes hazañas, "
"donde tanto poderes nuevos como antiguos se enfrentaron en una batalla por "
"el mundo mismo."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This tale begins in a distant and small country called Kodakuni, home of the "
"Sogen people. There they lived in peace for a long time, isolated from other "
"nations by a vast desert to the east, and towering mountain ranges to the "
"west and north. But their lives were changed when they were attacked by a "
"nation from the far west; clad in steel armour, with powers over fire and "
"death, they called themselves Wesnothians; led by the mighty general "
"Aeldhoryan, second Prince of Wesnoth, they easily conquered the Sogen."
msgstr ""
"Este cuento comienza en un país lejano y pequeño llamado Kodakuni, hogar del "
"pueblo Sogen. Allí vivieron en paz durante mucho tiempo, aislados de otras "
"naciones por un vasto desierto al este y altas cordilleras al oeste y norte. "
"Pero sus vidas cambiaron cuando fueron atacados por una nación del lejano "
"oeste; vestidos con armadura de acero, con poderes sobre fuego y muerte, se "
"llamaban a sí mismos wesnothianos; liderados por el poderoso general "
"Aeldhoryan, segundo príncipe de Wesnoth, conquistaron fácilmente a los Sogen."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:20
msgid ""
"It was in Wesnoth-ruled Kodakuni that Tenma Yozora lived. After being "
"orphaned during Aeldhoryan's invasion, she was raised by her fellow "
"villagers from Kuroi; she was very liked by everyone for her liveliness and "
"kind heart, but she often was lectured for being too brash. And this "
"brashness played a crucial role on that day which changed her life and, "
"consequently, the fate of the entire world..."
msgstr ""
"Fue en el Kodakuni gobernado por Wesnoth donde vivía Tenma Yozora. Tras "
"quedar huérfana durante la invasión de Aeldhoryan, fue criada por sus "
"compañeros aldeanos de Kuroi; era muy querida por todos por su vitalidad y "
"corazón bondadoso, pero a menudo la reprendían por ser demasiado impulsiva. "
"Y esa impulsividad jugó un papel crucial en aquel día que cambió su vida y, "
"en consecuencia, el destino de todo el mundo…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:25
msgid "Part VII: Awakening from Legend"
msgstr "Parte VII: Despertar de la Leyenda"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:29
msgid "Journey's Beginning"
msgstr "Comienzo del Viaje"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:39
msgid ""
"Tenma felt a bit scared as she bid her fellow villagers farewell and "
"followed that mysterious foreigner towards the Kodakuni Mountains. She'd "
"never imagined herself leaving home; even travelling to the lands of the "
"neighbouring Uma-ningen felt like a once-in-a-lifetime journey, and now she "
"was going to lands she couldn't even dream of... But, when she remembered "
"that it was all to free her country and to understand more about herself, "
"she felt her resolve strengthen."
msgstr ""
"Tenma sintió un poco de miedo al despedirse de sus compañeros aldeanos y "
"seguir a aquel misterioso extranjero hacia las Montañas de Kodakuni. Nunca "
"se había imaginado dejando su hogar; incluso viajar a las tierras de los "
"vecinos Uma-ningen le parecía un viaje único en la vida, y ahora iba hacia "
"tierras que ni siquiera podía soñar… Pero, al recordar que todo era para "
"liberar a su país y entender más sobre sí misma, sintió que su determinación "
"se fortalecía."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Olokun explained that they were going to use an ancient system of caves in "
"the mountains which would take them far away from Kodakuni. According to "
"him, those caves were dug by peoples known as dwarves and trolls. He also "
"told more about that land's ancient inhabitants: of humans known as "
"Aragwaithi, of a forest-dwelling folk he called elves, and of how their "
"homes were all destroyed when an army of fire-breathing creatures called "
"drakes attacked them."
msgstr ""
"Olokun explicó que iban a usar un antiguo sistema de cuevas en las montañas "
"que los llevaría lejos de Kodakuni. Según él, esas cuevas fueron excavadas "
"por pueblos conocidos como enanos y trolls. También contó más sobre los "
"antiguos habitantes de esa tierra: de humanos conocidos como aragwaithi, de "
"un pueblo habitante de bosques que llamó elfos, y de cómo sus hogares fueron "
"destruidos cuando un ejército de criaturas escupidoras de fuego llamadas "
"dracos los atacó."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:45
msgid ""
"And, in that war, the Maat'Karians' heroine, Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, had "
"fought with distinction, alongside her equally renowned foster-mother, Maat. "
"After the war, Myra had led Aragwaithi and Hannuks, the people of her mother "
"and her father respectively, towards a continent beyond the sea; there they "
"founded Maat'Kare."
msgstr ""
"Y, en esa guerra, la heroína de los maat'karianos, Myra de Hiera'Shirsha, "
"había luchado con distinción junto a su igualmente renombrada madre "
"adoptiva, Maat. Tras la guerra, Myra había liderado a los aragwaithi y "
"hannuks, el pueblo de su madre y de su padre respectivamente, hacia un "
"continente más allá del mar; allí fundaron Maat'Kare."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:55
msgid ""
"They did find more undead in those caves, but they were little more than "
"scattered bands of walking corpses, and so they didn't pose a great threat. "
"The tunnels stretched far beneath the earth, always going north. After some "
"days in the dark, they found, in the middle of a tunnel, a stairway carved "
"into the stone, leading upwards; climbing it, they returned to surface."
msgstr ""
"Sí encontraron más no-muertos en esas cuevas, pero no eran más que bandas "
"dispersas de cadáveres andantes, y por eso no representaban una gran "
"amenaza. Los túneles se extendían lejos bajo la tierra, siempre hacia el "
"norte. Tras algunos días en la oscuridad, encontraron, en medio de un túnel, "
"una escalera tallada en la piedra que subía; al escalarla, regresaron a la "
"superficie."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:59
msgid ""
"They found themselves in a vast meadow, with few scattered trees here and "
"there; the tall, dark-green grass, the wild animals peacefully feeding on "
"it, and the chilly wind that blew, all indicated that they were in a wild "
"region outside the warm Kodakuni. Olokun said that they were in the Silent "
"Lands, a region to the centre-north of the continent which was uninhabited "
"by humans."
msgstr ""
"Se encontraron en una vasta pradera, con pocos árboles dispersos aquí y "
"allá; la alta hierba verde oscura, los animales salvajes alimentándose "
"pacíficamente de ella y el viento frío que soplaba indicaban que estaban en "
"una región salvaje fuera del cálido Kodakuni. Olokun dijo que estaban en las "
"Tierras Silenciosas, una región al centro-norte del continente deshabitada "
"por humanos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:63
msgid ""
"He insisted on remaining underground, but Tenma refused to remain in the "
"cold, damp caves any longer; and Kenshiro, mostly to pick on the "
"Maat'Karian, sided with her. But travelling throughout that land proved to "
"be enervating in its own way: used to living amidst many people, the Yasai "
"girl felt uneasy with the silence that was only broken by the wind's "
"howling, and she kept constant conversation with both her companions, to the "
"point that even the stoic Olokun started getting annoyed."
msgstr ""
"Él insistió en permanecer bajo tierra, pero Tenma se negó a seguir en las "
"cuevas frías y húmedas; y Kenshiro, principalmente para molestar al "
"maat'kariano, se puso de su lado. Pero viajar por esa tierra resultó "
"agotador a su manera: acostumbrada a vivir entre mucha gente, la chica Yasai "
"se sentía incómoda con el silencio que solo rompía el aullido del viento, y "
"mantuvo conversación constante con ambos compañeros, al punto que incluso el "
"estoico Olokun empezó a molestarse."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:67
msgid ""
"But this monotony was broken in their tenth day travelling through the "
"Silent Lands..."
msgstr ""
"Pero esta monotonía se rompió en su décimo día viajando por las Tierras "
"Silenciosas…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:78
msgid ""
"Understanding herself and her own powers more deeply made Tenma feel much "
"better, but she couldn't avoid feeling embarrassed at how Olokun often "
"stared at her with such fervent admiration - even if she understood that he "
"was just thrilled for having the reincarnation of his people's greatest "
"heroine next to him."
msgstr ""
"Entenderse mejor a sí misma y a sus propios poderes hizo que Tenma se "
"sintiera mucho mejor, pero no pudo evitar sentirse avergonzada por cómo "
"Olokun a menudo la miraba con tanta admiración férvida —aunque entendía que "
"solo estaba emocionado por tener junto a él a la reencarnación de la mayor "
"heroína de su pueblo."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:81
msgid ""
"She also reflected on the memories inherited from her past life. Those "
"memories resurfaced as feelings rather than images or sounds; of those, none "
"occupied her thoughts more than the feeling of dread inspired by the mere "
"mention of Svarballi, the strongest of the three High Dragons, and the one "
"who had tried to destroy the world so many times in the past. That was the "
"ultimate foe she'd have to face: the being once created by the mightiest of "
"the Avatars who created the universe, to protect the world of Demere, the "
"Avatar of Life - only to become its greatest threat..."
msgstr ""
"También reflexionó sobre los recuerdos heredados de su vida pasada. Esos "
"recuerdos resurgían como sentimientos más que como imágenes o sonidos; de "
"ellos, ninguno ocupaba más sus pensamientos que el sentimiento de terror "
"inspirado por la mera mención de Svarballi, el más fuerte de los tres "
"Grandes Dragones, y el que había intentado destruir el mundo tantas veces en "
"el pasado. Ese era el enemigo definitivo al que tendría que enfrentarse: el "
"ser creado una vez por el más poderoso de los Avatares que crearon el "
"universo, para proteger el mundo de Demere, el Avatar de la Vida —solo para "
"convertirse en su mayor amenaza…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:84
msgid ""
"But before fighting him, she still had to save her people from Wesnothian "
"tyranny. Travelling through the tunnels was far easier that time, as there "
"were no more undead there. From certain point on, the three travellers saw "
"no more passages to the surface; even though Olokun tried to convince her "
"otherwise, Tenma insisted on seeing that as a sign that Knalga was closer, "
"and so she made the two men speed up their pace. In the thirtieth day of "
"underground journey, they found the first sign of life in those tunnels..."
msgstr ""
"Pero antes de enfrentarlo, aún debía salvar a su pueblo de la tiranía "
"wesnothiana. Viajar por los túneles fue mucho más fácil esta vez, ya que ya "
"no había no-muertos allí. Desde cierto punto, los tres viajeros no vieron "
"más pasajes hacia la superficie; aunque Olokun intentó convencerla de lo "
"contrario, Tenma insistió en verlo como una señal de que Knalga estaba más "
"cerca, y así hizo que los dos hombres aceleraran el paso. En el trigésimo "
"día de viaje subterráneo, encontraron el primer signo de vida en esos "
"túneles…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:88
msgid "The Hammermounts"
msgstr "Los Hammermounts"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:98
msgid ""
"The news that they were so far from Knalga should have disheartened Tenma, "
"Olokun thought, but she looked very excited as she walked through the "
"tunnels of the Aurvang Dwarves of the Hammermounts. She examined those "
"beings she'd never seen before with a curiosity that, to many, would be "
"insulting, but the dwarves, like Olokun, were charmed by her cheerfulness "
"and energy. In Augdras' feast, she was the star of the evening, singing "
"songs of her people in loud voices and accepting any of the drinking "
"challenges the dwarves threw at her; after the sixth emptied bowl of beer, "
"Augdras, cheeks blushed, declared that Tenma was officially an honorary "
"member of his clan."
msgstr ""
"La noticia de que estaban tan lejos de Knalga debería haber desanimado a "
"Tenma, pensó Olokun, pero ella parecía muy emocionada mientras caminaba por "
"los túneles de los enanos Aurvang de los Hammermounts. Examinaba a esos "
"seres que nunca había visto antes con una curiosidad que, para muchos, sería "
"insultante, pero los enanos, como Olokun, quedaron encantados por su alegría "
"y energía. En el banquete de Augdras, ella fue la estrella de la noche, "
"cantando canciones de su pueblo a viva voz y aceptando cualquiera de los "
"desafíos de bebida que los enanos le lanzaban; tras el sexto cuenco de "
"cerveza vaciado, Augdras, con las mejillas sonrojadas, declaró que Tenma era "
"oficialmente miembro honorario de su clan."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:101
msgid ""
"In the following day, Tenma braved a dire headache to sit alongside Olokun "
"and Kenshiro to talk with Augdras. He claimed that the tunnels once "
"connecting the Hammermounts to Knalga had crumbled ages before, but that the "
"Aurvang Dwarves could give the humans some of their gryphons, which they "
"could use to quickly reach their destination."
msgstr ""
"Al día siguiente, Tenma soportó un fuerte dolor de cabeza para sentarse "
"junto a Olokun y Kenshiro a hablar con Augdras. Él afirmó que los túneles "
"que alguna vez conectaban los Hammermounts con Knalga se habían derrumbado "
"edades atrás, pero que los enanos Aurvang podían darles a los humanos "
"algunos de sus grifos, que podrían usar para llegar rápidamente a su destino."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:104
msgid ""
"The possibility of travelling by air cheered up the trio, but, in their "
"third day in the halls of the Aurvang, they saw that their departure would "
"have to be delayed..."
msgstr ""
"La posibilidad de viajar por aire animó al trío, pero en su tercer día en "
"los salones de los Aurvang vieron que su partida tendría que retrasarse…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:114
msgid ""
"The news that they were so far from Knalga should have disheartened Tenma, "
"Olokun thought, but she looked very excited as she walked through the "
"tunnels of the Drokkor Trolls of the Hammermounts. She examined those tall, "
"strong beings she'd never seen before with unabashed curiosity, but the "
"trolls didn't care, for they too stared at that tiny, delicate and energetic "
"creature with great interest. Once at Thrur's abode, the humans were tended "
"by his shamans, who also prepared them some food: cooked mushroom and "
"roasted bats, which the starving humans ate with delight and gratitude."
msgstr ""
"La noticia de que estaban tan lejos de Knalga debería haber desanimado a "
"Tenma, pensó Olokun, pero ella parecía muy emocionada mientras caminaba por "
"los túneles de los trolls Drokkor de los Hammermounts. Examinaba a esos "
"altos y fuertes seres que nunca había visto antes con una curiosidad "
"descarada, pero a los trolls no les importó, pues ellos también miraban a "
"esa criatura pequeña, delicada y energética con gran interés. Una vez en la "
"morada de Thrur, los humanos fueron atendidos por sus chamanes, quienes "
"también les prepararon comida: hongos cocidos y murciélagos asados, que los "
"humanos hambrientos comieron con deleite y gratitud."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:117
msgid ""
"After the initial amazement, Tenma found the trolls to be quite boring for "
"their silence and stoicism, but she admired them for their surprising "
"kindness. In the day after the battle, she and her friends were received by "
"Thrur to discuss how the trolls could help them. According to him, the "
"tunnels that once connected the Hammermounts to Knalga had crumbled ages "
"before, but that he could place troll warriors to escort them towards Knalga "
"and introduce them to the trolls living there."
msgstr ""
"Tras el asombro inicial, Tenma encontró a los trolls algo aburridos por su "
"silencio y estoicismo, pero los admiró por su sorprendente amabilidad. Al "
"día siguiente de la batalla, ella y sus amigos fueron recibidos por Thrur "
"para discutir cómo los trolls podían ayudarlos. Según él, los túneles que "
"alguna vez conectaban los Hammermounts con Knalga se habían derrumbado "
"edades atrás, pero él podía colocar guerreros trolls para escoltarlos hacia "
"Knalga e introducirlos a los trolls que vivían allí."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:120
msgid ""
"The possibility of travelling with strong troll fighters protecting them "
"cheered up the trio, but, in their third day in the caves of the Drokkor, "
"they saw that their departure would have to be delayed..."
msgstr ""
"La posibilidad de viajar con fuertes guerreros trolls protegiéndolos animó "
"al trío, pero en su tercer día en las cuevas de los Drokkor vieron que su "
"partida tendría que retrasarse"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:130
msgid ""
"The news that they were so far from Knalga should have disheartened Tenma, "
"Olokun thought, but she looked very excited as she walked through the "
"tunnels of the Black Elves of the Hammermounts. She examined those strong, "
"yet beautiful beings she'd never seen before with a curiosity that annoyed "
"them a little – except for Svaryarna, who returned the intensity of her "
"stares in kind. At the eerily beautiful abode of the black elves, the humans "
"were, as promised, treated and served by pale and delicate maids; to Tenma's "
"slight disappointment, the warriors refused to play serving roles."
msgstr ""
"La noticia de que estaban tan lejos de Knalga debería haber desanimado a "
"Tenma, pensó Olokun, pero ella parecía muy emocionada mientras caminaba por "
"los túneles de los elfos negros de los Hammermounts. Examinaba a esos seres "
"fuertes pero hermosos que nunca había visto antes con una curiosidad que los "
"molestaba un poco —excepto a Svaryarna, quien devolvía la intensidad de sus "
"miradas con la misma fuerza. En la morada inquietantemente bella de los "
"elfos negros, los humanos fueron, como se prometió, atendidos y servidos por "
"doncellas pálidas y delicadas; para leve decepción de Tenma, los guerreros "
"se negaron a desempeñar roles de servicio."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:133
msgid ""
"After resting amidst the smoothest silky beds they'd ever laid on, the three "
"humans met Svaryarna at her hall to discuss how the black elves could repay "
"their aid. She told them that the tunnels once connecting the Hammermounts "
"to Knalga had long crumbled, but that they could easily reach those "
"mountains through the elvish forests on the way; though the black elves had "
"long ceased communicating with their cousins in the Lins-Elens, the King-in-"
"the-Woods, as the supreme elven lord was called, would never refuse a "
"request from any friendly elf, and so he'd let them through his lands if "
"they showed him her Fey Laurel."
msgstr ""
"Tras descansar en las camas de seda más suaves en las que jamás habían "
"dormido, los tres humanos se reunieron con Svaryarna en su salón para "
"discutir cómo los elfos negros podían pagar su ayuda. Ella les dijo que los "
"túneles que alguna vez conectaban los Hammermounts con Knalga se habían "
"derrumbado hacía mucho, pero que podían llegar fácilmente a esas montañas a "
"través de los bosques élficos en el camino; aunque los elfos negros habían "
"dejado de comunicarse con sus primos en los Lins-Elens hacía tiempo, el Rey-"
"en-el-Bosque, como se llamaba al señor élfico supremo, nunca rechazaría una "
"petición de cualquier elfo amistoso, y por lo tanto les dejaría pasar por "
"sus tierras si le mostraban su Laurel Feérico."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:136
msgid ""
"The possibility of travelling through friendly territory cheered up the "
"trio, but, in their third day in the dwelling of the black elves, they saw "
"that their departure would have to be delayed..."
msgstr ""
"La posibilidad de viajar por territorio amistoso animó al trío, pero en su "
"tercer día en la morada de los elfos negros vieron que su partida tendría "
"que retrasarse"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:146
msgid ""
"To Tenma's relief, the leaders of the trolls, the dwarves and the black "
"elves accepted attending the meeting without complaints, but allying with "
"each other, even against a common and very dangerous foe, was another "
"matter. In fact, the meeting would have totally spiralled out of control if "
"Tenma, worried about Olokun, hadn't lost her patience and taken control over "
"the situation by way of screaming and lambasting the cave dwellers for their "
"lack of pragmatism. After venting her frustration, she feared that they "
"would get mad at her, but surprisingly they accepted her lecture humbly, and "
"recognized that they should unite to fight the undead."
msgstr ""
"Para alivio de Tenma, los líderes de los trolls, los enanos y los elfos "
"negros aceptaron asistir a la reunión sin quejas, pero aliarse entre sí, "
"incluso contra un enemigo común y muy peligroso, era otro asunto. De hecho, "
"la reunión habría salido completamente de control si Tenma, preocupada por "
"Olokun, no hubiera perdido la paciencia y tomado el control de la situación "
"gritando y reprendiendo a los habitantes de las cuevas por su falta de "
"pragmatismo. Tras desahogar su frustración, temió que se enfadaran con ella, "
"pero sorprendentemente aceptaron su sermón con humildad y reconocieron que "
"debían unirse para luchar contra los no-muertos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:150
msgid ""
"In the end, a year-long truce was signed, and each faction swore to send the "
"strongest military contingent they could mass. Two days later, Tenma and "
"Kenshiro followed Svaryarna, Thrur and Augdras towards the Deep Valley; "
"Olokun was well, for the undead hadn't attacked during that time. Thus, the "
"unlikely allies descended into the so-called Lost Caves, a network of "
"tunnels long abandoned by all living denizens of the Hammermounts..."
msgstr ""
"Al final, se firmó una tregua de un año, y cada facción juró enviar el "
"contingente militar más fuerte que pudieran reunir. Dos días después, Tenma "
"y Kenshiro siguieron a Svaryarna, Thrur y Augdras hacia el Valle Profundo; "
"Olokun estaba bien, pues los no-muertos no habían atacado durante ese "
"tiempo. Así, los improbables aliados descendieron a las llamadas Cuevas "
"Perdidas, una red de túneles abandonada desde hacía mucho por todos los "
"habitantes vivos de los Hammermounts…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Thus the three friends left the Hammermounts. Although that unexpected "
"underground war had cost them an entire month, Tenma was glad for having "
"saved the Hammermounts' inhabitants from Ashura, and also with the thought "
"that they might finally get along with each other after fighting together."
msgstr ""
"Así los tres amigos dejaron los Hammermounts. Aunque aquella inesperada "
"guerra subterránea les había costado un mes entero, Tenma estaba contenta "
"por haber salvado a los habitantes de los Hammermounts de Ashura, y también "
"con la idea de que tal vez finalmente pudieran llevarse bien entre sí "
"después de luchar juntos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:165
msgid ""
"They travelled across the vast, green and silent meadows of the Great "
"Continent's centre-north more swiftly than before, now that they were "
"accompanied by new allies and with their provisions full, which made hunting "
"redundant and consequently saved them much time."
msgstr ""
"Viajaron a través de las vastas praderas verdes y silenciosas del centro-"
"norte del Gran Continente más rápido que antes, ahora acompañados por nuevos "
"aliados y con sus provisiones llenas, lo que hacía innecesaria la caza y por "
"lo tanto les ahorraba mucho tiempo."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:169
msgid ""
"In the thirtieth day since their departure from the Hammermounts, though, "
"Kenshiro claimed that he sensed someone following them. Olokun didn't take "
"that very seriously, for the razorbirds he sent scouting the region returned "
"with no news, but Tenma trusted his warrior's sense – and, as they entered a "
"vast swampy region bordered to the south by a distant mountain range, she "
"saw that she was right in doing so..."
msgstr ""
"En el trigésimo día desde su partida de los Hammermounts, sin embargo, "
"Kenshiro afirmó que sentía que alguien los seguía. Olokun no lo tomó muy en "
"serio, pues las aves navaja que envió a explorar la región regresaron sin "
"noticias, pero Tenma confió en el sentido guerrero de él —y, al entrar en "
"una vasta región pantanosa bordeada al sur por una lejana cordillera, vio "
"que tenía razón al hacerlo"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:174
msgid "Part VIII: An Irdyan Odyssey"
msgstr "Parte VIII: Una Odisea Irdiana"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:178
msgid "The Second Dragon War"
msgstr "La Segunda Guerra de los Dragones"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:188
msgid ""
"The crossing of the swamp was uneventful after that battle, and so they "
"reached the Emerald Plains without further incident. That region, which "
"Kenshiro identified after what he'd heard from Wesnothians, was a vast and "
"chilly meadow covered by an intensely green grass, and fuller with wild life "
"than the places the trio had visited up till then. Also according to "
"Kenshiro, those lands were inhabited by a very belligerent people known as "
"Baryags, who were constantly at odds with the Wesnothian Empire. Tenma "
"wondered whether they'd be welcomed there, since they too were enemies to "
"Wesnoth, but the Baryags wouldn't see the enemies of their enemies as "
"friends..."
msgstr ""
"El cruce del pantano fue sin incidentes tras aquella batalla, y así llegaron "
"a las Llanuras Esmeralda sin más problemas. Esa región, que Kenshiro "
"identificó por lo que había oído de los wesnothianos, era una vasta y fría "
"pradera cubierta por una hierba intensamente verde, y más llena de vida "
"salvaje que los lugares que el trío había visitado hasta entonces. También "
"según Kenshiro, esas tierras estaban habitadas por un pueblo muy beligerante "
"conocido como Baryags, que estaban constantemente en desacuerdo con el "
"Imperio Wesnothiano. Tenma se preguntó si serían bienvenidos allí, ya que "
"también eran enemigos de Wesnoth, pero los Baryags no verían a los enemigos "
"de sus enemigos como amigos"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:199
msgid ""
"The three friends rested at Yevan for a night only – or so did Olokun and "
"Kenshiro, for Tenma spent most of the night at Raskol's hall, drinking and "
"partying with his warriors as if she was one of them; after all, the Baryags "
"could look ruthless and hostile at first sight, but to friends they were "
"quite merry. In the following morning, Olokun had to summon an elemental to "
"carry Tenma as they resumed travelling, for she was simply exhausted."
msgstr ""
"Los tres amigos descansaron en Yevan solo una noche —o al menos lo hicieron "
"Olokun y Kenshiro, pues Tenma pasó la mayor parte de la noche en el salón de "
"Raskol, bebiendo y festejando con sus guerreros como si fuera una de ellos; "
"después de todo, los Baryags podían parecer despiadados y hostiles a primera "
"vista, pero con los amigos eran bastante alegres. A la mañana siguiente, "
"Olokun tuvo que invocar un elemental para llevar a Tenma mientras reanudaban "
"el viaje, pues ella estaba simplemente exhausta."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:203
msgid ""
"That was the smoothest part of the journey: the Emerald Plains were crossed "
"by many roads, there were many inns where the travellers could replenish "
"their provisions and, thanks to the Blue Laurel banner given them by Raskol, "
"they weren't harassed by anyone. Even Olokun was surprised at how organised "
"the region seemed to be; according to the owner of an inn where they slept "
"for a night, that was all the work of Dragana Vasilya, their warrior queen, "
"who had managed to unite and pacify the many Baryag clans through sword and "
"cunning."
msgstr ""
"Esa fue la parte más tranquila del viaje: las Llanuras Esmeralda estaban "
"cruzadas por muchos caminos, había muchas posadas donde los viajeros podían "
"reponer sus provisiones y, gracias al estandarte del Laurel Azul que les dio "
"Raskol, no fueron molestados por nadie. Incluso Olokun se sorprendió de lo "
"organizada que parecía la región; según el dueño de una posada donde "
"durmieron una noche, todo eso era obra de Dragana Vasilya, su reina "
"guerrera, que había logrado unir y pacificar a los muchos clanes baryag con "
"espada y astucia."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:207
msgid ""
"So impressed and curious about the Baryags were the friends that they "
"decided to take a small detour and go to Mhreghost, the greatest city in the "
"Emerald Plains. Once there, they were not left disappointed: Mhreghost was a "
"huge, beautiful and well-organized city, full of trees and people. Tenma "
"even saw an elf or two and a group of dwarves there, all merchants from "
"outside the plains. She was the most impressed of the trio, for she'd never "
"seen such a large human city before, and she didn't stop looking around, "
"trying to catch every single detail visible to her."
msgstr ""
"Tan impresionados y curiosos quedaron los amigos con los Baryags que "
"decidieron tomar un pequeño desvío y ir a Mhreghost, la mayor ciudad de las "
"Llanuras Esmeralda. Una vez allí, no quedaron decepcionados: Mhreghost era "
"una ciudad enorme, hermosa y bien organizada, llena de árboles y gente. "
"Tenma incluso vio uno o dos elfos y un grupo de enanos allí, todos "
"mercaderes de fuera de las llanuras. Ella fue la más impresionada del trío, "
"pues nunca había visto una ciudad humana tan grande, y no dejó de mirar "
"alrededor, intentando captar cada detalle visible para ella."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Their stay at Mhreghost would have possibly been the most pleasant moment of "
"their journey, were it not for the sighting of an enemy approaching the "
"city..."
msgstr ""
"Su estancia en Mhreghost posiblemente habría sido el momento más agradable "
"de su viaje, de no ser por la visión de un enemigo acercándose a la ciudad…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:222
msgid ""
"It sure was a violent world, Tenma thought as she, Olokun and Kenshiro rode "
"southwards across the Emerald Plains, witnessing the movement of Baryag "
"troops from town to town; she'd been forced out of her homeland by an enemy "
"military attack, got involved in an underground war, and now she was on her "
"way to yet another war..."
msgstr ""
"Seguro que era un mundo violento, pensó Tenma mientras ella, Olokun y "
"Kenshiro cabalgaban hacia el sur a través de las Llanuras Esmeralda, "
"observando el movimiento de tropas baryag de pueblo en pueblo; había sido "
"obligada a salir de su patria por un ataque militar enemigo, se había "
"involucrado en una guerra subterránea, y ahora iba camino a otra guerra más"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:226
msgid ""
"On the path to the Lins-Elens, they met Baryag messengers who informed them "
"of the many clashes already soaking the eastern plains in blood. The Baryags "
"were having trouble withstanding the spirited and furious drake offensive; "
"many smaller towns had fallen already, prompting Dragana to try and get the "
"Aragwaithi of the north to help her people in the war."
msgstr ""
"En el camino hacia los Lins-Elens, se encontraron con mensajeros baryag que "
"les informaron de los muchos choques que ya estaban empapando las llanuras "
"orientales en sangre. Los Baryags tenían problemas para resistir la ofensiva "
"enérgica y furiosa de los dracos; muchas ciudades pequeñas ya habían caído, "
"lo que llevó a Dragana a intentar conseguir que los aragwaithi del norte "
"ayudaran a su pueblo en la guerra."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:230
msgid ""
"This only motivated Tenma to hurry up towards the elven capital. Following "
"Dragana's advice, she and her friends searched for a deep rift amidst a "
"cluster of hills separating the plains and the Lins-Elens. The passage led "
"them to a vast flowery field framed by tall trees and lofty green walls; "
"before them, they saw a pair of towering gates guarded by powerful elf "
"warriors. To the humans' surprise, the elves let them inside their land as "
"soon as they claimed to have been sent by Dragana; as they followed the road "
"known as the Elven Path deep into the Lins-Elens, the trio understood why "
"they were so welcomed there..."
msgstr ""
"Esto solo motivó a Tenma a apresurarse hacia la capital élfica. Siguiendo el "
"consejo de Dragana, ella y sus amigos buscaron una profunda grieta entre un "
"grupo de colinas que separaba las llanuras de los Lins-Elens. El pasaje los "
"llevó a un vasto campo florido enmarcado por árboles altos y elevados muros "
"verdes; ante ellos vieron un par de puertas imponentes custodiadas por "
"poderosos guerreros elfos. Para sorpresa de los humanos, los elfos les "
"permitieron entrar en su tierra tan pronto como afirmaron haber sido "
"enviados por Dragana; mientras seguían el camino conocido como el Sendero "
"Élfico hacia el interior de los Lins-Elens, el trío entendió por qué eran "
"tan bienvenidos allí"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:241
msgid ""
"Tenma used to think the forests surrounding her village of Kuroi beautiful, "
"but they utterly paled before those where the greatest of all elvish "
"kingdoms flourished. The trees seemed to reach into the very skies, their "
"trunks covered in velvet-like moss and bright flowers, their leaves silvery-"
"green; and the ground was fluffy with flowerbeds and leaf litters, lit here "
"and there by the sun rays which crossed the high canopy and gave everything "
"a sleepy golden tint. At night, mists creeped around the trees, glowing "
"silver under the moonlight as the night's breeze ruffled the high canopy, "
"making the whole forest echo with the song of leaves."
msgstr ""
"Tenma solía pensar que los bosques que rodeaban su aldea de Kuroi eran "
"hermosos, pero palidecían totalmente ante aquellos donde florecía el mayor "
"de todos los reinos élficos. Los árboles parecían alcanzar los mismos "
"cielos, sus troncos cubiertos de musgo aterciopelado y flores brillantes, "
"sus hojas verde plateado; y el suelo era esponjoso con parterres de flores y "
"hojarasca, iluminado aquí y allá por los rayos de sol que cruzaban el alto "
"dosel y daban a todo un tinte dorado somnoliento. De noche, las nieblas se "
"arrastraban alrededor de los árboles, brillando plateadas bajo la luz de la "
"luna mientras la brisa nocturna agitaba el alto dosel, haciendo que todo el "
"bosque resonara con la canción de las hojas."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:245
msgid ""
"Riding swift horses trained for the forest ground, the trio reached the "
"elvish capital a day after entering the Lins-Elens. Metheldur was as "
"magnificent as they could have expected: surrounded by lofty walls, full of "
"beautifully designed elvish buildings and embellished by flowery fields and "
"singing fountains. As she marvelled at all those beauties, however, Tenma "
"couldn't avoid resenting the elves' looks of superiority, to the point that "
"the city itself lost much of its shine to her."
msgstr ""
"Cabalgando veloces caballos entrenados para el suelo del bosque, el trío "
"llegó a la capital élfica un día después de entrar en los Lins-Elens. "
"Metheldur era tan magnífica como podían esperar: rodeada de elevadas "
"murallas, llena de edificios élficos bellamente diseñados y embellecida por "
"campos floridos y fuentes cantantes. Sin embargo, mientras se maravillaba "
"con todas esas bellezas, Tenma no podía evitar resentir las miradas de "
"superioridad de los elfos, al punto que la ciudad misma perdió mucho de su "
"brillo para ella."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:249
msgid ""
"Greeted by slightly suspicious guards, Olokun requested an audience with Gil-"
"Thelyon; only in the following day the humans received permission to speak "
"with the King-in-the-Woods, the highest of all elven lords on the world. As "
"she crossed the tall archway leading into his palace, Tenma wondered whether "
"he would be the most arrogant of all the elves, but she was surprised by "
"what she saw..."
msgstr ""
"Recibidos por guardias ligeramente desconfiados, Olokun solicitó audiencia "
"con Gil-Thelyon; solo al día siguiente los humanos recibieron permiso para "
"hablar con el Rey-en-el-Bosque, el más alto de todos los señores élficos del "
"mundo. Mientras cruzaba el alto arco que llevaba a su palacio, Tenma se "
"preguntó si sería el más arrogante de todos los elfos, pero se sorprendió "
"por lo que vio…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:260
msgid ""
"Thus they went on southwards through the vast Lins-Elens, bound for the "
"Firecloud Peak. Elvish sentries guided the travellers along the way, though "
"the volcano itself was easy to find, as they only needed to follow the black "
"smoke column rising seemingly perennially from the southern horizon."
msgstr ""
"Así continuaron hacia el sur a través del vasto Lins-Elens, rumbo al Pico "
"Nube de Fuego. Centinelas élficos guiaron a los viajeros por el camino, "
"aunque el volcán mismo era fácil de encontrar, pues solo necesitaban seguir "
"la columna de humo negro que parecía elevarse perennemente desde el "
"horizonte sur."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:264
msgid ""
"The trio was also careful not to stumble on Cornelya's warrior band, sending "
"out forest elementals and razorbirds to scout the way ahead. Tenma didn't "
"believe that a small group of elf warriors could threaten them so much, but "
"Olokun reminded her that, in such a dense, vast forest, a single elf archer "
"could be a deadly threat."
msgstr ""
"El trío también tuvo cuidado de no toparse con la banda guerrera de "
"Cornelya, enviando elementales del bosque y aves navaja a explorar el camino "
"por delante. Tenma no creía que un pequeño grupo de guerreros elfos pudiera "
"amenazarlos tanto, pero Olokun le recordó que, en un bosque tan denso y "
"vasto, un solo arquero elfo podía ser una amenaza mortal."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:268
msgid "And he was right, even more than he would have wanted to be..."
msgstr "Y tenía razón, incluso más de lo que habría querido…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:279
msgid ""
"It was strange to have different company after travelling with only the two "
"men for so long, or so Tenma thought – especially considering that the "
"'different company' was a sullen elf princess whose very glares seemed "
"capable of murdering them. Her demeanour wasn't merely willful annoyance, it "
"was pure, genuine hatred. She refused any food or water offered her; in "
"fact, she'd have starved to death in those days, hadn't Olokun found a way "
"of giving her food without letting her know it was him."
msgstr ""
"Era extraño tener compañía diferente después de viajar tanto tiempo solo con "
"los dos hombres, pensó Tenma —especialmente considerando que la «compañía "
"diferente» era una princesa elfa hosca cuyas miradas parecían capaces de "
"asesinarlos. Su actitud no era mera molestia voluntariosa, era odio puro y "
"genuino. Rechazaba cualquier comida o agua que le ofrecieran; de hecho, "
"habría muerto de hambre en esos días si Olokun no hubiera encontrado una "
"forma de darle comida sin que ella supiera que era él."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:283
msgid ""
"As they left the Lins-Elens, the group entered a region rich in hills and "
"poor in greenery; only a few sparse trees and clusters of bushes broke the "
"brownish-greyness of the so-called Fire Hills. The few human settlements "
"spotted were avoided. Then, three days after leaving the forest, they "
"finally sighted the ever active volcano towering before them, breathing "
"columns of dark smoke that covered the entire region, plunging it into "
"darkness even though it was daytime..."
msgstr ""
"Al dejar los Lins-Elens, el grupo entró en una región rica en colinas y "
"pobre en vegetación; solo unos pocos árboles dispersos y grupos de arbustos "
"rompían el grisáceo-marrón de las llamadas Colinas de Fuego. Los pocos "
"asentamientos humanos avistados fueron evitados. Entonces, tres días después "
"de dejar el bosque, finalmente divisaron el volcán siempre activo elevándose "
"ante ellos, respirando columnas de humo oscuro que cubrían toda la región, "
"sumiéndola en oscuridad aunque fuera de día…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:294
msgid ""
"Veshtar Joohn indeed received them all in her citadel, a huge fortress built "
"with stone slabs that even trolls would have trouble moving. The Mother "
"Queen herself was a massive drake; so massive, in fact, that for a moment "
"Tenma thought she was an actual dragon."
msgstr ""
"Veshtar Joohn efectivamente los recibió a todos en su ciudadela, una enorme "
"fortaleza construida con losas de piedra que incluso los trolls tendrían "
"problemas para mover. La propia Reina Madre era un draco masivo; tan masivo, "
"de hecho, que por un momento Tenma pensó que era un verdadero dragón."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:297
msgid ""
"Veshtar welcomed the idea of fighting Vladnir Ohn – who, she said, had never "
"respected her clan, which he scornfully called 'breeders' –, but convincing "
"her to side with Baryags and elves was a much harder matter. In the end, she "
"agreed that she didn't need go to their aid, but that she'd still fight her "
"brother."
msgstr ""
"Veshtar acogió con agrado la idea de luchar contra Vladnir Ohn —quien, según "
"dijo, nunca había respetado a su clan, al que desdeñosamente llamaba "
"«criadores»—, pero convencerla de ponerse del lado de los baryags y los "
"elfos fue un asunto mucho más difícil. Al final, aceptó que no necesitaba ir "
"en su ayuda, pero que aún lucharía contra su hermano."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:300
msgid ""
"And she wasted no time before making her move, sending no less than four "
"large battalions towards the Kehshakaar. Tenma, Olokun, Kenshiro, Valerya "
"and Cornelya followed one which went around the southern Kehshakaar; they "
"didn't like those uncoordinated attacks, but that was better than nothing – "
"something they could see for themselves as they reached the Peaceful Plains, "
"a region bordering the lands of the elves, the Baryags and the Kehshakaar "
"Drakes..."
msgstr ""
"Y no perdió tiempo antes de hacer su movimiento, enviando no menos de cuatro "
"grandes batallones hacia el Kehshakaar. Tenma, Olokun, Kenshiro, Valerya y "
"Cornelya siguieron a uno que rodeaba el Kehshakaar sur; no les gustaban esos "
"ataques descoordinados, pero era mejor que nada —algo que pudieron comprobar "
"por sí mismos al llegar a las Llanuras Pacíficas, una región que limitaba "
"con las tierras de los elfos, los Baryags y los Dracos Kehshakaar"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:310
msgid ""
"Veshtar Joohn's drakes and Gelendras's elves decisively pushed Vladnir Ohn's "
"armies out of both the Lins-Elens and the Shakaar Mountains, thus "
"encroaching upon the Kehshakaar. But Tenma's group returned to the Emerald "
"Plains and met Dragana at the city of Argorod, which had been retaken so "
"recently its stone buildings were still warm with drake fire. When queried "
"on the subject, the queen said that she'd fought drake undead twice already, "
"though they weren't unlike the ones faced by the travellers."
msgstr ""
"Los dracos de Veshtar Joohn y los elfos de Gelendras empujaron decisivamente "
"a los ejércitos de Vladnir Ohn fuera tanto de los Lins-Elens como de las "
"Montañas Shakaar, así invadiendo el Kehshakaar. Pero el grupo de Tenma "
"regresó a las Llanuras Esmeralda y se reunió con Dragana en la ciudad de "
"Argorod, que había sido retomada tan recientemente que sus edificios de "
"piedra aún estaban calientes con fuego de draco. Cuando le preguntaron al "
"respecto, la reina dijo que ya había luchado contra dracos no-muertos dos "
"veces, aunque no eran distintos de los que enfrentaron los viajeros."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:314
msgid ""
"After being joined by the foreigners, the Baryag army won a streak of "
"crushing victories – in no small part thanks to Valerya, whose knowledge of "
"drake weaknesses was as invaluable as her strength and invulnerability to "
"drake fire. Not only that, but she had a charisma which motivated even the "
"Baryags, to whom she was unknown. As she said after another crushing "
"victory, she'd inherited that from her parents, Addraryn and Elyniver, both "
"of whom had been Wesnothian heroes."
msgstr ""
"Tras ser unidos por los extranjeros, el ejército baryag ganó una racha de "
"victorias aplastantes —en gran parte gracias a Valerya, cuyo conocimiento de "
"las debilidades de los dracos era tan invaluable como su fuerza e "
"invulnerabilidad al fuego de draco. No solo eso, sino que tenía un carisma "
"que motivaba incluso a los Baryags, a quienes era desconocida. Como dijo "
"tras otra victoria aplastante, lo había heredado de sus padres, Addraryn y "
"Elyniver, ambos héroes wesnothianos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:318
msgid ""
"The drakes, seeing themselves vulnerable on the plains and cornered by "
"humans, elves and other drakes, retreated into the Kehshakaar, their foes on "
"their heels. Finally, the armies of Dragana, Gelendras and Veshtar Joohn – "
"who decided to personally lead her warriors in the last battle – met at the "
"chain of volcanoes which comprised Shek'harya, Vladnir Ohn's citadel. The "
"drake lord himself stood atop his highest tower, so large that he could "
"easily be mistaken by a true dragon; next to him, stood a smaller, though "
"not less threatening, enemy..."
msgstr ""
"Los dracos, viéndose vulnerables en las llanuras y acorralados por humanos, "
"elfos y otros dracos, se retiraron hacia Kehshakaar, con sus enemigos "
"pisándoles los talones. Finalmente, los ejércitos de Dragana, Gelendras y "
"Veshtar Joohn —quien decidió liderar personalmente a sus guerreras en la "
"batalla final— se encontraron en la cadena de volcanes que conformaba "
"Shek'harya, la ciudadela de Vladnir Ohn. El mismo señor draco se encontraba "
"en lo alto de su torre más elevada, tan grande que fácilmente podía "
"confundirse con un verdadero dragón; a su lado estaba un enemigo más "
"pequeño, aunque no menos amenazante..."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:329
msgid ""
"And so the travellers left the Emerald Plains, their group larger than when "
"they had entered that region, and with one of the last people they'd expect "
"as company. Aetheryon spoke only what was needed, and remained at his corner "
"of the camp for most of the time. The others were courteous enough with him "
"– except for Tenma and Donar, both of whom made no point of showing the "
"Wesnothian prince a sliver of politeness."
msgstr ""
"Y así los viajeros dejaron las Llanuras Esmeralda, con su grupo más grande "
"que cuando habían entrado en esa región, y con una de las últimas personas "
"que esperarían como compañía. Aetheryon hablaba solo lo necesario y "
"permanecía en su rincón del campamento la mayor parte del tiempo. Los demás "
"fueron lo suficientemente corteses con él —excepto Tenma y Donar, quienes no "
"se esforzaron en absoluto por mostrarle al príncipe wesnothiano ni un ápice "
"de cortesía."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:333
msgid ""
"After a mere four days travelling along ample roads and through the Lintanir "
"Forest – the westernmost region of the Lins-Elens –, they reached a vast, "
"cold meadow bordered to the west and the south by towering, snow-capped blue "
"mountains; as Valerya proudly announced, they had just entered the "
"Northlands."
msgstr ""
"Tras solo cuatro días viajando por amplios caminos y a través del Bosque "
"Lintanir —la región más occidental de los Lins-Elens—, llegaron a una vasta "
"pradera fría bordeada al oeste y al sur por imponentes montañas azules "
"cubiertas de nieve; como Valerya anunció con orgullo, acababan de entrar en "
"las Tierras del Norte."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:337
msgid ""
"Aetheryon suggested taking the nearby Northern Route, which would lead them "
"to Dorest, capital of Wesnoth's northern provinces. Promising everyone haven "
"in the city, he argued that from Dorest he could muster troops to join the "
"fight against Aelvar. Tenma, Kenshiro and Donar were strongly against the "
"idea, until Valerya claimed to have a Staff of Righteous Flame, which causes "
"great destruction if shattered. With this safeguard against any possible "
"Wesnothian treachery, the group took the Northern Route, now led by "
"Aetheryon."
msgstr ""
"Aetheryon sugirió tomar la Ruta Norte cercana, que los llevaría a Dorest, "
"capital de las provincias norteñas de Wesnoth. Prometiendo refugio a todos "
"en la ciudad, argumentó que desde Dorest podría reunir tropas para unirse a "
"la lucha contra Aelvar. Tenma, Kenshiro y Donar se opusieron firmemente a la "
"idea, hasta que Valerya afirmó tener un Bastón de Llama Justa, que causa "
"gran destrucción si se rompe. Con esta salvaguarda contra cualquier posible "
"traición wesnothiana, el grupo tomó la Ruta Norte, ahora liderado por "
"Aetheryon."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:341
msgid ""
"After passing by many Wesnothian sentries along the road, they finally "
"sighted the walled city of Dorest – and with the sight came an all-too-"
"familiar sound of swords clashing and war cries..."
msgstr ""
"Tras pasar por muchos centinelas wesnothianos a lo largo del camino, "
"finalmente avistaron la ciudad amurallada de Dorest —y con la vista llegó un "
"sonido demasiado familiar de espadas chocando y gritos de guerra…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:346
msgid "The Far North"
msgstr "El Lejano Norte"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Tenma wasn't easily disarmed, but Aethra's hospitality caught her off guard. "
"The Wesnothian princess seemed oblivious to the differences in their social "
"standings, and treated all her guests with the warmth of an old friend. So "
"genuine was her kindness that Tenma even went easy on Aetheryon - who "
"nevertheless didn't shy from admitting his role in the Second Dragon War. "
"Aethra's reaction was one of resigned disappointment; it seemed she was used "
"to the ways of the Iron Dynasty, distasteful as she might find them."
msgstr ""
"Tenma no se desarmaba fácilmente, pero la hospitalidad de Aethra la tomó por "
"sorpresa. La princesa wesnothiana parecía ignorar las diferencias en sus "
"posiciones sociales y trataba a todos sus invitados con el calor de una "
"vieja amiga. Tan genuina era su amabilidad que Tenma incluso fue indulgente "
"con Aetheryon —quien, sin embargo, no evitó admitir su papel en la Segunda "
"Guerra de los Dragones. La reacción de Aethra fue de decepción resignada; "
"parecía estar acostumbrada a las costumbres de la Dinastía de Hierro, por "
"más desagradables que le parecieran."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:360
msgid ""
"After the introductions, Aetheryon and Donar explained that Queen Dragana of "
"the Baryags was interested in helping the Northern Alliance and Wesnoth "
"against Aelvar; Aeldhoryan was pleased by that, and assured everyone that "
"his father would accept the alliance, as Aelvar now was Wesnoth's foe as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Tras las presentaciones, Aetheryon y Donar explicaron que la reina Dragana "
"de los Baryags estaba interesada en ayudar a la Alianza del Norte y a "
"Wesnoth contra Aelvar; Aeldhoryan se mostró complacido por ello y aseguró a "
"todos que su padre aceptaría la alianza, ya que Aelvar ahora también era "
"enemigo de Wesnoth."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:364
msgid ""
"Afterwards, Aethra told of how the rebels had come from River Bork in many "
"ships; as Aelvar's main fortress stood on the farthest northern shores, "
"between the Frosty Wastes and the Black Marshes, it was agreed that the "
"rebels had established a foothold in the Mountains of Haag, which gave them "
"a huge tactical advantage. Donar suggested attacking the range to expel "
"Aelvar's forces from there, but Valerya advised him to wait until the "
"alliance between Wesnothians, northerners and Baryags was cemented before "
"attacking."
msgstr ""
"Después, Aethra contó cómo los rebeldes habían llegado desde el río Bork en "
"muchos barcos; como la principal fortaleza de Aelvar se encontraba en las "
"costas más septentrionales, entre los Yermos Helados y los Pantanos Negros, "
"se acordó que los rebeldes habían establecido una cabeza de puente en las "
"Montañas de Haag, lo que les daba una enorme ventaja táctica. Donar sugirió "
"atacar la cordillera para expulsar de allí a las fuerzas de Aelvar, pero "
"Valerya le aconsejó esperar hasta que la alianza entre wesnothianos, "
"norteños y baryags estuviera consolidada antes de atacar."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:368
msgid ""
"While swift messengers ran the Northlands, the travellers rested in Dorest. "
"Tenma was surprised to find herself so at ease among Wesnothians - although, "
"as Valerya was quick to point out, Dorest's people were a mix of Wesnothians "
"and Northerners, the latter of whom was famously sympathetic to any culture "
"under imperial oppression."
msgstr ""
"Mientras mensajeros veloces recorrían las Tierras del Norte, los viajeros "
"descansaron en Dorest. Tenma se sorprendió al encontrarse tan a gusto entre "
"wesnothianos —aunque, como Valerya señaló rápidamente, la gente de Dorest "
"era una mezcla de wesnothianos y norteños, estos últimos famosos por su "
"simpatía hacia cualquier cultura bajo opresión imperial."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:372
msgid ""
"Aethra herself seemed more Northerner than Wesnothian in that regard: she "
"kept Tenma company, making sure the imperial soldiers treated her and her "
"companions well; at the slightest hint that they insulted her guests, she "
"showed just how much of an Iron princess she could be. Aetheryon too "
"experienced her anger, and was made to compensate for everything bad he'd "
"done Tenma in all the ways Aethra knew how... which wasn't to say much, as "
"the very concept of inflicting cruelty seemed to escape her understanding. "
"Still, watching Aetheryon meekly bow to his twin's innocent fury amused "
"Tenma more than she cared to admit... and, before she could stop herself, "
"she began to look at him not as a power-hungry, scheming Wesnothian prince, "
"but as a young man who'd rather play with his sister than fulfil the heavy "
"expectations placed upon him."
msgstr ""
"La propia Aethra parecía más norteña que wesnothiana en ese aspecto: mantuvo "
"compañía a Tenma, asegurándose de que los soldados imperiales la trataran "
"bien a ella y a sus compañeros; ante la más mínima insinuación de que "
"insultaran a sus invitados, mostraba cuán princesa de Hierro podía llegar a "
"ser. Aetheryon también experimentó su ira y fue obligado a compensar todo lo "
"malo que había hecho a Tenma de todas las formas que Aethra conocía… lo cual "
"no era mucho, ya que el mismo concepto de infligir crueldad parecía "
"escapársele. Aun así, ver a Aetheryon inclinarse mansamente ante la furia "
"inocente de su gemela divertía a Tenma más de lo que quería admitir… y, "
"antes de poder detenerse, comenzó a mirarlo no como a un príncipe "
"wesnothiano hambriento de poder y conspirador, sino como a un joven que "
"prefería jugar con su hermana antes que cumplir las pesadas expectativas "
"puestas sobre él."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:376
msgid ""
"Two weeks later, Dorest received ambassadors of the Northern Alliance, the "
"Greenwood Elves and the Baryags – Barag Gór, the Forest of Thelien and Jotha "
"had opted to ignore the invitation. With the unlikely alliance formalised, "
"they discussed strategy; since Aelvar's ultimate goal was Knalga, the allies "
"agreed to concentrate their defences on Prestim, Bitok (two orcish cities "
"under the Northern Alliance) and Dverheim in the Mountains of Dorth; the "
"mighty port of Tirigaz belonged to Aelvar, but any sea move he made would be "
"opposed by the mermen of Jotha, who ruled the waters that washed the Far "
"North's western shores."
msgstr ""
"Dos semanas después, Dorest recibió embajadores de la Alianza del Norte, los "
"Elfos del Bosque Verde y los Baryags —Barag Gór, el Bosque de Thelien y "
"Jotha habían optado por ignorar la invitación. Con la improbable alianza "
"formalizada, discutieron estrategia; dado que el objetivo final de Aelvar "
"era Knalga, los aliados acordaron concentrar sus defensas en Prestim, Bitok "
"(dos ciudades orcas bajo la Alianza del Norte) y Dverheim en las Montañas de "
"Dorth; el poderoso puerto de Tirigaz pertenecía a Aelvar, pero cualquier "
"movimiento marítimo que hiciera sería opuesto por los sirénidos de Jotha, "
"que dominaban las aguas que bañaban las costas occidentales del Lejano Norte."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:380
msgid ""
"The key in both Aelvar's and the alliance's strategy was, thus, River Bork, "
"which ran from the Mountains of Haag to the Heart Mountains –  and, thus, "
"Knalga; if the rebels sailed it freely – and the Northerners had no navy to "
"oppose Aelvar's ships – the allies' land defences would be meaningless. "
"Donar then repeated his plan of attacking the Mountains of Haag; Aetheryon "
"decided to follow him with a Wesnothian battalion, and soon Olokun and Tenma "
"pledged themselves to go as well."
msgstr ""
"La clave en la estrategia tanto de Aelvar como de la alianza era, por lo "
"tanto, el río Bork, que corría desde las Montañas de Haag hasta las Montañas "
"del Corazón —y, por ende, hasta Knalga; si los rebeldes navegaban libremente "
"por él —y los norteños no tenían marina para oponerse a los barcos de Aelvar"
"— las defensas terrestres de los aliados serían inútiles. Donar repitió "
"entonces su plan de atacar las Montañas de Haag; Aetheryon decidió seguirlo "
"con un batallón wesnothiano, y pronto Olokun y Tenma se comprometieron a ir "
"también."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:384
msgid ""
"And so they left Dorest in the following day; after crossing River Bork, "
"they went through a narrow meadow between the Desert of Death and the Silent "
"Forest, two dreaded regions. After meeting – and destroying – a few rebel "
"outpost, they reached the Mountains of Haag; once there, finding Aelvar's "
"fortress in those mountains was surprisingly easy..."
msgstr ""
"Y así partieron de Dorest al día siguiente; tras cruzar el río Bork, "
"atravesaron una estrecha pradera entre el Desierto de la Muerte y el Bosque "
"Silencioso, dos regiones temidas. Tras encontrarse —y destruir— algunos "
"puestos rebeldes, llegaron a las Montañas de Haag; una vez allí, encontrar "
"la fortaleza de Aelvar en esas montañas resultó sorprendentemente fácil"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:395
msgid ""
"So, is there any Olokun left now that you're done with him? No offence, but "
"we need him in our travel..."
msgstr ""
"Entonces, ¿queda algo de Olokun ahora que terminaste con él? Sin ofender, "
"pero lo necesitamos en nuestro viaje…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:399
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:403
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:407
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:411
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:415
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:419
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:423
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:427
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:431
msgid "Derceto"
msgstr "Derceto"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:399
msgid ""
"(giggling) Worry not, his hands ached after all the massaging I demanded, "
"but I have healed them myself. Speaking of, there he comes! Now that "
"everyone's here, I'll tell you this tale that comes to us from the very dawn "
"of time..."
msgstr ""
"(riendo) No te preocupes, le dolían las manos después de todo el masaje que "
"exigí, pero yo misma las he sanado. Hablando de eso, ¡ahí viene! Ahora que "
"todos estamos aquí, les contaré esta historia que nos llega desde el "
"mismísimo amanecer del tiempo…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:403
msgid ""
"In this day and age, hardly a border stops those with the spirit to travel, "
"but there was a time when every race knew no land but the one where they "
"first appeared: humans were limited to Arajunna, orcs to Argea, elves to the "
"forests of the Great Continent, drakes to the volcanic islands of Morogor "
"and dwarves to the Heart Mountains. Only the dragons lived everywhere, for "
"the sky was their realm."
msgstr ""
"En esta era, apenas una frontera detiene a quienes tienen espíritu para "
"viajar, pero hubo un tiempo en que cada raza no conocía otra tierra que "
"aquella donde apareció por primera vez: los humanos estaban limitados a "
"Arajunna, los orcos a Argea, los elfos a los bosques del Gran Continente, "
"los dracos a las islas volcánicas de Morogor y los enanos a las Montañas del "
"Corazón. Solo los dragones vivían en todas partes, pues el cielo era su "
"reino."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:407
msgid ""
"Those were also the days when the High Dragons of the Sky, the Fire and the "
"Water – Svarballi, Agniballi and Nitiballi – watched over Irdya. Unlike his "
"peers, Svarballi took no single people under his wings, for his mission was "
"to serve as mediator between all races. Each had a single paramount "
"individual, one whom Svarballi recognised as the wisest or the strongest of "
"their kind; to them the Sky Dragon gave the epithet of Kings and Queens of "
"Irdya."
msgstr ""
"También eran los días en que los Grandes Dragones del Cielo, del Fuego y del "
"Agua —Svarballi, Agniballi y Nitiballi— vigilaban Irdya. A diferencia de sus "
"pares, Svarballi no tomó a un solo pueblo bajo sus alas, pues su misión era "
"servir como mediador entre todas las razas. Cada una tenía un individuo "
"supremo, uno que Svarballi reconocía como el más sabio o el más fuerte de su "
"especie; a ellos el Dragón del Cielo les otorgó el epíteto de Reyes y Reinas "
"de Irdya."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:411
msgid ""
"Paramount among humans, who bask in the light, was the King-Under-the-Sun, "
"whilst the mightiest chief of the nocturnal orcs was the King-Under-the-"
"Moon. The wisest of all elves who thrived in the forests was known as the "
"King-in-the-Woods, and the most stalwart lord of the mining dwarves was the "
"King-in-the-Earth; the trolls, who rose from the very bowels of Irdya, were "
"led by the King-in-the-Abyss. Though we merfolk revered Nitiballi, we had a "
"sage of our own, the Queen-in-the-Ocean. Finally, Agniballi was acknowledged "
"by dragons, drakes and saurians alike as the King-in-the-Air, as the skies "
"were their undisputed domain."
msgstr ""
"Entre los humanos, que se bañan en la luz, el principal era el Rey-Bajo-el-"
"Sol, mientras que el jefe más poderoso de los orcos nocturnos era el Rey-"
"Bajo-la-Luna. El más sabio de todos los elfos que prosperaban en los bosques "
"era conocido como el Rey-en-el-Bosque, y el señor más firme de los enanos "
"mineros era el Rey-en-la-Tierra; los trolls, que surgieron de las mismas "
"entrañas de Irdya, eran liderados por el Rey-en-el-Abismo. Aunque nosotros "
"los sirénidos reverenciábamos a Nitiballi, teníamos nuestra propia sabia, la "
"Reina-en-el-Océano. Finalmente, Agniballi era reconocido por dragones, "
"dracos y saurios por igual como el Rey-en-el-Aire, ya que los cielos eran su "
"dominio indiscutido."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:415
msgid ""
"One day, however, Svarballi became twisted by his own unyielding sense of "
"justice, and declared war upon all of Irdya's children. He gave his enemies "
"some time to prepare themselves for the onslaught - certainly a display of "
"'fairness' in his view. And the Kings prepared by harnessing their own "
"kind's greatest powers into mighty items."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, un día Svarballi se torció por su propio sentido inflexible de "
"justicia y declaró la guerra a todos los hijos de Irdya. Les dio a sus "
"enemigos algún tiempo para prepararse para el asalto —ciertamente una "
"muestra de «justicia» según su punto de vista. Y los Reyes se prepararon "
"canalizando los mayores poderes de sus propios pueblos en objetos poderosos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:419
msgid ""
"The merfolk obtained the storm-wielding Trident of the Seas from Nitiballi; "
"the wisest of the humans, a mage called An-Usrukhar, crafted the greatest of "
"all magic staffs, while the King-Under-the-Moon forged the finest of blades, "
"the dreaded World-Burner; Griknagh of the trolls and Moradin of the dwarves "
"received the Hammers of Ymir and Buri, which could forge the mightiest runes "
"and split the very earth apart."
msgstr ""
"Los sirénidos obtuvieron el Tridente de los Mares portador de tormentas de "
"Nitiballi; el más sabio de los humanos, un mago llamado An-Usrukhar, forjó "
"el mayor de todos los bastones mágicos, mientras que el Rey-Bajo-la-Luna "
"forjó la más fina de las hojas, el temido Quemamundo; Griknagh de los trolls "
"y Moradin de los enanos recibieron los Martillos de Ymir y Buri, capaces de "
"forjar las runas más poderosas y partir la misma tierra."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:423
msgid ""
"These powers were dubbed the Kings' Regalia. The King-in-the-Woods and the "
"King-in-the-Air, by their turn, had always wielded one, for theirs were part "
"of their own nature: the former counted with his unique connection to the "
"faerie plane given him by the blood of Tithanya, the First of the Faeries, "
"whilst the latter was the master of the Brilliant Flame."
msgstr ""
"Estos poderes fueron llamados las Regalias de los Reyes. El Rey-en-el-Bosque "
"y el Rey-en-el-Aire, por su parte, siempre habían empuñado una, pues las "
"suyas formaban parte de su propia naturaleza: el primero contaba con su "
"conexión única al plano feérico otorgada por la sangre de Tithanya, la "
"Primera de las Hadas, mientras que el segundo era el maestro de la Llama "
"Brillante."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:427
msgid ""
"When the Kings and Svarballi clashed, the War of Irdya's Kings began. With "
"the strength of the Regalia and of two High Dragons on their side, the Kings "
"managed to stem the tides of chaos Svarballi unleashed upon the world, and "
"even succeeded in stopping Svarballi himself in a battle. But that was when "
"tragedy struck: Moradin, having grown greedier by the power of his Hammer, "
"murdered Griknagh and stole his Hammer. The trolls demanded the dwarves to "
"return it, to no avail, and so they decided to retrieve the Hammer by force "
"– thus starting their millennia-old war."
msgstr ""
"Cuando los Reyes y Svarballi chocaron, comenzó la Guerra de los Reyes de "
"Irdya. Con la fuerza de las Regalias y de dos Grandes Dragones de su lado, "
"los Reyes lograron contener las mareas de caos que Svarballi desató sobre el "
"mundo e incluso lograron detener al propio Svarballi en una batalla. Pero "
"entonces ocurrió la tragedia: Moradin, volviéndose más codicioso por el "
"poder de su Martillo, asesinó a Griknagh y robó su Martillo. Los trolls "
"exigieron a los enanos que lo devolvieran, sin éxito, y así decidieron "
"recuperarlo por la fuerza —iniciando así su guerra milenaria."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:431
msgid ""
"Orcs and elves took the trolls' side, but the humans remained neutral, "
"trying to hold their alliance together – to no avail. The dragons and the "
"merfolk tried to fight Svarballi on their own, but it were their leaders, "
"Agniballi and Nitiballi, who managed to defeat the Sky Dragon. Irdya was no "
"longer endangered, but its children were disunited; wisely, the Kings hid "
"their Regalia, knowing that, if used against each other, they could wreak "
"major destruction. This is the legend of the Kings' Regalia and of the War "
"of Irdya's Kings."
msgstr ""
"Orcos y elfos tomaron partido por los trolls, pero los humanos permanecieron "
"neutrales, intentando mantener su alianza unida —sin éxito. Los dragones y "
"los sirénidos intentaron luchar contra Svarballi por su cuenta, pero fueron "
"sus líderes, Agniballi y Nitiballi, quienes lograron derrotar al Dragón del "
"Cielo. Irdya ya no estaba en peligro, pero sus hijos quedaron desunidos; "
"sabiamente, los Reyes ocultaron sus Regalias, sabiendo que, si se usaban "
"unas contra otras, podrían causar una destrucción mayor. Esta es la leyenda "
"de las Regalias de los Reyes y de la Guerra de los Reyes de Irdya."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:435
msgid ""
"Tenma went to sleep with her head aching that night – it had been a while "
"since she'd last received so much new information. But most of all, she felt "
"a bit depressed for knowing that the hostility and distrust between peoples "
"was so much older and deeper that she originally thought..."
msgstr ""
"Tenma se fue a dormir con la cabeza doliéndole esa noche —había pasado un "
"tiempo desde la última vez que recibió tanta información nueva. Pero sobre "
"todo, se sintió un poco deprimida al saber que la hostilidad y la "
"desconfianza entre los pueblos eran mucho más antiguas y profundas de lo que "
"originalmente pensaba…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:439
msgid ""
"As she mused about all those things alone in the shores outside Castelfrost, "
"she was approached by Derceto. The mermaid hadn't wished to broach that "
"particular subject in front of everyone; but there, alone on the shore, she "
"explained how she knew about Tenma's true identity; of how Myra's spirit had "
"merged with the spirits of nature after her body was destroyed, of how she "
"had resided in the deepest chambers of the Underwater Temple, and of how "
"Derceto, breaking a rule set by her predecessors, had entered those chambers "
"and met Myra's spirit, quickly befriending her – for, as the spirit said, "
"she felt lonely after the death of Akhen Wadjet, her last descendant..."
msgstr ""
"Mientras reflexionaba sobre todo eso sola en las costas fuera de "
"Castelfrost, fue abordada por Derceto. La sirénida no había querido tocar "
"ese tema en particular delante de todos; pero allí, sola en la orilla, "
"explicó cómo sabía de la verdadera identidad de Tenma; de cómo el espíritu "
"de Myra se había fusionado con los espíritus de la naturaleza tras la "
"destrucción de su cuerpo, de cómo había residido en las cámaras más "
"profundas del Templo Submarino, y de cómo Derceto, rompiendo una regla "
"establecida por sus predecesoras, había entrado en esas cámaras y conocido "
"al espíritu de Myra, haciéndose rápidamente su amiga —pues, como dijo el "
"espíritu, se sentía sola tras la muerte de Akhen Wadjet, su último "
"descendiente…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:443
msgid ""
"The retinue, now joined by merfolk, left Castelfrost early in the following "
"morning, hurrying southwards to catch up with Aelvar. Following a trail of "
"burned-down villages, they reached Bitok nearly two days after leaving "
"Castelfrost; to their shock, the orcish city was found in ruins. Its few "
"survivors reported that Aelvar had left it three days before, going even "
"further southwards."
msgstr ""
"El séquito, ahora acompañado por sirénidos, dejó Castelfrost temprano a la "
"mañana siguiente, apresurándose hacia el sur para alcanzar a Aelvar. "
"Siguiendo un rastro de aldeas incendiadas, llegaron a Bitok casi dos días "
"después de dejar Castelfrost; para su horror, la ciudad orca fue encontrada "
"en ruinas. Sus pocos sobrevivientes informaron que Aelvar la había "
"abandonado tres días antes, dirigiéndose aún más al sur."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:446
msgid ""
"Without thinking twice, the group pressed on towards the Heart Mountains; a "
"day later, they finally found Aelvar's army at one of Knalga's gates, known "
"as the Earth's Mouth; but the situation there was just as bad as in Bitok..."
msgstr ""
"Sin pensarlo dos veces, el grupo continuó hacia las Montañas del Corazón; un "
"día después, finalmente encontraron al ejército de Aelvar en una de las "
"puertas de Knalga, conocida como la Boca de la Tierra; pero la situación "
"allí era tan mala como en Bitok…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:457
msgid ""
"Tenma thought she'd been deep underground during her stay in the "
"Hammermounts, but in the caves of Knalga she understood what the true "
"underground was like. With the aid of earthen spirits and elementals, the "
"travellers, Donar's battalion and Aetheryon's soldiers descended into the "
"steep tunnel known as the Crimson Path; the reddish glow coming from its "
"bottom, as well as the rising temperature and the increasingly dense smoke, "
"gave them a foretaste of what awaited them..."
msgstr ""
"Tenma pensó que había estado muy bajo tierra durante su estancia en los "
"Hammermounts, pero en las cuevas de Knalga entendió cómo era el verdadero "
"subsuelo. Con la ayuda de espíritus terrestres y elementales, los viajeros, "
"el batallón de Donar y los soldados de Aetheryon descendieron al empinado "
"túnel conocido como el Sendero Carmesí; el resplandor rojizo que venía de su "
"fondo, junto con el aumento de temperatura y el humo cada vez más denso, les "
"dio un anticipo de lo que les esperaba…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:468
msgid ""
"Tenma hadn't known Knalga before that war, and she knew little of its "
"history and meaning for the peoples on that side of the continent. Still, as "
"she watched the vast range exploding here and there with volcanic wrath "
"alongside her friends and hundreds of dwarves, trolls and humans, she "
"couldn't avoid feeling her heart ache. For the first time since she'd awoken "
"as Myra, she had suffered a defeat - and a devastating one."
msgstr ""
"Tenma no había conocido Knalga antes de esa guerra, y sabía poco de su "
"historia y significado para los pueblos de ese lado del continente. Aun así, "
"mientras veía la vasta cordillera explotar aquí y allá con furia volcánica "
"junto a sus amigos y cientos de enanos, trolls y humanos, no pudo evitar "
"sentir que le dolía el corazón. Por primera vez desde que había despertado "
"como Myra, había sufrido una derrota —y una devastadora."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:472
msgid ""
"The Knalgan survivors were relocated to Dorest, where Aeldhoryan had already "
"received the Warders of the Alliance. The Wesnothian prince signed a "
"prolonged truce with the northerners; a few days later, six caravans filled "
"with provisions and clothing arrived from the Emerald Plains; the Baryags "
"were unable to send warriors to their allies' aid, but they could afford "
"supporting them economically."
msgstr ""
"Los sobrevivientes knalganos fueron reubicados en Dorest, donde Aeldhoryan "
"ya había recibido a los Guardianes de la Alianza. El príncipe wesnothiano "
"firmó una tregua prolongada con los norteños; unos días después, seis "
"caravanas llenas de provisiones y ropa llegaron desde las Llanuras "
"Esmeralda; los Baryags no pudieron enviar guerreros para ayudar a sus "
"aliados, pero sí podían apoyarlos económicamente."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:476
msgid ""
"In the following two weeks, a more complete report on the incident's "
"aftermath was completed: many dwarvish and troll clans had perished, either "
"swallowed by the rivers of lava or left stranded beyond salvation by them. "
"The human settlements in the valleys of the Heart Mountains suffered the "
"same fate; only those that lay on the range's outskirts could be evacuated "
"in time. Volcanic ashes were seen falling as far north as Melmog, and as far "
"south as Kerlath, ruining many a plantation."
msgstr ""
"En las siguientes dos semanas se completó un informe más detallado sobre las "
"consecuencias del incidente: muchos clanes enanos y trolls habían perecido, "
"ya sea tragados por los ríos de lava o dejados varados sin salvación por "
"ellas. Los asentamientos humanos en los valles de las Montañas del Corazón "
"sufrieron el mismo destino; solo aquellos que estaban en las afueras de la "
"cordillera pudieron ser evacuados a tiempo. Se vieron cenizas volcánicas "
"cayendo tan al norte como Melmog y tan al sur como Kerlath, arruinando "
"muchas plantaciones."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:480
msgid ""
"But neither Tenma, nor Valerya – both of whom were still shaken by Knalga's "
"destruction – nor Cornelya – who still tended to the badly wounded Kenshiro "
"– bothered very much about knowing all those things. As the Yasai girl told "
"Olokun one day, all she wanted at the moment was to go to New Maat'Kare. "
"Derceto had found them at Dorest by then, declaring that she'd take them "
"safely across the sea."
msgstr ""
"Pero ni Tenma, ni Valerya —ambas aún conmocionadas por la destrucción de "
"Knalga— ni Cornelya —quien aún cuidaba al gravemente herido Kenshiro— se "
"molestaron mucho en conocer todos esos detalles. Como le dijo la chica Yasai "
"a Olokun un día, en ese momento lo único que quería era ir a Nueva "
"Maat'Kare. Derceto los había encontrado en Dorest para entonces, declarando "
"que los llevaría sanos y salvos a través del mar."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:484
msgid ""
"The only reason they didn't depart as soon as they could was Kenshiro. The "
"revelation that he was Prince Aeldhoryan's son had been eclipsed by all the "
"other events, but after the gathering which decided the Northern Alliance's "
"new headquarters and truce with Wesnoth, the Wyvern of Wesnoth personally "
"visited the warrior at his tent."
msgstr ""
"La única razón por la que no partieron tan pronto como pudieron fue "
"Kenshiro. La revelación de que era hijo del príncipe Aeldhoryan había sido "
"eclipsada por todos los demás eventos, pero tras la reunión que decidió el "
"nuevo cuartel general de la Alianza del Norte y la tregua con Wesnoth, el "
"Guiverno de Wesnoth visitó personalmente al guerrero en su tienda."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:488
msgid ""
"Kenshiro had always suspected, from rumours heard among his fellow Ken-"
"Ningen, that his father was Aeldhoryan, but he didn't know the story of how "
"he'd arrived in Kodakuni by accident, of how he'd been defeated by the Mad "
"Dog Kyouken in their first fight; of how his mother, Natsu, had found and "
"tended to the Wesnothian prince; and of how a Wesnothian scouting party was "
"attacked by Sogen warriors while searching for Aeldhoryan, a clash which "
"ultimately resulted in Wesnoth declaring war on Kodakuni - and in the final "
"duel between Aeldhoryan and Kyouken."
msgstr ""
"Kenshiro siempre había sospechado, por rumores oídos entre sus compañeros "
"Ken-Ningen, que su padre era Aeldhoryan, pero no conocía la historia de cómo "
"había llegado a Kodakuni por accidente, de cómo había sido derrotado por el "
"Perro Loco Kyouken en su primer combate; de cómo su madre, Natsu, había "
"encontrado y cuidado al príncipe wesnothiano; y de cómo un grupo de "
"exploración wesnothiano fue atacado por guerreros sogen mientras buscaban a "
"Aeldhoryan, un choque que finalmente resultó en que Wesnoth declarara la "
"guerra a Kodakuni —y en el duelo final entre Aeldhoryan y Kyouken."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:492
msgid ""
"The prince explained that he had kept Kenshiro's parentage a secret out of "
"fear for Emperor Taryen's reaction - for never would he have accepted a "
"grandson with low-born foreign blood. Kenshiro, by his turn, answered that "
"he didn't care about being formally recognised as his son: he had no "
"intention of claiming the Wesnothian throne, nor had he ever missed a "
"father, for Natsu had given him all the love he'd ever needed."
msgstr ""
"El príncipe explicó que había mantenido en secreto la paternidad de Kenshiro "
"por miedo a la reacción del emperador Taryen —pues nunca habría aceptado a "
"un nieto con sangre extranjera de baja cuna. Kenshiro, por su parte, "
"respondió que no le importaba ser reconocido formalmente como su hijo: no "
"tenía intención de reclamar el trono wesnothiano, ni nunca había echado de "
"menos a un padre, pues Natsu le había dado todo el amor que alguna vez "
"necesitó."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:496
msgid ""
"Thus, almost three weeks after the Core's destruction, as Kenshiro fully "
"healed, Tenma and Valerya overcame the shock of Knalga's destruction, the "
"refugees left Dorest and the volcanic eruptions lowered in intensity, the "
"travellers went to Tirigaz, once again under the Northern Alliance's "
"banners, escorted by Northerner and Wesnothian troops. Once there, they "
"headed straight to the city's docks, where Derceto already awaited them "
"alongside other friends..."
msgstr ""
"Así, casi tres semanas después de la destrucción del Núcleo, cuando Kenshiro "
"sanó completamente, Tenma y Valerya superaron el shock de la destrucción de "
"Knalga, los refugiados dejaron Dorest y las erupciones volcánicas "
"disminuyeron en intensidad, los viajeros fueron a Tirigaz, nuevamente bajo "
"los estandartes de la Alianza del Norte, escoltados por tropas norteñas y "
"wesnothianas. Una vez allí, se dirigieron directamente a los muelles de la "
"ciudad, donde Derceto ya los esperaba junto a otros amigos…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:506
msgid ""
"And thus, after many detours and battles and after meeting so many new "
"friends and allies, Tenma began the crossing of the Vast Sea towards the "
"land beyond the setting sun, and the final stop of her world odyssey: Netjer-"
"Ta."
msgstr ""
"Y así, tras muchos desvíos y batallas y después de conocer a tantos nuevos "
"amigos y aliados, Tenma comenzó el cruce del Vasto Mar hacia la tierra más "
"allá del sol poniente, y la parada final de su odisea mundial: Netjer-Ta."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:510
msgid ""
"Having always lived deep inside the continent, Tenma had worried that "
"unstable and stormy aquamarine world would do her no good. And yet, as the "
"ship crossed the waters at full speed and the wind ran through her long "
"hair, soaking it with salty droplets and filling her lungs with the smell of "
"the sea, Tenma felt strangely nostalgic."
msgstr ""
"Habiendo vivido siempre en lo profundo del continente, Tenma había temido "
"que el inestable y tormentoso mundo aguamarina no le hiciera bien. Y sin "
"embargo, mientras el barco cruzaba las aguas a toda velocidad y el viento "
"corría por su largo cabello, empapándolo con gotas saladas y llenándole los "
"pulmones con el olor del mar, Tenma sintió una extraña nostalgia."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:514
msgid ""
"The same could not be said of Kenshiro, Algil and, surprisingly, Valerya, "
"all of whom felt so seasick that they often had to stop on sand banks to "
"rest, much to Cornelya's teasing."
msgstr ""
"Lo mismo no podía decirse de Kenshiro, Algil y, sorprendentemente, Valerya, "
"todos los cuales se mareaban tanto que a menudo tenían que detenerse en "
"bancos de arena para descansar, para gran diversión de Cornelya."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:518
msgid ""
"The elf, by her turn, seemed to change during the long sea journey. "
"Everybody had noticed already that, since their arrival in the Northlands, "
"she had been more open to conversation with Kenshiro; as they sailed the "
"ocean, she began speaking with the others as well - and speak without barbs "
"in her words. The merfolk had a part in that; having no grudge towards them, "
"Cornelya befriended Derceto's people – and, because they were already close "
"friends with Olokun, Tenma and the other humans, the elf often caught "
"herself joining the merfolk as they laughed at Tenma's jokes."
msgstr ""
"La elfa, por su parte, parecía cambiar durante el largo viaje marítimo. "
"Todos ya habían notado que, desde su llegada a las Tierras del Norte, había "
"estado más abierta a conversar con Kenshiro; mientras navegaban el océano, "
"comenzó a hablar también con los demás —y a hablar sin espinas en sus "
"palabras. Los sirénidos tuvieron parte en eso; sin guardar rencor hacia "
"ellos, Cornelya se hizo amiga del pueblo de Derceto —y, como ya eran "
"cercanos amigos de Olokun, Tenma y los otros humanos, la elfa a menudo se "
"sorprendía uniéndose a los sirénidos mientras reían con los chistes de Tenma."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:522
msgid ""
"Indeed, Tenma and her friends owed the merfolk a great deal. Led by Derceto, "
"they guided and fed them, and also protected the ship from the myriad of "
"monsters living in those waters. They even pulled the vessel with their own "
"strength so that it could enter a current that would take the travellers "
"past the Wesnoth-held Green Isle and, at the same time, safely far from it."
msgstr ""
"En efecto, Tenma y sus amigos debían mucho a los sirénidos. Liderados por "
"Derceto, los guiaron y alimentaron, y también protegieron el barco de la "
"miríada de monstruos que vivían en esas aguas. Incluso tiraron del barco con "
"su propia fuerza para que pudiera entrar en una corriente que llevaría a los "
"viajeros más allá de la Isla Verde en poder de Wesnoth y, al mismo tiempo, a "
"salvo lejos de ella."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:526
msgid ""
"With the invaluable aid of Derceto and her people, the ship sighted the "
"shores of Netjer-Ta for the first time a mere forty days after departing "
"from Tirigaz. The first thing they saw was lofty, but ruined towers rising "
"from a densely forested peninsula; that was, as Olokun explained, the "
"ancient city of Maat'Kare, founded by Myra and abandoned after the War of "
"the Jewel. As she watched the towering ruins amidst the thick tropical "
"forest, Tenma felt her heart ache – but she angrily waved that feeling "
"aside; after all, she said to herself, those were not her own feelings, but "
"those of 'her former self'."
msgstr ""
"Con la invaluable ayuda de Derceto y su pueblo, el barco avistó las costas "
"de Netjer-Ta por primera vez apenas cuarenta días después de partir de "
"Tirigaz. Lo primero que vieron fueron torres elevadas pero en ruinas que se "
"alzaban desde una península densamente boscosa; esa era, como explicó "
"Olokun, la antigua ciudad de Maat'Kare, fundada por Myra y abandonada tras "
"la Guerra de la Joya. Mientras observaba las imponentes ruinas entre el "
"espeso bosque tropical, Tenma sintió que le dolía el corazón —pero apartó "
"ese sentimiento con enojo; después de todo, se dijo a sí misma, esos no eran "
"sus propios sentimientos, sino los de «su yo anterior»."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:530
msgid ""
"The merfolk led the ship along the sandy south-eastern coast of Netjer-Ta "
"until they reached the beaches of a golden desert, so vast it stretched "
"beyond the horizon: that was the Silent Desert, the last stage of their long "
"journey. The merfolk built a camp near the docking site to wait for their "
"leader's return – because forty days were far from being enough to make her "
"get sick of Olokun. As she entered that new environment, Tenma could not "
"avoid another strange feeling; for those were the very same golden sands "
"where 'her former self' had died to become a legend..."
msgstr ""
"Los sirénidos guiaron la nave a lo largo de la costa sudoriental arenosa de "
"Netjer-Ta hasta que llegaron a las playas de un desierto dorado tan vasto "
"que se extendía más allá del horizonte: ese era el Desierto Silencioso, la "
"última etapa de su largo viaje. Los sirénidos construyeron un campamento "
"cerca del lugar de atraque para esperar el regreso de su líder, porque "
"cuarenta días estaban muy lejos de ser suficientes para que ella se cansara "
"de Olokun. Al entrar en ese nuevo entorno, Tenma no pudo evitar otra extraña "
"sensación; pues esas eran exactamente las mismas arenas doradas donde «su yo "
"anterior» había muerto para convertirse en leyenda..."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:535
msgid "Ancient Realms"
msgstr "Reinos Antiguos"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:545
msgid ""
"Tenma resigned to being the centre of attention as she strode across the "
"vast and imposing city alongside her friends. She could hear the "
"Maat'Karians whispering about her: apparently, they were genuinely impressed "
"by her participation in the battle, and also by the strength of her "
"elementals, but they were still doubtful about her truly being Myra reborn. "
"Not that it bothered her, of course."
msgstr ""
"Tenma se resignó a ser el centro de atención mientras avanzaba por la vasta "
"e imponente ciudad junto a sus amigos. Podía oír a los maat'karianos "
"susurrar sobre ella: aparentemente, estaban genuinamente impresionados por "
"su participación en la batalla y también por la fuerza de sus elementales, "
"pero aún dudaban de que realmente fuera Myra renacida. No es que eso la "
"molestara, por supuesto."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:549
msgid ""
"Cornelya and Kenshiro both stayed at the healing centre; Tenma, Olokun, "
"Valerya, Derceto and Algil went to the Wadjet Hall as soon as they had a "
"meal. The large hall was crowded not only with Lords and Sages, but also "
"with young mages, soldiers and even commoners, all of whom stared at the "
"Yasai girl with a mix of awe and suspicion. She sat on a marble chair next "
"to the dais where Ankhmare already stood; and then, running the whole hall "
"with his eyes, the Star Master began..."
msgstr ""
"Cornelya y Kenshiro se quedaron en el centro de sanación; Tenma, Olokun, "
"Valerya, Derceto y Algil fueron al Salón Wadjet tan pronto como comieron. El "
"gran salón estaba abarrotado no solo de Señores y Sabios, sino también de "
"jóvenes magos, soldados e incluso plebeyos, todos los cuales miraban a la "
"chica Yasai con una mezcla de asombro y sospecha. Ella se sentó en una silla "
"de mármol junto al estrado donde ya estaba Ankhmare; y entonces, recorriendo "
"todo el salón con la mirada, el Maestro Estelar comenzó…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:560
msgid ""
"It was a relief to have a calm place to stay after fifteen months travelling "
"through inhospitable regions, or so Tenma thought – even though New "
"Maat'Kare wasn't exactly peaceful, with all the political tension between "
"Ankhmare and Ramoses. She had believed, from everything Olokun had told her, "
"that Akhen's Prophecy was regarded as the truth by most Maat'Karians, but "
"she now felt like a tool in a political fight – though she had developed "
"such a strong antagonism towards Ramoses that she accepted to train under "
"Ankhmare without complaint."
msgstr ""
"Fue un alivio tener un lugar tranquilo donde quedarse tras quince meses "
"viajando por regiones inhóspitas, o eso pensó Tenma —aunque Nueva Maat'Kare "
"no era exactamente pacífica, con toda la tensión política entre Ankhmare y "
"Ramoses. Había creído, por todo lo que Olokun le había contado, que la "
"Profecía de Akhen era considerada verdad por la mayoría de los "
"maat'karianos, pero ahora se sentía como una herramienta en una lucha "
"política —aunque había desarrollado un antagonismo tan fuerte hacia Ramoses "
"que aceptó entrenar bajo Ankhmare sin quejas."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:564
msgid ""
"In her second day in New Maat'Kare, she was taken by Olokun and the Star "
"Master to see the city, and was told its history. By the end of the day, she "
"was taken to the Abyss Dungeons, where she saw the Trident of the Seas. To "
"her own distaste, she felt a warm, nostalgic feeling when holding the mighty "
"weapon; but sighting the dreaded Sky Soul, which was kept inside a powerful "
"magic jail, only made her 'other self's' worst memories resurface: fleeting "
"images of cities burned, loved ones gone, endless suffering..."
msgstr ""
"En su segundo día en Nueva Maat'Kare, Olokun y el Maestro Estelar la "
"llevaron a ver la ciudad y le contaron su historia. Al final del día, fue "
"llevada a las Mazmorras del Abismo, donde vio el Tridente de los Mares. Para "
"su propio disgusto, sintió una cálida sensación nostálgica al sostener el "
"poderoso arma; pero al ver el temido Alma del Cielo, que se mantenía dentro "
"de una poderosa cárcel mágica, solo hizo resurgir los peores recuerdos de "
"«su otro yo»: imágenes fugaces de ciudades incendiadas, seres queridos "
"perdidos, sufrimiento interminable…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:568
msgid ""
"Tenma knew the Maat'Karian might have done that on purpose, but seeing the "
"Sky Soul only strengthened her resolve to destroy it; thus, in the following "
"dawn, she met Ankhmare at the Academy to start her training."
msgstr ""
"Tenma sabía que los maat'karianos podrían haberlo hecho a propósito, pero "
"ver el Alma del Cielo solo fortaleció su determinación de destruirla; así, "
"al amanecer siguiente, se reunió con Ankhmare en la Academia para comenzar "
"su entrenamiento."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:572
msgid ""
"And, while Tenma continued on the path to become the Dragon-Slayer of "
"Akhen's Prophecy, Cornelya followed the faun Umbrius to Argea and to a path "
"she had long forsaken, but whose call she couldn't ignore forever..."
msgstr ""
"Y mientras Tenma continuaba por el camino para convertirse en la "
"Cazadragones de la Profecía de Akhen, Cornelya siguió al fauno Umbrius hacia "
"Argea y hacia un camino que había abandonado hacía mucho, pero cuyo llamado "
"no podía ignorar para siempre…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:583
msgid ""
"Thus Cornelya and Kenshiro decided to stay at Heartwood Valley – though she "
"was still unsure about what drove her to that, in the end. She'd never felt "
"so full of doubt: in those days at that mystical valley, she felt an almost "
"irresistible desire to throw her weapons away and embrace her true self "
"again; in those days at the home of fauns and faeries, she found herself at "
"peace."
msgstr ""
"Así Cornelya y Kenshiro decidieron quedarse en el Valle del Corazón de "
"Madera —aunque ella aún no estaba segura de qué la impulsaba a eso, al "
"final. Nunca se había sentido tan llena de dudas: en esos días en ese valle "
"místico, sentía un deseo casi irresistible de arrojar sus armas y abrazar "
"nuevamente a su verdadero yo; en esos días en el hogar de faunos y hadas, se "
"encontraba en paz."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:587
msgid ""
"But whenever she smiled, scenes of a human village burning, of her mother "
"being murdered and of cruel iron boots kicking her frail childish body "
"flashed in her mind, reminding her of the oath she'd sworn to herself – of "
"using whatever means available to defend her home and people – and that she "
"had gone on that journey on her father's command alone."
msgstr ""
"Pero cada vez que sonreía, escenas de una aldea humana ardiendo, de su madre "
"siendo asesinada y de crueles botas de hierro pateando su frágil cuerpo "
"infantil destellaban en su mente, recordándole el juramento que se había "
"hecho a sí misma —de usar cualquier medio disponible para defender su hogar "
"y su gente— y que había emprendido ese viaje solo por orden de su padre."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:591
msgid ""
"While both Cornelya and Kenshiro improved their skills, thousands of miles "
"away their old enemy-turned-ally embarked on a quest of his own..."
msgstr ""
"Mientras tanto Cornelya y Kenshiro mejoraban sus habilidades, a miles de "
"kilómetros de distancia su viejo enemigo convertido en aliado emprendía una "
"búsqueda propia…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:602
msgid ""
"For three weeks, Tenma trained with the commitment and focus of a Hachiman "
"Priestess of Kodakuni; however, much to her frustration, she didn't improve "
"nearly as much as she had expected. According to Ankhmare, her current "
"strength was just the surface of her true potential, that her true power lay "
"in her connection to nature's spirits. But no method employed – from guided "
"meditation to summoning her spirits and begging them for aid – seemed to "
"work; all she accomplished was recovering a few more memories from her past "
"life."
msgstr ""
"Durante tres semanas, Tenma entrenó con el compromiso y la concentración de "
"una Sacerdotisa Hachiman de Kodakuni; sin embargo, para su frustración, no "
"mejoró ni de cerca tanto como esperaba. Según Ankhmare, su fuerza actual era "
"solo la superficie de su verdadero potencial, que su verdadero poder residía "
"en su conexión con los espíritus de la naturaleza. Pero ningún método "
"empleado —desde la meditación guiada hasta invocar a sus espíritus y "
"rogarles ayuda— parecía funcionar; todo lo que logró fue recuperar algunas "
"memorias más de su vida pasada."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:605
msgid ""
"Concerned about his new pupil's slow progress, Ankhmare thought on a "
"solution. He'd already dismissed her suggestion of going to the Windsong in "
"the North Pole – who, according to Akhen's Scrolls, had found a way to "
"connect to the spirits of nature –, as there was no guarantee that they'd "
"welcome them with anything short of destructive ciphers. Still, talking "
"about them gave Ankhmare an idea; and then, in the following morning, master "
"and disciple set out for the last remnant of Windsong presence on Netjer-"
"Ta..."
msgstr ""
"Preocupado por el lento progreso de su nueva alumna, Ankhmare pensó en una "
"solución. Ya había descartado su sugerencia de ir a las Hijas del Viento en "
"el Polo Norte —quienes, según los Pergaminos de Akhen, habían encontrado una "
"forma de conectarse con los espíritus de la naturaleza—, pues no había "
"garantía de que las recibieran con algo menos que cifrados destructivos. Aun "
"así, hablar de ellas le dio una idea a Ankhmare; y entonces, a la mañana "
"siguiente, maestro y discípula partieron hacia el último remanente de "
"presencia de las Hijas del Viento en Netjer-Ta…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:615
msgid ""
"Never before had Tenma felt so annoyed at her 'former self'. She couldn't "
"hide that she was ecstatic for having Akashia with her, but she didn't know "
"how to express this joy in a way that wasn't awkward. In fact, she didn't "
"even understand why she felt like that; she'd learned from Ankhmare that "
"they'd been close friends, but Tenma wondered just how close they had truly "
"been."
msgstr ""
"Nunca antes Tenma se había sentido tan molesta con su «yo anterior». No "
"podía ocultar que estaba extasiada por tener a Akashia con ella, pero no "
"sabía cómo expresar esa alegría de una manera que no fuera incómoda. De "
"hecho, ni siquiera entendía por qué se sentía así; había aprendido de "
"Ankhmare que habían sido amigas cercanas, pero Tenma se preguntaba cuán "
"cercanas habían sido realmente."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:618
msgid ""
"Akashia herself was confused and irascible; she'd taken everything Ankhmare "
"had told her about Maat'Kare's history, the Sky Soul and the current world "
"order quite well, but the story of Myra's fall made her suddenly gloomy. As "
"expected, she dismissed the claim that Tenma was Myra's reincarnation, and "
"neither the girl nor the Star Master insisted on the subject, unwilling to "
"incur in Akashia's wrath. After examining her, Ankhmare declared that only "
"her brain had been fully restored; the rest of her body was half-dead, much "
"like a vampire's."
msgstr ""
"La propia Akashia estaba confundida e irascible; había tomado bastante bien "
"todo lo que Ankhmare le había contado sobre la historia de Maat'Kare, el "
"Alma del Cielo y el orden mundial actual, pero la historia de la caída de "
"Myra la sumió repentinamente en melancolía. Como era de esperar, desestimó "
"la afirmación de que Tenma era la reencarnación de Myra, y ni la chica ni el "
"Maestro Estelar insistieron en el tema, no queriendo incurrir en la ira de "
"Akashia. Tras examinarla, Ankhmare declaró que solo su cerebro había sido "
"completamente restaurado; el resto de su cuerpo estaba medio muerto, muy "
"parecido al de un vampiro."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:621
msgid ""
"After failing to find anything in Hiera'Laksha regarding nature magic, Tenma "
"and Ankhmare discussed what they had seen and heard. It seemed evident to "
"both that Ramoses and the rogue dwarves were in cahoots against what they "
"apparently saw as a plot headed by the Star Master and the foreigners to "
"topple them. Leaving New Maat'Kare had proved to be a mistake, as the "
"absence of Ankhmare had allowed Ramoses and his allies to take over the "
"government."
msgstr ""
"Tras no encontrar nada en Hiera'Laksha respecto a la magia de la naturaleza, "
"Tenma y Ankhmare discutieron lo que habían visto y oído. A ambos les parecía "
"evidente que Ramoses y los enanos renegados estaban confabulados contra lo "
"que aparentemente veían como un complot encabezado por el Maestro Estelar y "
"los extranjeros para derrocarlos. Dejar Nueva Maat'Kare había resultado ser "
"un error, pues la ausencia de Ankhmare había permitido a Ramoses y sus "
"aliados tomar el control del gobierno."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:624
msgid ""
"With New Maat'Kare too dangerous at the moment, worried about the dwarvish "
"attack and about Algil's fate, Ankhmare, Tenma and Akashia headed towards "
"the Cyan Mountains - to Hammerstead, the underground capital of the dwarves, "
"where the Arcanister kept and protected the Aigathol's greatest relic..."
msgstr ""
"Con Nueva Maat'Kare demasiado peligrosa en ese momento, preocupados por el "
"ataque enano y por el destino de Algil, Ankhmare, Tenma y Akashia se "
"dirigieron hacia las Montañas Cian —a Hammerstead, la capital subterránea de "
"los enanos, donde la Arcanista guardaba y protegía la mayor reliquia de los "
"Aigathol…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:634
msgid ""
"It had been a while since Tenma had been to such a brutal and gory battle – "
"the last being at the Earthenheart Caves – and, even though she had gotten "
"used to fighting by then, she still had a hard time with such grim sights."
msgstr ""
"Había pasado un tiempo desde que Tenma había estado en una batalla tan "
"brutal y sangrienta —la última había sido en las Cuevas del Corazón Terrestre"
"— y, aunque ya se había acostumbrado a luchar para entonces, aún le costaba "
"con visiones tan sombrías."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:637
msgid ""
"If the human felt that way, one can imagine how Ansaxa felt for seeing the "
"tunnels of her own city nearly blocked with piles of the mangled corpses of "
"those whom she'd vowed to guide and protect. After giving a proper cremation "
"to all fallen warriors, she gathered her best gryphon masters and explorers "
"and ordered them to scout all of Netjer-Ta if needed be, until they found "
"the rebel dwarves' headquarters."
msgstr ""
"Si la humana se sentía así, uno puede imaginar cómo se sintió Ansaxa al ver "
"los túneles de su propia ciudad casi bloqueados con pilas de cadáveres "
"destrozados de aquellos a quienes había jurado guiar y proteger. Tras dar "
"una cremación adecuada a todos los guerreros caídos, reunió a sus mejores "
"maestros de grifos y exploradores y les ordenó explorar todo Netjer-Ta si "
"era necesario, hasta que encontraran el cuartel general de los enanos "
"rebeldes."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:640
msgid ""
"And, as one of the gryphon masters returned a mere four days later with news "
"of the rebels' whereabouts, Ansaxa summoned her most trusted commanders and "
"declared that she would personally lead her forces to Narthaol's base. "
"Hoping to find clues on Algil's fate – or, better still, the dwarf himself – "
"Tenma followed her, and so did Ankhmare and Akashia..."
msgstr ""
"Y, cuando uno de los maestros de grifos regresó apenas cuatro días después "
"con noticias sobre el paradero de los rebeldes, Ansaxa convocó a sus "
"comandantes más confiables y declaró que ella misma lideraría sus fuerzas "
"hacia la base de Narthaol. Esperando encontrar pistas sobre el destino de "
"Algil —o, mejor aún, al propio enano—, Tenma la siguió, y también lo "
"hicieron Ankhmare y Akashia"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:650
msgid ""
"With their dwarvish allies safe, the only threat to Ankhmare and Tenma was "
"Ramoses himself, but neither of them could even tell with certainty the "
"state of affairs in New Maat'Kare; Wesir's attack only seemed to indicate "
"that the general had seized power, but it might had also been a 'lone wolf' "
"move. Tenma believed that, if Ramoses had indeed overtaken the government, "
"Olokun, and possibly Valerya and Derceto as well, would have been forced out "
"of the city – in which case they would have reunited by then."
msgstr ""
"Con sus aliados enanos a salvo, la única amenaza para Ankhmare y Tenma era "
"el propio Ramoses, pero ninguno de los dos podía saber con certeza el estado "
"de las cosas en Nueva Maat'Kare; el ataque de Wesir solo parecía indicar que "
"el general había tomado el poder, pero también podría haber sido un "
"movimiento de «lobo solitario». Tenma creía que, si Ramoses había tomado "
"efectivamente el gobierno, Olokun, y posiblemente Valerya y Derceto también, "
"habrían sido obligados a salir de la ciudad —en cuyo caso ya se habrían "
"reunido para entonces."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:654
msgid ""
"Worried about New Maat'Kare's situation, Tenma, Ankhmare and Akashia parted "
"ways with Ansaxa's retinue as they returned to the Aigathol caves – Algil "
"followed the Arcanister, as she wanted to talk with him about Ymer's Hammer; "
"escorted through the easiest mountain paths by dwarvish scouts, they managed "
"to return to the Silent Desert in a mere three days; as the fourth one "
"dawned, they sighted the monumental walls of the desert city rising above "
"the horizon. Encircling it, there were huge scores of elementals, deployed "
"by Ramoses to greet the Star Master and the girl from the Seer's Prophecy..."
msgstr ""
"Preocupados por la situación en Nueva Maat'Kare, Tenma, Ankhmare y Akashia "
"se separaron del séquito de Ansaxa mientras regresaban a las cuevas Aigathol "
"—Algil siguió a la Arcanista, pues quería hablar con ella sobre el Martillo "
"de Ymer; escoltados por exploradores enanos a través de los caminos "
"montañosos más fáciles, lograron regresar al Desierto Silencioso en solo "
"tres días; al amanecer del cuarto, avistaron las monumentales murallas de la "
"ciudad del desierto elevándose sobre el horizonte. Rodeándola, había enormes "
"cantidades de elementales, desplegados por Ramoses para recibir al Maestro "
"Estelar y a la chica de la Profecía del Vidente…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:665
msgid "Well, I have to admit, you were really impressive back there..."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, tengo que admitir que estuviste realmente impresionante allá atrás…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:669
msgid ""
"Akashia, how could you do this to yourself, to me...? Do you really think I "
"wanted to lose you again?"
msgstr ""
"Akashia, ¿cómo pudiste hacerte esto a ti misma, a mí…? ¿Realmente crees que "
"quería perderte otra vez?"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:673
msgid ""
"I wanted to teach you... No, to remind you of what made Myra so strong. It "
"wasn't her spells, or her summoning skills, or the Trident of the Seas, as "
"much as it was her will to protect those who were dear to her. On her own, "
"she was formidable; at the sight of her loved ones in danger, however, not "
"even death itself could stop her..."
msgstr ""
"Quería enseñarte… No, recordarte qué hacía a Myra tan fuerte. No eran sus "
"hechizos, ni sus habilidades de invocación, ni el Tridente de los Mares, "
"tanto como su voluntad de proteger a quienes le eran queridos. Por sí sola "
"era formidable; pero ante la visión de sus seres queridos en peligro, ni "
"siquiera la muerte misma podía detenerla…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:677
msgid ""
"(smirking) Now, how can you say I'm dear to you? Even if you were once Myra, "
"as Tenma Yozora you have just recently met me..."
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo) Ahora, ¿cómo puedes decir que te soy querida? Incluso si alguna "
"vez fuiste Myra, como Tenma Yozora apenas me conoces recientemente…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:681
msgid ""
"You know, in my culture we believe that, when people truly love each other, "
"it's because their souls are connected; so that, even after they die and are "
"reborn as different people, their feelings for each other remain the same. I "
"may not be Myra, but our souls are still the same, and so should be our "
"feelings."
msgstr ""
"Sabes, en mi cultura creemos que, cuando las personas se aman "
"verdaderamente, es porque sus almas están conectadas; de modo que, incluso "
"después de morir y renacer como personas diferentes, sus sentimientos mutuos "
"permanecen iguales. Puede que no sea Myra, pero nuestras almas siguen siendo "
"las mismas, y por lo tanto también deberían serlo nuestros sentimientos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:685
msgid ""
"So, if Jevyan was reborn in this time, would you still love him...? No, "
"don't answer, I don't want to hear it... Better, let me ask you this: if we "
"were to meet again in another life, another time, would you be able to love "
"me...?"
msgstr ""
"Entonces, si Jevyan renaciera en este tiempo, ¿aún lo amarías…? No, no "
"respondas, no quiero oírlo… Mejor, déjame preguntarte esto: si nos "
"volviéramos a encontrar en otra vida, en otro tiempo, ¿podrías amarme…?"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:689
msgid "Let this be my answer... (kisses her)"
msgstr "Que esta sea mi respuesta… (la besa)"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:693
msgid ""
"(smiling) I see... In the end, I suppose I should feel lucky, for being able "
"to die in your arms a second time; not everyone can boast a death so "
"peaceful..."
msgstr ""
"(sonriendo) Entiendo… Al final, supongo que debería sentirme afortunada por "
"poder morir en tus brazos una segunda vez; no todos pueden presumir de una "
"muerte tan pacífica…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:697
msgid ""
"Thus Akashia passed away, once again in the arms of her beloved; but this "
"time her face was one of peace and happiness, for now she knew that she, "
"too, was loved. Tenma carried her lifeless body to the Phoenix's Nest, the "
"city's highest tower, and there she built a funeral pyre. Her friends merely "
"watched; they knew Tenma needed to do that herself. The pyre's flames shone "
"intensely in the darkening skies for many minutes, and then the chilly night "
"breeze spread the ancient heroine's ashes over the city of her beloved."
msgstr ""
"Así Akashia falleció, una vez más en los brazos de su amado; pero esta vez "
"su rostro era de paz y felicidad, pues ahora sabía que también era amada. "
"Tenma llevó su cuerpo sin vida al Nido del Fénix, la torre más alta de la "
"ciudad, y allí construyó una pira funeraria. Sus amigos solo observaron; "
"sabían que Tenma necesitaba hacerlo ella misma. Las llamas de la pira "
"brillaron intensamente en los cielos oscurecientes durante muchos minutos, y "
"luego la fría brisa nocturna esparció las cenizas de la antigua heroína "
"sobre la ciudad de su amado."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:701
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, the masters loyal to Ankhmare – such as Shirahel and Akhetamun – "
"were released from captivity. Although Ramoses was adamant about enduring "
"judgment for his actions, Ankhmare himself publicly forgave him. Later, "
"Tenma was summoned to the City Hall; there, her identity as Myra's "
"reincarnation and the Dragon-Slayer from Akhen's Prophecy was acknowledged "
"by all."
msgstr ""
"Mientras tanto, los maestros leales a Ankhmare —como Shirahel y Akhetamun— "
"fueron liberados de su cautiverio. Aunque Ramoses insistió en enfrentar el "
"juicio por sus acciones, el propio Ankhmare lo perdonó públicamente. Más "
"tarde, Tenma fue convocada al Salón de la Ciudad; allí, su identidad como "
"reencarnación de Myra y Cazadragones de la Profecía de Akhen fue reconocida "
"por todos."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:705
msgid ""
"This meant two things: firstly, that Tenma had some inheritance to claim, "
"such as the Trident of the Seas. But the first thing she claimed was the Sky "
"Soul itself: she argued that the Maat'Karians had suffered enough with that "
"burden, and that she now was the best guardian it could possibly have. Tenma "
"personally descended into the Jewel's Chambers to collect it; for the first "
"time in the Maat'Karians' millenarian history, their peace would not be "
"haunted by the presence of the cursed jewel."
msgstr ""
"Esto significaba dos cosas: primero, que Tenma tenía una herencia que "
"reclamar, como el Tridente de los Mares. Pero lo primero que reclamó fue el "
"propio Alma del Cielo: argumentó que los maat'karianos ya habían sufrido "
"suficiente con esa carga, y que ahora ella era la mejor guardiana que podía "
"tener. Tenma descendió personalmente a las Cámaras de la Joya para "
"recogerla; por primera vez en la historia milenaria de los maat'karianos, su "
"paz no estaría atormentada por la presencia de la joya maldita."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:709
msgid ""
"Secondly, Tenma had a new journey ahead, and she'd already decided, after "
"discussing Akhen's Scrolls with the masters, that it would start in "
"Arajunna, where Akhen had found clues about the Ancient Ones, or the "
"Avatars, creators of the High Dragons. Tenma remembered having learned a few "
"things about them in her past life from Nitiballi himself, but she felt she "
"needed to learn much more. She believed that such knowledge would be "
"invaluable in finding ways to destroy Svarballi – who, she recalled, could "
"only be destroyed by the power of an Avatar."
msgstr ""
"En segundo lugar, Tenma tenía un nuevo viaje por delante, y ya había "
"decidido, tras discutir los Pergaminos de Akhen con los maestros, que "
"comenzaría en Arajunna, donde Akhen había encontrado pistas sobre los "
"Antiguos, o los Avatares, creadores de los Grandes Dragones. Tenma recordaba "
"haber aprendido algunas cosas sobre ellos en su vida pasada del propio "
"Nitiballi, pero sentía que necesitaba aprender mucho más. Creía que tal "
"conocimiento sería invaluable para encontrar formas de destruir a Svarballi —"
"quien, recordaba, solo podía ser destruido por el poder de un Avatar."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:713
msgid ""
"Something else drew her to Arajunna: the Deva Sword, once wielded by "
"Akashia. Its unusual qualities were well-known, but only Tenma realised that "
"its power was of a different nature than anything known to either herself or "
"the Maat'Karian masters. As it was known that sword had been brought in by "
"the Windsong alongside Akashia herself, and that she was a native of "
"Arajunna, so was that continent the logical next step of the journey."
msgstr ""
"Algo más la atrajo hacia Arajunna: la Espada Deva, que una vez empuñó "
"Akashia. Sus cualidades inusuales eran bien conocidas, pero solo Tenma se "
"dio cuenta de que su poder era de una naturaleza distinta a todo lo conocido "
"tanto por ella como por los maestros maat’karianos. Como se sabía que esa "
"espada había sido traída por las Hijas del Viento junto con la propia "
"Akashia, y que ella era nativa de Arajunna, ese continente era el siguiente "
"paso lógico del viaje."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:717
msgid ""
"Two weeks after the battle against Ramoses, Algil returned from the Aigathol "
"Caves – carrying, on his back, the Hammer of Ymer itself. He'd spent all "
"that time trying to convince Ansaxa and her advisers to let him return the "
"hammer to its rightful owners, but it had been the rebels' return, and their "
"surprising support for Algil's cause, that ultimately convinced them. "
"Genuinely happy that the dwarves had finally chosen peace, Tenma told her "
"friends to ready themselves to travel once again..."
msgstr ""
"Dos semanas después de la batalla contra Ramoses, Algil regresó de las "
"Cuevas de Aigathol llevando a cuestas el mismísimo Martillo de Ymer. Había "
"pasado todo ese tiempo intentando convencer a Ansaxa y a sus consejeros de "
"que le permitieran devolver el martillo a sus legítimos dueños, pero fue el "
"regreso de los rebeldes y su sorprendente apoyo a la causa de Algil lo que "
"finalmente los convenció. Genuinamente feliz de que los enanos finalmente "
"hubieran elegido la paz, Tenma les dijo a sus amigos que se prepararan para "
"viajar una vez más..."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:728
msgid ""
"With the Queen-in-the-Ocean on their side, sailing from Netjer-Ta to "
"Arajunna was much easier and safer – not only because of her absolute power "
"over both the weather and the sea currents, but also because scores of "
"mermen and even some naga, amazed by Derceto's power, joined her ranks, thus "
"increasing the number of escorts protecting the Maat'Karian vessels."
msgstr ""
"Con la Reina-en-el-Océano de su lado, navegar desde Netjer-Ta hasta Arajunna "
"fue mucho más fácil y seguro, no solo por su poder absoluto sobre el clima y "
"las corrientes marinas, sino también porque decenas de sirénidos e incluso "
"algunos naga, asombrados por el poder de Derceto, se unieron a sus filas, "
"aumentando así el número de escoltas que protegían las naves maat’karianas."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:732
msgid ""
"That journey was much more pleasant as well. Cornelya was friendlier with "
"everyone, her 'Princess of Blood' façade seemingly gone – even if the "
"perspicacious Valerya still found her gloomily staring at the ocean at times "
"–; Olokun finally accepted his own feelings and returned Derceto's in kind; "
"Algil was much more lighthearted, even Kenshiro was more carefree than Tenma "
"had seen him to be since they were children."
msgstr ""
"Ese viaje también fue mucho más agradable. Cornelya se mostró más amistosa "
"con todos, su fachada de «Princesa de la Sangre» parecía haber desaparecido —"
"aunque la perspicaz Valerya todavía la encontraba a veces mirando "
"sombríamente al océano—; Olokun finalmente aceptó sus propios sentimientos y "
"correspondió los de Derceto; Algil estaba mucho más alegre, e incluso "
"Kenshiro se mostraba más despreocupado de lo que Tenma lo había visto desde "
"que eran niños."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:736
msgid ""
"Tenma herself also had been changed considerably by the events in Netjer-Ta, "
"and not just in terms of power. If once she saw Myra as some sort of "
"parasite stuck to her against her will, now she saw – and, more importantly, "
"accepted – the 'other woman' as part of herself, embracing her memories and "
"feelings as her own."
msgstr ""
"La propia Tenma también había cambiado considerablemente por los eventos en "
"Netjer-Ta, y no solo en términos de poder. Si antes veía a Myra como una "
"especie de parásito adherido a ella contra su voluntad, ahora veía —y, más "
"importante aún, aceptaba— a la «otra mujer» como parte de sí misma, "
"abrazando sus recuerdos y sentimientos como propios."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:740
msgid ""
"And so she embraced Myra's burden as well: whenever she found herself alone "
"on the ship's prow, usually at nightfall, she held the Sky Soul in her hands "
"and peered into it. There, in the eerie depths of the jewel, she could see "
"the destruction of Garet-Desh and of Hiera'Shirsha, the deaths of Maat, "
"Abhai, Akashia and so many others, the Battle of the Crystal Tower, even the "
"corruption of Menon Hekare, the legendary Master of Four Lights... She "
"watched all the chaos and all the suffering caused by Svarballi, and felt "
"her resolve grow stronger."
msgstr ""
"Y así también abrazó la carga de Myra: cada vez que se encontraba sola en la "
"proa del barco, generalmente al anochecer, sostenía el Alma del Cielo en sus "
"manos y miraba en su interior. Allí, en las inquietantes profundidades de la "
"joya, podía ver la destrucción de Garet-Desh y de Hiera'Shirsha, las muertes "
"de Maat, Abhai, Akashia y tantos otros, la Batalla de la Torre de Cristal, "
"incluso la corrupción de Menon Hekare, el legendario Maestro de las Cuatro "
"Luces… Observaba todo el caos y todo el sufrimiento causado por Svarballi, y "
"sentía que su determinación se fortalecía."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:744
msgid ""
"After a mere fifteen days, the sailors spotted the ancient towers of Ifeh, "
"the oldest surviving city of the Chomi who inhabited Arajunna, and a secret "
"ally of New Maat'Kare. Trusting Olokun's friendship with Ifeh's authorities, "
"the group had decided to prepare for the crossing of the dangerous Arajunnan "
"midlands there; but, as their ship docked on the busy Chomi port, they saw "
"that their journey on that continent would be much harder than they "
"originally expected..."
msgstr ""
"Tras solo quince días, los marineros avistaron las antiguas torres de Ifeh, "
"la ciudad sobreviviente más antigua de los chomi que habitaban Arajunna, y "
"un aliado secreto de Nueva Maat'Kare. Confiando en la amistad de Olokun con "
"las autoridades de Ifeh, el grupo había decidido prepararse allí para cruzar "
"las peligrosas tierras medias de Arajunna; pero, al atracar su barco en el "
"concurrido puerto chomi, vieron que su viaje por ese continente sería mucho "
"más difícil de lo que originalmente esperaban…"

#. [part]
#. [time], id=dreamland
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:749
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/schedules.cfg:154
msgid "Dreamland"
msgstr "Tierra de los Sueños"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:759
msgid ""
"Crossing that veil was easily one of the strangest experience Tenma had ever "
"had. She felt the difference in mediums as she moved from the Land of the "
"Dead into the Dreamland quite intensely; it was like swimming from warm "
"water into a very cold pool."
msgstr ""
"Cruzar ese velo fue fácilmente una de las experiencias más extrañas que "
"Tenma había tenido jamás. Sintió la diferencia de medios con gran intensidad "
"al pasar de la Tierra de los Muertos a la Tierra de los Sueños; era como "
"nadar desde agua tibia a una piscina muy fría."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:763
msgid ""
"Once she got used to the 'atmosphere' of the Dreamland, she noticed that she "
"no longer needed to use her soul senses in order to locate herself; in fact, "
"she could feel, hear, see and smell again, but all these senses seemed "
"strangely amplified – stranger still, the feeling of surreality was much "
"greater there. She was, as she soon noticed, like in a dream..."
msgstr ""
"Una vez que se acostumbró a la «atmósfera» de la Tierra de los Sueños, notó "
"que ya no necesitaba usar sus sentidos del alma para ubicarse; de hecho, "
"podía volver a sentir, oír, ver y oler, pero todos estos sentidos parecían "
"extrañamente amplificados —aún más extraño, la sensación de irrealidad era "
"mucho mayor allí. Estaba, como pronto notó, como en un sueño…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:774
msgid ""
"Tenma had never felt so frightened in her life: as she walked amidst the "
"burning ruins and flaming trees, she easily recognised that landscape, for "
"that was the same landscape she'd grown up knowing: she was back to Kodakuni."
msgstr ""
"Tenma nunca en su vida se había sentido tan asustada: mientras caminaba "
"entre las ruinas ardientes y los árboles en llamas, reconoció fácilmente ese "
"paisaje, pues era el mismo paisaje que había conocido al crecer: había "
"vuelto a Kodakuni."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:778
msgid ""
"It wasn't difficult to find evidence that the destruction had been wrought "
"not by god-like beings, but by humans - and humans from Wesnoth. However, "
"that was no relief: invoking her Dragon-Slayer wings, Tenma flew towards "
"Umashima, the Sogen's greatest city. The time to reunite the Kings and "
"Queens of Irdya had come sooner than she'd expected, and she was running out "
"of time – but first, she had to finish what had set her on that journey, "
"nearly two years earlier..."
msgstr ""
"No fue difícil encontrar evidencia de que la destrucción no había sido obra "
"de seres divinos, sino de humanos —y humanos de Wesnoth. Sin embargo, eso no "
"era un alivio: invocando sus alas de Cazadragones, Tenma voló hacia "
"Umashima, la mayor ciudad de los Sogen. El momento de reunir a los Reyes y "
"Reinas de Irdya había llegado antes de lo que esperaba, y se le estaba "
"acabando el tiempo —pero primero tenía que terminar lo que la había puesto "
"en ese viaje, casi dos años antes…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:783
msgid "Part IX: March of Kings"
msgstr "Parte IX: Marcha de Reyes"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:787
msgid "Rise of Chaos"
msgstr "Ascenso del Caos"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:797
msgid ""
"News of the Imperial Army's defeat at Umashima spread like wildfire "
"throughout Kodakuni. Inspired by the tales – often exaggerated – of Tenma's "
"exploits, the other Sogen towns and villages staged their own uprisings; and "
"the Wesnothian outposts, too stunned by those news and without Imperial "
"support, could not withstand that wave of rebellion. In the days following "
"the Battle of Umashima, the Sogen capital received news after news of "
"successive triumphs all over Kodakuni, turning the Independence Day into the "
"Independence Fortnight."
msgstr ""
"La noticia de la derrota del Ejército Imperial en Umashima se extendió como "
"reguero de pólvora por todo Kodakuni. Inspirados por los relatos —a menudo "
"exagerados— de las hazañas de Tenma, las demás ciudades y aldeas sogen "
"organizaron sus propios levantamientos; y los puestos wesnothianos, atónitos "
"por esas noticias y sin apoyo imperial, no pudieron resistir esa ola de "
"rebelión. En los días posteriores a la Batalla de Umashima, la capital sogen "
"recibió noticia tras noticia de triunfos sucesivos por todo Kodakuni, "
"convirtiendo el Día de la Independencia en la Quincena de la Independencia."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:801
msgid ""
"Tenma was the only one not sharing in the joy that took over Kodakuni. She "
"worried about the crisis in the West, and even more about her friends; not "
"even her strolls amidst the blooming cherry trees around Umashima gave her "
"any peace of mind. On the fifth day after the battle, however, she gathered "
"with Ikki and Yamamoto and declared that she could not tarry there any "
"longer."
msgstr ""
"Tenma fue la única que no compartía la alegría que se apoderó de Kodakuni. "
"Se preocupaba por la crisis en el Oeste, y aún más por sus amigos; ni "
"siquiera sus paseos entre los cerezos en flor alrededor de Umashima le daban "
"paz mental. Sin embargo, al quinto día después de la batalla, se reunió con "
"Ikki y Yamamoto y declaró que no podía quedarse allí por más tiempo."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:805
msgid ""
"Thus, in the following morning, a contingent of hardened Sogen warriors "
"gathered at the Elder's command. Ikki was appointed as their commander under "
"Tenma, as she would be the one deciding where they should go. Thus, under "
"some protest by civilians who did not understand why their friends and "
"relatives had to leave Kodakuni, the Sogen army left Umashima towards the "
"setting sun."
msgstr ""
"Así, a la mañana siguiente, un contingente de endurecidos guerreros sogen se "
"reunió bajo el mando del Anciano. Ikki fue nombrado su comandante bajo "
"Tenma, ya que ella sería quien decidiría a dónde debían ir. Así, pese a "
"algunas protestas de civiles que no entendían por qué sus amigos y "
"familiares tenían que dejar Kodakuni, el ejército sogen partió de Umashima "
"hacia el sol poniente."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:809
msgid ""
"It took them only two days to cross Kodakuni's border and enter the Sunrise "
"Road. That path meandered through the northern mountains before going "
"westwards, bordering the Great Inner Sea and crossing the Diurna Plains. The "
"sighting of the ever-raging Firecloud Peak signalled that they were about to "
"enter Wesnoth proper – and also that they had reached the rising tides of "
"destruction..."
msgstr ""
"Solo les tomó dos días cruzar la frontera de Kodakuni y entrar en el Camino "
"del Amanecer. Ese sendero serpenteaba por las montañas del norte antes de "
"dirigirse al oeste, bordeando el Gran Mar Interior y cruzando las Llanuras "
"Diurnas. El avistamiento del siempre furioso Pico Nube de Fuego señaló que "
"estaban a punto de entrar en el Wesnoth propiamente dicho —y también que "
"habían llegado a las crecientes mareas de destrucción…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:820
msgid ""
"Leaving the Sogen and some drakes at Valerya's Fire Sanctuary, Tenma and "
"Veshtar Joohn set out for the dreaded Flamebreath Desert. As she flew over "
"the golden sea of sand, nestled on the Mother Queen's huge hand, the young "
"woman understood why that region was widely regarded as the world's hottest "
"place; even her sweat seemed to evaporate as soon as it emerged on her skin."
msgstr ""
"Dejando a los sogen y algunos dracos en el Santuario de Fuego de Valerya, "
"Tenma y Veshtar Joohn partieron hacia el temido Desierto del Aliento de "
"Llama. Mientras volaba sobre el mar dorado de arena, acurrucada en la enorme "
"mano de la Reina Madre, la joven comprendió por qué esa región era "
"ampliamente considerada el lugar más caliente del mundo; incluso su sudor "
"parecía evaporarse apenas surgía en su piel."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:824
msgid ""
"At certain height, however, the heat such a level that Tenma had to shield "
"herself with magic to avoid being scorched by the air itself. Even the "
"drakes seemed troubled by the heat."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, a cierta altura, el calor alcanzó tal nivel que Tenma tuvo que "
"protegerse con magia para evitar ser abrasada por el mismo aire. Incluso los "
"dracos parecían molestos por el calor."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:828
msgid ""
"It was then that they finally sighted what had looked, from afar, to be a "
"very long mountain range. As the retinue flew over it, they saw that it was "
"actually the ridge of an immense caldera. Inside it, through the thick smoke "
"rising from the ground, Tenma could see the silhouettes of huge towers, each "
"of them capable of sheltering at least ten drakes as large as Veshtar Joohn, "
"all made of dark volcanic rock. The drakes landed about three kilometres "
"into the crater; for, as the Mother Queen explained, as long as they were on "
"the ruins of Aghayu, not even the skies would be safe..."
msgstr ""
"Fue entonces cuando finalmente avistaron lo que desde lejos parecía una "
"cordillera muy larga. Al volar sobre ella, vieron que en realidad era el "
"borde de una inmensa caldera. Dentro, a través del denso humo que se elevaba "
"del suelo, Tenma pudo ver las siluetas de enormes torres, cada una capaz de "
"albergar al menos diez dracos tan grandes como Veshtar Joohn, todas hechas "
"de roca volcánica oscura. Los dracos aterrizaron a unos tres kilómetros "
"dentro del cráter; pues, como explicó la Reina Madre, mientras estuvieran en "
"las ruinas de Aghayu, ni siquiera los cielos serían seguros"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:839
msgid ""
"The new Queen-in-the-Air set for the Heart Mountains as soon as she left "
"Tenma at the Fire Sanctuary; but Tenma herself decided to linger there a "
"little longer, for she did not want to spoil Aeldhoryan's and Natsu's moment "
"– after all, the lovers hadn't seen each other in nearly twenty years. "
"However, it was the couple that urged them all to go to leave; Valerya's "
"students decided to follow Tenma, hoping to find their master again."
msgstr ""
"La nueva Reina-en-el-Aire partió hacia las Montañas del Corazón tan pronto "
"como dejó a Tenma en el Santuario de Fuego; pero la propia Tenma decidió "
"quedarse allí un poco más, pues no quería arruinar el momento de Aeldhoryan "
"y Natsu —después de todo, los amantes no se habían visto en casi veinte "
"años. Sin embargo, fue la pareja quien les instó a todos a partir; los "
"estudiantes de Valerya decidieron seguir a Tenma, esperando encontrar "
"nuevamente a su maestra."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:843
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, the elvish capital of Metheldur was far from the Firecloud "
"Peak; and, while they entered and crossed the vast Lins-Elens, the "
"necromancer already launched his siege on the greatest city of the elves..."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, la capital élfica de Metheldur estaba lejos del Pico Nube de "
"Fuego; y mientras entraban y cruzaban el vasto Lins-Elens, el nigromante ya "
"había lanzado su asedio sobre la mayor ciudad de los elfos…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:854
msgid ""
"Cornelya did have a great deal of work to do: rebuild the kingdom's "
"defences, attend the ravaged elvish settlements, destroy the undead "
"remnants, restore the dead woods... That night, however, she allotted some "
"time for herself. After Gil-Thelyon's funeral, she asked for the company of "
"her brother, her friends and her still unofficial parents-in-law; Tenma had "
"to hold back her laughter as she saw Natsu's reluctance as Kenshiro and "
"Cornelya confessed their love for each other – though, in the end, the Sogen "
"priestess was warm enough to hug her new daughter-in-law."
msgstr ""
"Cornelya tenía mucho trabajo por hacer: reconstruir las defensas del reino, "
"atender los asentamientos élficos devastados, destruir los restos no-"
"muertos, restaurar los bosques muertos… Esa noche, sin embargo, se reservó "
"algo de tiempo para sí misma. Tras el funeral de Gil-Thelyon, pidió la "
"compañía de su hermano, sus amigos y sus aún no oficiales suegros; Tenma "
"tuvo que contener la risa al ver la reticencia de Natsu mientras Kenshiro y "
"Cornelya confesaban su amor mutuo —aunque, al final, la sacerdotisa sogen "
"fue lo suficientemente cálida como para abrazar a su nueva nuera."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:858
msgid ""
"Afterwards, Kenshiro and Cornelya disappeared for many hours; Gelendras told "
"Tenma that they had last been sighted heading for the Glimmering Willows. "
"The new couple only appeared again in the following morning; some elves "
"commented amongst themselves that their new queen seemed happy like she had "
"not been since she was a child, but they were sensible enough to avoid "
"commenting on that any further."
msgstr ""
"Después, Kenshiro y Cornelya desaparecieron durante muchas horas; Gelendras "
"le dijo a Tenma que habían sido vistos por última vez dirigiéndose a los "
"Sauces Resplandecientes. La nueva pareja solo reapareció a la mañana "
"siguiente; algunos elfos comentaron entre sí que su nueva reina parecía "
"feliz como no lo había estado desde que era niña, pero fueron lo "
"suficientemente sensatos como para no comentar más al respecto."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:862
msgid ""
"Also in the following morning, Tenma gathered the surviving drakes and "
"prepared to leave. Cornelya would stay and take care of her people, and so "
"did Kenshiro and Natsu. Aeldhoryan, however, decided to follow Tenma; after "
"all, his country was in a dire crisis. Dragana also stayed at Metheldur, but "
"she promised that, should they need it, Tenma and Aeldhoryan could count on "
"her aid."
msgstr ""
"También a la mañana siguiente, Tenma reunió a los dracos sobrevivientes y se "
"preparó para partir. Cornelya se quedaría a cuidar de su pueblo, y también "
"lo hicieron Kenshiro y Natsu. Aeldhoryan, sin embargo, decidió seguir a "
"Tenma; después de todo, su país estaba en una grave crisis. Dragana también "
"se quedó en Metheldur, pero prometió que, si lo necesitaban, Tenma y "
"Aeldhoryan podrían contar con su ayuda."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:866
msgid ""
"Flying as quick as they could, the drakes managed to reach the eastern "
"stretches of the Heart Mountains in two days. That was the first time Tenma "
"saw the range after the Earthenheart's destruction; volcanic activity had "
"decreased but a little, though new roads could now be seen meandering "
"through the mountains. Tenma was heartened to see that the Northerners were "
"trying to rebuild their homes, but that ended as they neared the Dwarven "
"Doors, headquarters of the Northern Alliance..."
msgstr ""
"Volando lo más rápido que pudieron, los dracos lograron llegar a las "
"extensiones orientales de las Montañas del Corazón en dos días. Era la "
"primera vez que Tenma veía la cordillera tras la destrucción del Corazón "
"Terrestre; la actividad volcánica había disminuido solo un poco, aunque "
"ahora se podían ver nuevos caminos serpenteando por las montañas. Tenma se "
"animó al ver que los norteños intentaban reconstruir sus hogares, pero eso "
"terminó al acercarse a las Puertas Enanas, cuartel general de la Alianza del "
"Norte…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:877
msgid ""
"Olokun did not like seeing everyone go their separate ways again so soon "
"after reuniting, but they had no choice; with both Galdra and Svarballi on "
"the loose, they were lucky that they could still think about mounting a "
"proper counter-attack at all."
msgstr ""
"A Olokun no le gustaba ver a todos separarse de nuevo tan pronto después de "
"reunirse, pero no tenían opción; con Galdra y Svarballi sueltos, tenían "
"suerte de que aún pudieran pensar en montar un contraataque adecuado."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:881
msgid ""
"As if that was not enough, they now had another matter to worry about: the "
"disturbance in the magic currents, which was much more serious than they had "
"anticipated. Though its cause was unknown, its effects could easily be "
"noticed in the following days: the younger mages in Aeldhoryan's forces, to "
"their horror, found themselves suddenly unable to harness their own magic. "
"Even some of the more experienced mages had trouble invoking their spells, "
"though the Umbra mages seemed unaffected."
msgstr ""
"Como si eso no fuera suficiente, ahora tenían otro asunto de qué "
"preocuparse: la perturbación en las corrientes mágicas, que era mucho más "
"grave de lo que habían anticipado. Aunque su causa era desconocida, sus "
"efectos se pudieron notar fácilmente en los días siguientes: los magos más "
"jóvenes en las fuerzas de Aeldhoryan, para su horror, se encontraron de "
"repente incapaces de canalizar su propia magia. Incluso algunos de los magos "
"más experimentados tenían problemas para invocar sus hechizos, aunque los "
"magos Umbra parecían no verse afectados."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:885
msgid ""
"On their way to the White Woods, they found traces left by Wesir indicating "
"that he had gone east after his defeat at Dan'Tonk. Elemental scouts cut off "
"his escape routes, cornering him, shepherding him to a place of his enemies' "
"choosing. They rejoiced when they found signs that Wesir had taken refuge in "
"the White Woods; there, they would be able to complete two goals at the same "
"time. But neither Olokun, nor Ankhmare, nor Aeldhoryan felt any relief; for "
"they knew how much more dangerous a trapped beast could become..."
msgstr ""
"En su camino hacia los Bosques Blancos, encontraron rastros dejados por "
"Wesir que indicaban que había ido al este tras su derrota en Dan'Tonk. "
"Exploradores elementales cortaron sus rutas de escape, acorralándolo y "
"guiándolo hacia un lugar elegido por sus enemigos. Se regocijaron al "
"encontrar señales de que Wesir se había refugiado en los Bosques Blancos; "
"allí podrían cumplir dos objetivos al mismo tiempo. Pero ni Olokun, ni "
"Ankhmare, ni Aeldhoryan sintieron alivio alguno; pues sabían cuán más "
"peligroso podía volverse una bestia acorralada…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:896
msgid ""
"That was easily the worst moment in Tenma's life. Even when Knalga was "
"destroyed, she felt that she had done everything that she could to prevent "
"that from happening; that she had only failed to save the Earthenheart "
"because she had not known Aelvar's plans soon enough. But now, she was as "
"well-prepared as she thought possible, and still, with all her power, she "
"had been forced to watch powerlessly as Svarballi destroyed the Windsong..."
msgstr ""
"Ese fue fácilmente el peor momento en la vida de Tenma. Incluso cuando "
"Knalga fue destruida, sintió que había hecho todo lo que pudo para evitar "
"que ocurriera; que solo había fallado en salvar el Corazón Terrestre porque "
"no había conocido los planes de Aelvar lo suficientemente pronto. Pero "
"ahora, estaba tan bien preparada como creía posible y, aun así, con todo su "
"poder, se había visto obligada a mirar impotente cómo Svarballi destruía a "
"las Hijas del Viento…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:899
msgid ""
"But Svarballi himself did not finish the Order, for he had another prey in "
"mind – a prey he would not let escape again..."
msgstr ""
"Pero el propio Svarballi no terminó con la Orden, pues tenía otra presa en "
"mente —una presa que no dejaría escapar nuevamente…"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:909
msgid ""
"And they certainly moved fast. Those trolls, dwarves and black elves, who "
"ferociously tried to kill each other a mere three years before, worked "
"together to take Tenma to her goal with even greater effort. She needed no "
"further motivation to go on in that war, but as she watched their dedicated "
"teamwork, the Yasai felt her resolve grow even stronger."
msgstr ""
"Y ciertamente se movieron rápido. Esos trolls, enanos y elfos negros, que "
"ferozmente habían intentado matarse unos a otros apenas tres años antes, "
"trabajaron juntos para llevar a Tenma a su objetivo con aún mayor esfuerzo. "
"No necesitaba más motivación para seguir en esa guerra, pero al ver su "
"trabajo en equipo dedicado, la Yasai sintió que su determinación se "
"fortalecía aún más."

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:913
msgid ""
"And their efficiency was astounding; moving at uncanny speed through the "
"underground maze, they reached their goal in a mere fortnight. Tenma "
"suggested her allies to send out scouts after Cornelya, Algil or Udhark, "
"then she herself flew to Weldyn, the capital of Wesnoth. Against Svarballi, "
"she was willing to get even the hated Iron Emperor's help - and, after all "
"the destruction wrought by Galdra, he certainly would be more willing to "
"hear her out..."
msgstr ""
"Y su eficiencia era asombrosa; moviéndose a una velocidad inquietante por el "
"laberinto subterráneo, alcanzaron su objetivo en apenas quince días. Tenma "
"sugirió a sus aliados enviar exploradores tras Cornelya, Algil o Udhark, "
"luego ella misma voló a Weldyn, la capital de Wesnoth. Contra Svarballi, "
"estaba dispuesta a aceptar incluso la ayuda del odiado Emperador de Hierro —"
"y, tras toda la destrucción causada por Galdra, ciertamente estaría más "
"dispuesto a escucharla"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:925
msgid "Final: Dracomachia"
msgstr "Final: Dracomachia"

#. [part]
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/intros.cfg:935
msgid ""
"The most fearsome thing is not death itself; but to live on and see everyone "
"and everything you cherish gone."
msgstr ""
"Lo más temible no es la muerte en sí; sino seguir viviendo y ver a todos y "
"todo lo que aprecias desaparecer."

#. [set_menu_item], id=Valerya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:22
msgid "Summon Aragwaithi Reinforcements"
msgstr "Reclamar Refuerzos Aragwaithi"

#. [message], speaker=Olokun
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:33
msgid ""
"From now on the battle will rage on more violently than ever... Valerya, "
"please send out the sign, and let us hope the Aragwaithi will fulfil their "
"promise..."
msgstr ""
"Desde ahora la batalla arderá con más violencia que nunca… Valerya, por "
"favor envía la señal, y esperemos que los aragwaithi cumplan su promesa…"

#. [message], speaker=Cornelya
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:93
msgid ""
"Fast and faithful, as expected from folk who claim cultural kinship with "
"elves."
msgstr ""
"Rápidos y fieles, como era de esperar de un pueblo que reclama parentesco "
"cultural con los elfos."

#. [message], speaker=Tenma
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:97
msgid ""
"Just shut up, you... (shouting) Hey, Aragwaithi! We're attacking "
"Castelfrost, could you please deal with the outer sentries for us? If they "
"catch us from behind, we'll be smashed like a big fat bug!"
msgstr ""
"Solo cállate, tú… (gritando) ¡Oigan, aragwaithi! ¡Estamos atacando "
"Castelfrost, podrían encargarse de los centinelas exteriores por nosotros? "
"¡Si nos atrapan por detrás, nos aplastarán como a un bicho gordo!"

#. [message], speaker=Varyon
#: Aria_of_the_Dragon_Slayer/utils/scenario-utils.cfg:101
msgid ""
"Understood, friends. Aragwaithi, charge! Let us make sure our land remains "
"safe for our children!"
msgstr ""
"Entendido, amigos. ¡Aragwaithi, carguen! ¡Asegurémonos de que nuestra tierra "
"siga siendo segura para nuestros hijos!"

